reviewTitle: The Dark Horse is a great place for a casual meal and drink!

reviewText: we arrived for a late lunch and we were seated immediately we all got burgers all good but not exceptional the atmosphere is what really makes this place great loads of cool artifacts unlike other reviews a waitress came and took our order the food took a little bit to arrive but nothing outrageous overall a good experience
i cannot wait for this bar to close the manager was very rude to my group of 8 people too many bars in boulder for us to go out of our way to go here

amazed at the friendliness of the staff all of them that kind of service and engaging people is rare these days yes the food was tasty but its the staff that takes this over the top you order at a station then pick up your food drinks at the bar and they are so helpful and seem happy to be there
it was a great spot for a casual team dinner nice character a bit loud with lots of surprises everywhere the chicken burger was amazing

the 3 joint wings are deceptively small you would think you are getting huge wings when you hear they serve them with the flat and drumsticks still intact in reality there is little meat on the wings dry rub seasoning was good though just a rip off for 15 the red pepper poppers were excellent i dont like the taste of jalapenos so the red jalapeno was a nice twist a less hot more smoky tasting jalapeno raspberry sauce was a bit odd as a dipper so i just ate them as is tons of cream cheese and well breaded

what an eclectic place so neat love the logg cabin type structure lots of nooks and separate areas to enjoy drinks and food together funky decor and quirky styling great place to play eye spy haha we are here for lunch while passing through boulder you order at the counter and pick up at window no table service food was good perfectly fine sandwich for ten bucks no complaints soft drinks are refillable at bar
classic college bar with endless curly fries burgers wings type faire ceiling covered w old buggies and various antiques many ups and downs booth tables pool video games etcbeware wings are hot
this place definitely had a college student drinking spot vibe but they gave great portions and the food was good servers were very friendly as well

a hidden gem from the outside this place looks a bit sketch when you enterwow the ambiance and decor is absolutely stunning only photos can capture this the food very good we recommend the chicken tenders make sure you ask for them in basted in sauce the onion rings are very crispy but a bit lean on the onion the gourmet hamburgers are very large and stacked tall with toppings the staff are very friendly definitely recommend popping in
reviewTitle: A hidden gem; wait until you walk in!

reviewText: burger and fries this is the second time this week that ive ordered the blues burger and fries burger was incredible but fries both times were so salty that i was unable to eat them i love salt and always end up adding salt to my fries at other restaurantsnot at the dark horse the first time i ordered the fries i thought it was a fluke second time ive learned my lesson and will never order their fries again

met a friend for lunch nice day was able to be seated outside pretty good burger not great great service server checked up on us as necessary good music not so loud you cant have a conversation right across the street from some large cu dorms so i imagine they are pretty hopping on the weekend the bathroom door trick is stupid just stop it

had great burgers and fries very fresh burger toppings and side salads fries were very good and red pepper poppers were perfect felt very comfortable eating here as staff made everything easy and safe

reviewText: we havent eaten at an iron skillet in years we ate from the buffet i have to say this is some of the best chicken potatoes and gravy i have had in a long time the salad bar was fresh and selection good yes we will eat here again

nice place to stop when youre on the road foods ok little overpriced and if youre eating off the buffet if you dont get there when its fresh it can be a little tough and we can try see a little bit but youre on the road so youre limited staff there a little slow at times its not the first time that ive eaten here so i can say that
they want you in and they want you out even faster but she was nice about itstrange experience the buffet was dried up food and ordering off the menu was not much better

excellent authentic decoration fantastic turkish foods served by very sympa people thank you
food is great qualitytry their combination platters you get to sample a little bit of everything staff is even betteralways courteous and willing to accommodate your meal requests

situated in a small place in a residential neighborhood of cliffside park the restaurant has some good original turkish foods that are worhty the visit if you enjoy having some drinks make sure to bring some of your own we brought some wine bottles and this very kind hostess provided us with the glasses awesome place

my brother and his family were visiting from dakota they had never been to a turkish restaurant there are none in dakota they wanted to try new things and my wife and i love cinar my brother and his family absolutely loved the food there are a lot of turkish restaurants in the cliffsidefairview area my wife and i have tried most of them and i still maintain that this is one of the best

just has a fabulous meal at the very authentic turkish restaurant excellent service with top quality ingredients in the dishes served

we were a group of 10 people and had visited to celebrate a birthdaythe staff attitude completely suckedthey did not even cut the birthday cake for usand were really rude and haughty during every interaction they did not even offer tea for a second time despite asking food was really blandnothing to comment on

nothing fancy about just good friendly casual turkish food with a very good menu portions are good size and the service is on point cinar offer a family friendly environment but you wont go wrong bringing a date here

reviewText: we were 4 adults with a baby and went here for dinner on a saturday night the staff were very pleasant and accomodating we enjoyed the chicken and vegetable soup and grilled eggplant spread as appetizers we sampled the stuffed eggplant lamb shish kebab and adana kebabs all were delicious we also enjoyed a custard similar to flan and the kadayif sweet cheese pastry overall a great experience and we will be back on our next visit to cliffside park

reviewText: truly outstanding each beer was better than the last with the south park calob merica pale ale taking the gold wife had the adult mac and cheese which was amazing and i had the fish and chips which were perfectly crispy and flaky hats off to the entire staff and brewmaster i cant recommend wynkoop enough
do not get their macandcheese it is a large waste of money has nearly no taste and no cheese 010 would not recommend ever getting it
good beer but they do charge a rip off 35 junk fee so be aware but i just deducted off the tip so no sweat off my back but be aware of this rip off junk fee when visiting
reviewTitle: Good beer but be aware of rip off junk fee

reviewText: was heading over to the market street food court when my spouse and i decided to try wynkoop this turnedout to be a great choice though its only pub food the quality was well above average and at a fair price the wait staff were very friendly and attentive definitely a repeat visit upon my return visit to denver

we visited wynkoop brewing company twice during our time in denver very easy to find a short walk from union station several good beers on tap and delicious wings and fries a bit disappointed in the nashville hot chicken sandwich thoughjust hot sauce poured on top of the chicken loved the atmosphere and will visit again the next time i am in denver restrooms are down a flight of stairs in the basement good and friendly service 3 service charge added to bill for kitchen staff
we enjoyed our dinner here they brew some nice beers and the food menu has enough options for everyone they dont take reservations but the place is large and we didnt have a wait

went here late saturday morning they were just opening up and we were the third pair of guests we sat outdoor and before it was 12pm half the terrace was full already we ordered a 5sampler platter bison burger sweet potato waffle fries coleslaw and a saturdaysunday only available avocado toast with herb cream cheese the food looked remarkably well and the taste was the same high quality comfort food they checked in on us on regular occasion we enjoyed the time here and continued our journey with a full stomach
reviewTitle: Great comfort food and craft beers

reviewText: nice patio and super kind staff im not the biggest beer drinker but my husband got some good ones in a flight i would go back
cool staff serving some of the best beer in the city in a good location in a historic building prices were average but considering the quality of the beer i wasnt complaining

great food enjoyed the buffalo chicken sandwich and companion had a grilled salmon on a salad their beer was awesome we had their lager and a cider would recommend for a meal or drink great and timely brewery
reviewTitle: A good spot for a bite to eat and brew

reviewText: stopped by for drinks had a flight of 4 to sample and all were good good service at the bar helpful informative and friendly

on our way to ball game tonight stopped for dinner at wynkoop i had their cheese steak with sweet potato waffle fries i would have preferred a roll with less bulk since there was a lot to eat my spouse had a beef burger with swiss cheese and our daughter had the beef burger with cheddar cheese both enjoyed their sandwiches we also enjoyed their wixa weiss beer with our dinner service was prompt and the food very tasty

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: very cozy and welcoming little cafe ive been coming here for years i love their drinks most recently i got the caramel frappe and that was lovely the empanadas are delicious especially the brisket one and the desserts i ordered dulce de leche birthday cakes here before and i highly recommend those for smaller individual desserts i can recommend the chocolate covered dulce de leche tart or the killer layers of pastry dough dulce de leche and meringue

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: stopped on a whim the empanadas were excellent and it was the best caramel frappucino ive ever had the pastries were great as was the service great place

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: this place is relaxing with a pleasant atmosphere and a hidden jewel close to dfw airport good for small business meetings or just enjoy a coffee with someone or like in todays case a tea solo the one mayor issue is that the pastries are the best around here and its impossible to stay away from them it would even be a sin even if youre trying to loss weight you need to try them or the cakes hope you enjoy this place as i do
reviewTitle: Relaxing, pleasant with one mayor issue...

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: found this wonderful place in a nondiscreet open air mall coffee was excellent as well as the pastries enormous variety of international flavors will come back

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i loved this place with its mounds of cookies and pastries which were all delicious i tried quite a few of them but in my haste i failed to take note of their names their coffee was good too but the maté fell flat which someplace that specializes in argentinian cuisine should be able to handle but that had great empanadas to compensate i went their every day of my trip to the dfw area

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: we tried a number of pastries empanadas coffee cocoa i love this place every bite was savored i am only sad that i dont live nearby this will forever be a dfw stop for us from now on all was delicious stop here for sweets that are not too sweet unlike american bakeries

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i just happened to pass by this bakery and out of curiosity i went inside and found out they have a lot of selections of cakes pies pastries and empanadas i ordered a frappe and coconut tart and it was good the coffee ️ house is small but overall my first visit was good

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: a grand surprise wonderful pastries and empanadas favorites were the ricotta tart and the ham and cheeses empanada coffee is robust and modestly priced my second trip and empanadas showed a consistent flavor and marvelous crust took a few home reheated ham and cheese for seconds in microwave turned out great

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: heard about this place and sauntered in one sunday morning incredible wonderful looking cakes and empanadas the seating area is small but comfortable i liked the cans of diet coke all soda in cans actually the cream on the cakes is always fresh with a good variety of empanadas including an offer to make custom versions too highly recommended best cake store i have seen or found in dfw try it out

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: sad to report that i finally found a place that provide delicious and scrumptious desserts but the place really needs cleaning probably we visited late in the day and the servers were tired those beautiful glass counters were loaded with fingerprint stains and tables and chairs were dirty
reviewTitle: Scrumptious Dessert But Place Needs Cleaning

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: loved this awesome little coffee shop off 183 and beltline in irving the latte was good the pastries were amazing great coffee shop atmosphere inside with little tables covered outside and the salsa music in the background just added to the fun the empanadas are wonderfully delicate and flavorful we tried the spinach egg and cheese brisket and the beef empanadas empanadas were small 199 each and worth every penny the ground beef had such a wonderful south american seasoning so so good i will be back to try all the empanadas and all the amazing looking pastries too

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: im a regular visitor to this bakery to indulge in their mouthwatering and magnificent pastries and flavorful snacks and it always has been a delightful visit ordered a caramel and cream cake for my sons birthday and everyone loved it will visit here again

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: lots of good looking desserts with good coffee to complement the sweets also sells argentine grocery items small selection reminds people of home

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i am from argentina so i had to go visit them the place is really nice it has a sitting area they have a lot of argentine goodies i think i bought one of each they were really really good i felt like i was at home again i totally recommend them

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: every time i stop in here i get immediately transported to argentina the food selection is exactly like you would see in the country empanadas horno solamente are tasty with several varieties baked and ready to consume the coffee is just how i like it while in s a go out of your way you will enjoy an escape 5000 miles away in your own back yard most likely because the owner is from mendoza

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i discovered this place shortly after i moved to irving seven years ago the food and pastries are delicious and their mayan mocha is wonderful if they were on my way to work i would be stopping there every day the interior is comfortable and the music they play is enjoyable also the staff is always friendly

this place has food so delicious we dine there usually twice a month we also went to try their new location and i must say they fulfilled my expectations we came food was served perfectly appetizers so good everything was served in a timely manner staff friendly and helpfull great place to take a date or family for diner
went to cinar for first time in january for a friends birthday food and service was great and i found out they deliver delivery now part of my weekly routine

this restaurant was suggested by a cab driver we were glad we decided to follow the advice nice place with an interesting decor good appetizers the adana kebob was awesome service was prompt will definitely return if we are ever in this area again
lets keep this short and sweet go to this restaurant the fried calamari was amazing the adana kebab was amazing and large and the baklava was delicious also its byob
reviewTitle: Best Turkish food I've ever had

reviewText: ニュージャージーでちゃんとしたトルコ料理店 現地の味雰囲気をよく作られていた また次回もお世話になりたいお店
reviewTitle: 間違いないトルコ料理

reviewText: this is seriously one of the best restaurants ive been to its not ultra fine dining 3 michelin stars book 3 months in advance type of deal but the food is pretty authentic and its amazing just absolutely amazing everything off the grill is just so juicy and tender and wonderful the lamb shank for example doesnt need a knife the meat just slides of the bone with a fork what more can you ask for hurry in and try this place
great food and service byo waiterswaitresses helpful and pleasant eaten there several times and never been disappointed
excellent adana kabab and rocca salad average setting and decor chonan salad was not the best nor the stuffed grape leaves will definitely give it another try

we were in the mood for a quick lunch and dropped by to check out cinar which a friend had highly recommended the lunch was even better than expected my shepherd salad was one of the best i had ever tasted my husband gave rave reviews to the mushroom casserole mantar guvec this is now on our favorites list

great experience on a brewery good choice of local beers good food for the kind good service no expresso but regular coffee location and staff help to the overall satisfaction a good choice for a different option
reviewTitle: Nice for a lunch on a brewery

reviewText: stopped in quick for a beer and an appetizer to share server was incredibly friendly and stopped to chat for a few minutes beers were good and split the pretzel normally not big into mustard but theirs was excellent very good outdoor seating with shade
stopped here for dinner with my wife great service nice selection of beer and good food too would recommend the bison burger and kurts mile high beer both were great
reviewTitle: Nice Place for a Beer and Dinner

reviewText: we really enjoy wynkoop it has turned into kind of a old time historic destination the service was pretty slow they seemed to be short staffed the beer was ok
reviewTitle: We always enjoy a stop at Wynkoop.

reviewText: enjoyed fantastic beer here my favorite beer was the hazy train ipa also very good beef burger friendly staff and great that you here can see how they brew

super fun place gather a crowd for a meet and great waitstaff kept drinks flowing nice bbq buffet had access to pool tables and other activities so close to the train station and the hotels around the station such a wonderful time was had by all

decided to fuel up before we took a train to dia airport the location is perfect right by union station the burgers and fries were very good and perfectly prepared our waitress was nice and efficient and even though we made it clear we were in a hurry the service was fantastic and they even gave drink refills would definitely recommend

they make their own beer which was a small selection but a good range of ipas for different palates we had a hefeweizen and a sour both very good my bison burger was solid and i upgraded to sweet potato fries which were excellent a small surprise was a 1 charge to make it a cheeseburger unfortunately my wifes tuna tartare was a big disappointment to her we split a wedge salad which was very large and pretty tasty the whole thing ran us about 75 so youre paying a little more for location
reviewTitle: Decent food, great beer, a little pricey

reviewText: after ending the free walking tour of downtown denver at union station we stopped here because it was across the street and was recommended by someone my husband ordered the shrimp po boy sandwich and some beers the sandwich was good with ample amount of shrimp and very thick too much had to tear some off bread the service was efficient except that it took a bit long to check out and pay
reviewTitle: good lunch option across from Union Station

reviewText: really enjoyed my brew and burger here no real wow factor but beer was good and burger was inexpensive and tasty just felt it was rather stuck in the 80s and nothing really stood out thankfully did not want a tee shirt as the gift nook was rather barren nothing bad just felt it could be a little better

my wife and i went to wynkoop recently while on vacation in denver it was a great choice we went for lunch on a sunday we were able to sit outside in large area which was great because it was a very nice day we started with the quesosalsa and chips both were excellent my wife had the green chicken chile she loved it but large portion for bowl but great stuff i had the fish and chips and excellent great service and selection of beers and cocktails great experience and highly recommend

we wanted to eat outside but not necessarily on the street this restaurant along with a few along this route has a elevated outdoor eating area inside too which fit the bill our server brittni was wonderful we were in the mood for nachos so we each got a plate with a cup of green chili to top them off hubby had a beer called move your car he loves craft beers and was in quite the dilemma choosing from beers at this brewing company

a brew restaurants like many towns have an old building with great food and service nothing fancy but lots of good food wife had ribs which come with everything under the sun not the fastest service i have ever had but i would return in a heartbeat if i was in the area very near coirs field
reviewTitle: Lots of good food and happy servers

reviewText: we stopped here for a late lunch due to the location and it looked kind of lively on a midweek midafternoon day they were out of the chicken parm sandwich and waitress recommended the traditional one chicken patty was large and skin was super thick and cooked until it was a rock hard not great service was very slow as seems to be the case at many places these days due to staff issues
great location in lodo to try some local brews patio seating was nice limited food options for vegetarians

we wanted to visit the oldest brewpub in denver we found our server great but the beer pretty traditional and not as interesting as many other breweries these days we wanted to try the one different beeryam beer but they were out

came here for some drinks yesterday and we were seated outside as it was a beautiful day we had beer flights and a few shots everything was great and out server was super nice and accommodating will be returning
visited from florida awesome selection of beer and tasty food in a convenient location as well its close to union station
very good ate here while here on a trip to tex from atl great brews and a chill atmosphere keep it up

you have got to go visit this place for ice cream and crêpes i had the and it was out of this world clean friendly service and great atmosphere highly impressed by the owners interaction with the customers

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i worked from here for a few hours and had excellent coffee and a pastry everything was very good and the service provided was great i would easily work here again
reviewTitle: Excellent for a coffee and a pastry

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: have been going there for a year great foodrecently visited at a lunch time around 1130am bad service dirty dishes had to tell employee to wash the utensil before trying to use it on my frappenote to owner please look into thismy spinach empanadas were burnt spinach was so dryyour employees can make you or break you went there august 192015

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: argentina bakery is a very special and unique place in irving when i lived in irving i would frequent this bakery on special evenings for a desert or on a weekend for breakfast now that i live out of town whenever i am in the irvingdallas area i always try to stop buy their delicious empanadas fresh pastries and special deserts that are lightly sweet are some of my favorite items to order truly a unique find in irving texas

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: es una pequeña embajada de sabor argentino matutino íbamos en búsqueda de un starbucks y nos encontramos con este cafecito aunque no son tan rápidos y efectivos como lo es el starbucks se compensa con la variedad y el sabor de la repostería y panadería muy recomendable

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: amazing a rare find in the metroplex reminds me of the coffee houses in south korea love it and will be back everyone must try a sweet here

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: this has become a regular stop in our week the coffee is consistently good the best in town we havent tried everything but everything we did try has been as good as it looks the empanadas have perfect flakey pastry i am getting hungry thinking about them
reviewTitle: Good coffee, good empanadas, good sweets every day!

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i was able to get several finger foods such as pastries and empanadas to take to an outdoor concert at the botanical gardens in ft worth my group loved each one of the various types i brought i will return any time i need something tasty for a group or myself

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: cakes are delicious and they have a lot of argentinian specialists coffee is good as well they sell also argentinian products

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: this place is a hidden gem the coffee is excellent and there are not enough visits to try everything in the case if you are into leche cake or other authentic argentinian pastry this is the place it is not easy to find but worth the effort it is behind the target and if you are fan of tuesday morning make this a two stop event after some serous bargain hunting reward yourself with an expresso or cappuccino and make sure to try the brisket empanadas
reviewTitle: If you want a real pastery to go with great coffee -this is the place

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: the best empanadas in the dallas area and a comfortable place to relax with a coffee and a sweet a great place to be

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: this place is incredible from the moment you walk in you will be pleased fresh cakes and gateau galore fruit tarts and so many pasteries everything is fresh i would go back in a heart beat

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: it is hard to find a nonstarbucks cafe in irving this one is great with wifi good coffee and pretty tasty empanadas if you are not in the mood for sweets

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: the empenadas a baked meat pie that looks like a pastry is the star to me never can decide between the chicken or beef so get both my son likes the little sandwiches in saran wrap this place is always clean and very comfortable we go get lunch and bring back besitos for the office super good coffee drinks expresso etc i like the cafe americano decaf this is a casual place order at the counter many many choices of desserts and pastries great for breakfast or lunch worth a detour
reviewTitle: Me and my whole company staff love Argentina Bakery

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i been coming to this place since theyve opened everything they have here from the coffee and tea pastries cakes and the famous speciality the empanadas are just great mouth wateringis a small cozy place with a small seating area comfortable and wifi is free nice to come and chat with the friends however and wont recomended for families with kids specialy on th eweekends when is crowded they have a great assosrtment of coffee and tea for salealso try the fresh bread they have on a daily basis 200 recomended

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: this is a small bakery with tons of things to choose from i always go for the empanadas and 2 or 3 of them is enough for me to get full my favorites are the ham cheese and spinach and cheese they have coffee and tea for sale and an assortment of amazing pastries most of them made with dulce de leche you can also order the empanadas by the doze ahead of time definitely a must

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: we decided to go here because of all the great reviews we found on line we order 4 different pastries to share my husband and myself and they were moist fresh and delicious this is a bakery coffee house and mini argentina store it was fun and the owner helped us pick out our treats will definitely go back
reviewTitle: This was an amazing bakery full of delicious treats for all

reviewText: i found this location off a mapping gps app while waiting for an evening post dinner business meeting the decor was nice with exposed brick beam staff were knowledgeable and friendly i had sliders and an adult beverage it a location i would visit again if in guymon in business

after a long day on the road hotel staff suggested the pub and they were right i was going to have one if their half pound hamburgers but opted instead for a huge cobb salad and my wife had what she described as the best monte cristo sandwich that she has ever had prices were right also only downside were a couple of loud drunks in the bar area
good food good service and great price great location and the atmosphere is always fun i would recommended to anyone
the food is good the wings and the hot dog are the best i really like to go there and enjoy a good drink with friends and family
we had a large group and called to see if they could take care of us not only did they take care of us they were quick efficient friendly and very accommodating

we dropped in for lunch while passing through guymon we had the pulled pork sandwich with sweet potatertots the pork was nicemoist and tasty the bbq sauce on the side was good also the sweet potatertots were interesting if a bit sweet for my taste seems some sweetener was added very limited tap beer selection service was attentive until it was time for the check i had to search for a waitress i will return
this is our second favorite restaurant in town not expensive and everyone in our group can find something to eat
good service and yummy chicken fried steak sandwich nobody left hungry service was pretty good even though they were pretty busy
we had a bowl of their home made soup it was very good nice hot like i want soup im sure other things are tasty also

check or the copper barit is impressive as a matter of fact the whole place is impressive waitress was excellent food was made from scratch even the salsa and queso had the street tacos lunch special for 5 definitely a value so impressed with this restaurant

traveling through the panhandle on a sunday night opted for the pub side enjoyed just kicking back and watching locals eating drinking sundays in guymon ok no liquor and only 32 beer young men playing pool families watching football etc very enjoyable waitress tender much better than average pub food reasonably priced big portions friendly place ive no qualms about returning next time im that way

have eaten here 4 times now and have never been disappointed very good beer specials and their food ranks near the top in guymon have tried something different every time and liked it all usually busy but staff is good spacious with seating around bar area and out front in restaurant seating area also have a nice room for partiesmeetings

drive to guymond for a lets go for a drive day stopped off here for dinner very clean inside cheap drinks and cheap food food was really good the salad bar was fresh and cold husband had the bacon cheeseburger and enjoyed it i had the fish and chips probably one of the top best catfish i have ever had they hand bread their fish so good
spacious usually well staffed good food great variety tons of sandwiches to choose from great sweet potato fries handles large crowds well
was able to be seated with big group very quickly i had beef enchiladas which were some of the better i have had my wife had the philly which she said was ok would go again
ive met friends here for lunch good place with quick service although sometimes getting the initial order in takes some extra time
typical sports bar but seemed quite large for the area diverse menu with plenty of choices plenty of beer choices too some pool tables for those that feel the need friendly staff and ample parking

we visited here on a busy weekend bike rally and we were seated immediately and our server was helpful and made great suggestions for our dinner we received our food quickly and we all thought it was delicious great adult beverages suggested by our server too moderately priced food and drinks will be visiting pub on the bricks again
lovely wait staff food was outstanding lovely atmosphere close to our hotel just what my husband and i craved after a day of traveling 890 miles
i get all the birthday cakes at this place just love it
reviewTitle: I get all the birthday cakes at this place just love it

reviewText: great place wonderful cakes and pastries weve had many special occasion cakes done here they are the real deal
reviewTitle: Great place, wonderful cakes and pastries.  We've had many special occasion cakes done here- they are the real deal!

reviewText: their tea cookies are the best in town
reviewTitle: Their tea cookies are the best in town!

reviewText: beautiful presentations great desserts
awesome
best cakes ever
heavenly desserts

lotta people eating here so good must be fairly good we had excellent service the buffet looked good with lotsa veggies desserts salad bar meats that i didnt get an opinion of we ordered off of the men the blt grilled cheese were ok the french fries were packaged fried from frozen the chili was some weird brown gravy with so much hot pepper seasoning that i could only take one bite oh yes the buffet is 12 sandwiches 7 with tax
food was tasty this is one of the better petros wish they were all like thisfriendly staff clean

family and i were passing through long road trip and it was good to sit down for a meal but you have to remember that its still gas station food steak tips alfredo and patty melt were all pretty good and very filling my kids had the mac and cheese which was just the simple box stuff food was hot and came out fast its ok if you really want to sit down but you could prob do better looking for a dennys
reviewTitle: Good food. Skip the salad bar.

reviewText: easy highway access great selection menu has something for everyone chicken fries chicken with mashed potatoes country gravy was delicious salad bar left a little to be desired no eggs no carrots some burnt croutons lettuce was very fresh though would stop here again

we were on a trip to grand canyon and saw this off i40 there were lots of cars there so thats always a good sign i got chicken tender basket and my husband got beef tips on taters and toast my husband said it was outstanding it must have been cause he licked the plate my tenders were very good too they have a buffet but i thought it was a little pricey will go back
reviewTitle: really good food for a truck stop

reviewText: the buffet on a saturday night was bbq plus several other items salad and desserts the price was 1399 which seemed high given the location and the fact that bbq west of the mississippi is always a dicey proposition being on a budget i ordered a burger off the menu the result was edible but uninspiring i should have gone with the buffet the salad bar was well stocked considering the location and the food didnt look bad sweet iced tea a rarity outside of the south was a plus friendly service and clean restaurant
reviewTitle: Below average burger; should have gone with the buffet

reviewText: the iron skillet is in the petro gas complex ok menu along with reasonable buffet prompt service and friendly staff this is a general highway pit stop clean restrooms tid bits for sale including nice fudge to take with you in the car
reviewTitle: Good stop, easy on & off highway

reviewText: if traveling its a place to stop and get a great salad as far as other menu items they were decent great tea great salad easy to get to from freeway

great bacon great ham great tea and they bring you your own pitcher service very good our waitress offered to have anything we wanted cooked fresh if the buffet items werent fresh enough we had low expectations coming in but found a very nice stop instead not gourmet but good people
diner piccolo e carino con un ottimo servizio ai tavoli se vuoi fare colazione allamericana questo e un ottimo posto great place great service and food i loved having breakfast there 5 days in a row
the crab cake egg benefits were worth the calories harsh brown was crispy spicy crab meat that was very flavorful
reviewTitle: Great all day breakfast options - lunch available too

reviewText: in a little strip mall and its not very big but it is really quaint staff are very friendly r and very good food not too expensive

this place was buzzing when we visited for a late lunch on a sunday they have a lot of interesting funcreative food options and many creative and delicious drinks i dropped a star though because they forgot about our order and left us sitting there for about an hour before i asked what happened besides that though the staff were friendly and helpful and the food was good its clearly a popular spot
we dined here for an early dinner they were not crowded the building is very cool and our waitress was good all the food we got was really good

we came here a once while in town for gabf and this was a very fun brewery to visit it was packed when we came but we were seated promptly and the service was good overall we had chips and queso which was tasty and paired really well with their triple ipa which was very good we didnt get to try many more of their brews so well have to come back on our next trip to denver

ive been to denver a bunch of times over the last 8 years and ive been to wynkoop numerous times they always have a bunch of beers on tap and they are always changing nice outdoor seating for people watching my favorite past time
reviewTitle: Nice spot for a beer close to Union Station

reviewText: this place was great the food was hearty and really good and the beers were great too this place was big so great for larger parties the mac and cheese was awesome
i had the pleasure of visiting the brewery and sitting outsidewhat a good group of people and terrific beer i will be back on my next trip to denver

we stopped here across from union station after our walking tour huge place but we were able to sit outside which is quite nice service was a bit slow but that may have been due to lunch hour business beer selection of course was wonderful food was ok like beer places no expectations but happy enough location was great and outside with a good view towards union station and people watching on a sunny day
reviewTitle: Not bad for a Touristy Beer Place

reviewText: a big busy brewery in or bordering the lodo neighbourhood we came here one night to meet up and get some drinks we got flights of different beers which were pretty fun and they didnt throw us out for only getting drinks which was nice its quite loud there and busy but overall its a cool place to spend an hour drinking or even getting food it did look good from afar
reviewTitle: A big busy pub worth a visit

reviewText: actually that is just one of several great beers that wynkoop has i ordered a flight of their standard five beers but had to add the mountain oyster stout and the we be yammin happy hour is a great time to visit discounts on food are nice staff was great will definitely return maybe even tonight
reviewTitle: Don't forget the 3B's. Bull's Balls Beer.

reviewText: we took the train from the airport to union station and stumbled over to the nearby wyncoop brewery with our large spinner suitcase what a relief we were warmly welcomed seated beer was great food very good what more could we ask for oh and days later during our visit to the beer exhibit at the colorado history museum we learned that the wynkoop brewery was cofounded by former colorado governor hickenlooper when he was a young man
reviewTitle: Good food, great service, convenient location

reviewText: the ambiance is pretty funlots of space with with games different tables and old denver vibe the service was fantastic the drinks were good but the food was pretty medium mine was barely warm but this is an iconic place and i recommend a visit to the wynkoop in the heart of denver

located around the corner from denvers union train station this trendy brewpub is well worth a stop for both the craft beers and delicious food im not much of a beer guy but i enjoyed their local pale ale and the rueben sandwich was superb we started off with the chips and queso and ended with the peanut butter mousse pieand so glad we did both we excellent bookends to a delicious lunch our server was pleasant and attentive i look forward to visiting wynkoop brewing company on my next visit to denver
reviewTitle: Great Brew Pub in Downtown Denver!

reviewText: arrived in denver lunch time heard denver is known for their beer selection so decided on a brewery pick this place because of the reviews and it was a quick walk from our hotel very pleased food beer flight and atmosphere was perfect im from texas so walking into a brewery with a billiard upstairs plus bar im in heaven so what i enjoyed mexican radio beer with lime mac and cheese and free pool oh and our server was completely helpful and attentive
we had a great time and the service was excellent i was beered out so the bartender recommended sangria two weeks later i am still raving to my friends cozy delicious perfection delicious

this was our first dinner in denver and i thought it was going to be a good one this place was expensive the beer wasnt good the service was terrible and the food was equal to applebees which isnt very good parking in the area is also super expensive

there are many incredible places in north america and the is one not tot to be missed with a daily menu of brewedinhouse beers ales ciders and sodas this downtown location is perfect for any occasion bar seating is excellent dining areas upstairs and down are extremely nice and the noise level of this grand establishment makes conversation not only possible but enjoyable the food offerings are inviting with many options for all ranges from bistro to vegan this is a farmtotable restaurant with 20 beers on tap
reviewTitle: Wonderful environment, Great beer, Great Food, Great People!

reviewText: wynkoop has some very creative and enjoyable beers they have a great selection to choose from so you wont be left picking one of four super hopped beers the kitchen does a good job too it is american bar food with some beer inspired dishes my last visit was green chille vegetarian that was very delicious and wonderfully spicy the wings are great i have my favorite wing spot at home but when i am in town this is where i go the house sauce franks hot sauce based is deliciously peppery

this brewery and restaurant is located so conveniently across from denvers downtown union station and in an old historic building too our adult group stopped in to quench our thirst and have a mid afternoon snack before going to dinner downtown thanks to our server michelle who was prompt and attentive while serving the guys their mexi lager choices a cilantro margarita for myself and a grilled sausage board the board provided just the right amount of snacks to tide us over always an enjoyable spot to spend some down time
reviewTitle: An Absolute Go To for Any Hour Beer and Appetizer Plate

reviewText: visited her 3 out of 4 nights during a recent trip we were attracted by the range of beers but were so impressed with the service and food too particularly enjoyed the british style cask conditioned ale that was on tap
reviewTitle: Magnificent choice of beer; great food

reviewText: western wild turnofthelast century bar with games sports tv screens what go see red poppers are great cole slaw better than curly fries spare ribs are good late lunch not crowded at all mad atmosphere hasnt changed since 1975 great beer lineup

hadnt been in the dark horse since the 70s but amazingly enough not much has changed dont remember the burgers being as good and this time there were lots of families with kids running around glad we chose the dark horse for dinner
reviewTitle: Can't believe this place is still going... strong!!

reviewText: granddaughter is a freshman and she chose this place for dinner glad she did glad non of the stuff over my head fell down very good burgers good beer and she had a coke interesting approach to service go to the window order and pay and they will shout your name prices are good and the burger with great cole slaw was generous size better than ferg burger in queenstown nz
reviewTitle: Great evening with people on their way to the game

reviewText: we stopped in as we had good memories of the dark horse in the70s and 80s yes a couple of lifetimes ago the burgers were decent but overallthe money that they saved by making it totally selfservice should have been repurposed to the cleaning crew

this bar is an iconic fixture in the republic of boulder students locals have been going here for decades it is typical bar fare which is actually pretty good lots of beer choices other adult beverages games galore a fun place to meet old friends new fine wine not so much but thats not why you go here be part of history visit

not a lot of places endure like this one has the burgers are very good prices are more than fair and its a fun place to go for happy hour be sure and walk around upstairs and check out all the crazy humorous kitsch hanging from walls and ceilings
reviewTitle: Iconic Boulder Bar & Burgers - Been coming since 1989

reviewText: we had some time to kill before flying home from denver so we made our way through boulder and found this place in accident im so glad we did this place may have the coolest decor of any place that ive ever been to assuming youre into it the staff were cool because we had a lot of questions lol the wings were great and the pulled pork sandwich with fries was all good as well you have to walk around and take it all in im so glad places like this still exist

as loud crazy just short of overthetop places go this is a good one prices seemed right they were calling our food orders pretty quickly and everything was tasty everyone in our group proclaimed it had been a great choice for us decent sized portions lots of beer selections and a house red that was cheap and drinkable as places like this go this was a very enjoyable one
reviewTitle: Excellent for the kind of place it is

reviewText: such a cool historic bar in the middle of boulder the atmosphere is casualfun they have a huge collection of random objects stuffed everywhere walls celings etc every room is fun to check out everything and there are lots of rooms the smell is wonderfulold wood and leather the food is great very affordable and quick service they have added an outdoor patio area which is another great space for entertaining i have been going there for 30 years on every trip to boulderand it is always a great time
great food great atmosphere in a college town personable staff prices were awesome when compared to other places in town

stopped here for burgers under 21 have to be out by 945 order food and pick it up yourself from kitchen window have to go to bar separately for drinks very crowded but worth it for great burgers at average price for boulder area we had asian wings bit oversauced rocky mountain oysters burgers were very very good we each got a different type and we were all thrilled with them would recommend and go back because of the burgers
reviewTitle: Inconvenient for families but worth it great burgers

reviewText: love the atmosphere the food and the people we visit everytime were in town from texas come hungry because you do not want to miss out on their burgers
we stopped in for some burgers they were tastey interesting building with a neat interior id go back again next time in town
we have visited the dark horse several times and like the laid back feel the food is great always the blues burger and hot wings

dark horse bar is a great place serving up great for and libations this a classic landmark bar in boulder place looks like it was built in the 1800s but is actually built in the mid 1900s great service and good food cool unique atmosphere
delicious and reasonably priced food staff was friendly and helpful lots to choose from and a nice place to meet up with friends it does get busy but plenty of room to sit

staying overnight in boulder and dark horse recommended by hotel glad we went wasnt crowded on thursday night but big place and layout has multiple themes love the old bar and pub region didnt even know they had karaoke until walking around after finished meal no table service but the orderpick up system works and food ready fast take time to walk around so many uniqueantiquehistoric things to see
there for a wedding fun surroundings food excellent waite staff did a fabulous job with well over 120 people would be fun to go back and have a chance to sample the beers
reviewTitle: Great venue for a wedding or any large gathering.

reviewText: nice place food was delicious service a little slow good variety of wine atmosphere was nice decent price for what they offered

i did the classic flight tasting which included 5 pours and a 6th gratis to compare the rosés and a charcuterie board both the wines and cheeses were delightful and savannah was a great guide lovely atmosphere even on a slower evening and worth a visit if youre even a casual wine drinker
reviewTitle: Private tasting is worth the spend

reviewText: cassie sullivan director of sales and events at bigsbys folly was outstanding i was very apprehensive about planning a baby shower from out of town cassies assistance in planning set up day the of event and help with rental pick up issue was amazing everyone who attended the shower loved the venue the production room was perfect and the food was fabulous i would highly recommend bigsbys folly

we had a group of 6 nice table friendly server they didnt have a wine two of us wanted to try in our flight and they replaced it with a bad one but upon request to swap out immediately did so cheese board very good sparkling wines very nice

wine has been good and we have done the blending party which is fun i writing this because lately the food has gotten worse and the service has been horrible we have started skipping the dinning room all together and just doing to go wine
what a fun place for our group of ladies to meet we had wine and brunch the staff was very attentive the bloody marys were very good

attended a private event at this barbistro really good food and nice presentation patio in back was a nice respite from inside crowded not stuffy away from our event nice place mostly 2030 year old crowd
highly recommend checking this place out we really enjoyed the flight of reserve red wines very cool decor and great music
reviewTitle: Loved our visit and the wines

reviewText: this is a great spot to hang out and enjoy the neighborhood and some great wine the cheese plate is a must with the variety of flights will i go back yes wine club is good too and offer some good deals and events

what a fun restaurantwinery to visit great ambiance and atmosphere in this restaurant in the warehouse district in denver staff was super accommodating outside seating in the front and back of the restaurant and you are allowed to bring your dogs to while seated outdoors highly recommend and worth a visit
this is a way fun place for wine tasting and food the charcuterie board was awesome there is great seating inside and a beautiful patio the staff was friendly the ambiance was exceptional

we met a friend for drinks before dinner at another restaurant i had a single glass and my companions each had flights of the house recommended wines we liked the space and the staff but the wine isnot good sour tart and harsh were the terms that came to mind for each of us we would return for cocktails and to try the food but cannot recommend the wines at all

what an awesome place intimacy created in a large space beautifully appointedloved the crystal chandeliers attached to rustic wood beams great wine and appetizer selections up and coming neighborhood highly recommend
we did a wine tasting with a cheese board the wines were excellent and the service was suburb the place itself is very cozy
we met another couple for drinks and appetizers great wine selection great food staff was friendly up and coming trendy neighbourhood
reviewTitle: Great place to spend an evening!

reviewText: we had drinks and appetizers outside on the patioall was great good service and food really neat up and coming neighbourhood
excellent food and wonderful service one great salad bar food made fresh to order prices are great
great atmosphere and great people go here all the time with family and for meetings good food and good prices
bland iqf unconcerned staff wanting a hamburger you know ground beef patty on a couple of pieces of bread mcdonalds is cheaper and better

stopped for lunch passing through guymon ok they make homemade potato chips and they are the best the green chili cheese burger was very tasty its a popular spot with the locals and leos also a full service bar along with the restaurant fifth street amd main

traveled through guymon and ate at this pub the pub was downtown and split between a dining room and a nice bar areawe had the fried picklesgreat i had a ruben and wife had a pulled pork sandwich and both were very good the wait staff was very friendly and attentive
great place awesome music love the atmosphere and the staff fajitas are always great jesse is a great bartender my 2 year old loves watching the activity

the food is fantastic the ambiance is great the 5 lunch special cant be beat it is centrally located to my job so i walk there several times a week the staff is outstanding the owners are hard working and are almost always there working love the menu this place is overall the best place to eat in guymon
on a road trip recently we stayed in guymon both coming and going we ate there both times food was served hot and fast the servers were both personable and very good

i enjoy the pub when i want a pub experience the menu is good and the food is very consistent and good service is excellent and there is comfortable room were not all squashed together it is a pub so there are tvs and music and its a little loud as you would expect a pub to be the restaurant up front is much more quiet

was traveling solo through guymon and wanted some dinner was surprised how big the place is seemingly bigger on the inside tardislike ordered the catfish which came with a trip to the small but nicely stocked salad bar and two additional sides food was better than average bar food prices were more than reasonable for the portion size and staff was friendly if a little rushed since it was march madness and wing night so there was a large crowd where i was in the pub
reviewTitle: Look for the sign that says ALLEN'S

reviewText: my husband and i enjoyed a wonderful meal ina great atmosphere we sat on the pub side and had porkchops and a ruben sandwich it was good and lots of it love homemade chips

went to this little restaurant three times during the easter break while visiting this town service was excellent the salad bar was refreshingly fresh and looked so healthy the entrees were all so delicious and served in a pleasing manner

we eat lunch at the bricks a few times a month and i have to say we really enjoy the food servers and the atmosphere my favorite dish is the chicken fajitas with beans and rice and i love the rice we appreciate michael krystal and all the staff for their hard work and good food

we had a long day starting in holbrook and losing teo hours to day light savings time searching for a place tobeat in guymon was frustrating very few recent reviews and even fewer good reviews we settled on the bricks and we very pleasently rewarded we were kind of reluctant to hit a pub but the food was really quite good and the service was quietly efficient go there you will be glad you did

great general menu fabulous 5 lunch specials fast service from friendly servers love the ambiance in the pub portion there is a pub area and a general dining area so you chose where you would like to eat there is also a meeting room

3 things that matter were present cleanliness great service and awesome food additional plus was you could tell food was from scratch having moved to this area from ky i have had difficulty with that no more i will be a regular

authorName: The Places Where We Go Podcast
reviewText: stopped here for beers and dinner prior to a hockey game at pepsi center decent beer selection our table going for esb an ommegang belgian and a saison these were paired with their fish and chips fish was a bit on the crunchier well browned side i probably prefer my fish in this style somewhat more lightly golden fried service was extremely attentive and friendly enjoyable
this old 2 story building has lots of great beer as well as lots of character the upstairs has several pool tables a nice causal place

here for another private party with about 400 people or so we had one of the upstairs rooms this place is huge food was just so so drinks and service excellent i would not be seaking out this place but it was good for a party this size
stopped by after walking the downtown area with family we pulled up seats outside for great views people and the beautiful weather everyone was happy about their choice

my wife and i were out clubbing and decided to stop by for appetizer and a drink we were very happy with the service we received as well as the food and drink we hope to come back soon for a full meal however my bathroom experience was interesting after being tapped on the shoulder by one of the ghostly residentsgreat time great stories
we were attended to very well and seated quickly very attentive waitress very happy with the food would love to go back
we stopped by for lunch and a few drinks my son got a few local brews and i had wine we got a plate of nachos to share and they were some of the best ive ever had
four of us had the sampler which was outstanding great selection of beer and the staff was very helpful explaining all the options had the rocky mt oyster beer which was unusual but tasty
reviewTitle: Great beer, outstanding service and good food

reviewText: this renovated old denver building has become a trendy place to meet friends and have snacks it was a fun atmosphere

stopped for a quick small bite on our way to the game had the pretzels and beer cheese delicious hubby enjoyed his beer and i enjoyed my tequila mojito enjoyable start to a fun evening would recommend

was touring breweries and came here for good food and beer thought the outdoor seating overlooking union station was lovely the beer was average and the food was decent but overpriced i enjoyed the bbq chicken salad but not for 14 friendly wait staff but this was nothing special for out of towners

we came in just to try the beer and were lucky enough to have big mike as a server friendly helpful and very knowledgeable loved the beer we tried and they have a huge variety to pick from sitting outside was lovely
we had hot wings and short rib grill cheese was really good ample portions and priced reasonably my husband got the beer sampler and was a very happy man

we landed on thursday and werent sure where to go for my birthday dinner 4 of us tried wyncoop and i will say i was a little skeptical at first david was our server and i will say he completely changed the experience for the better the food was excellent but the service and the historical stories about the wyncoop were awesome thanks again david

we went here at the end of our vacation we tried two different beers and had a beef and bison burgers the service was very nice and good advice about the beers given the burgers were great however we did not taste any difference between the beef or bison we suggest to take the beef and save 4 usd the beers were very nice and if we return to denver we for sure will go back
had the salmon sandwich yesterday and it was perfectly cooked i like the accompanying ingredients and the focaccia bread

nice relaxed place with home brewed beer make sure you go down to the basement and look at the beer tanks we had a couple of pints chicken wings and a pulled pork sandwich very down to earth but serious about their beer
it was very good my husband had the pork chops he said they were very tender good flavor i had the sirloin it had good flavor but could have been a little more tender good service
i had trouble finding a good place to eat in guymon but this was a pleasant surprise great food and service

my husband and i stopped here for lunch on sunday afternoon we ordered sandwiches off the menu i had a hamburger and my husband had the ruben both were very good as were the sides homemade potato chips and sweet potato fries we would definitely stop again the building itself is impressive apparently built for an implement dealer years ago so it has an open span design

after a long morning of driving across western kansas one of the loneliest drives to be had anywhere guymon looked and felt like a big city it was lunchtime and i pulled in here and had a good experience the bricks looks and feels like a collegetown or even big city spot and i bet its pretty popular after dark i certainly wasnt expecting this in guymon the service was good my burger came out promptly and it was good fortified i felt ready to drive several more hours through some pretty lonely country
reviewTitle: Great oasis on a long drive across the plains.

reviewText: we have eaten here many times and have always been good food no matter what you order service some times can be a little slow

given the limited choices available on a sunday evening we went here sat in the bar area as the main dining room was closing salad bar was awesomehavent seen one that good in quite some time had a blue moon on tap and fried catfish the food was good portions were huge service was decent and prices are cheaper than what i expected great stop
reviewTitle: Where to Go on a Sunday Night?

reviewText: for lunch we decided to try this place as it was close to the meeting location the building is a repurposed oil well motor building with high ceilings it has a great feel to it the food was excellent as was the service there are multiple televisions broadcasting sports plus pool tables
there was no id problem wasnt even asked for one was just told that we could not be served obviously we would have been fine with showing our valid united states issued ids

the fact that my wife made a bad review got us on the no service list this restaurant is a joke the no service list might sound bad but once youve seen the service its basically the same thing reviews should make you want to improve but they just hide them and bar people that wrote them there are very good waitresses but they are over shadowed by the incompetent ones
food was excellent and reasonably priced the service was a bit slow but we were in no hurry seems like a place the locals frequent a lot we will go there again when in guymon
this is the best place to eat the service is great the food is great and you always get plenty to eat best wings in town

service here is great food is excellent but the pub distinction is questionable to me a pub is a place with great beers on tap bricks has a few 32 domestics and that is about it bottle selection is also slim overall though if you are not a beer snob like myself and can do 32 bubmillercoors light it is likely ok

my husband and i stopped at the pub on the bricks while on a road trip we were pleasantly surprised with the atmosphere and the quality of the food we had a sweet bartender that chatted with us the grilled catfish was delightful great prices the free salad bar is a definite plus although we dont usually eat that much food come hungry and dont be afraid to sit at the bar for dinner
reviewTitle: Good food, good service, good prices

reviewText: we saw the pub on the bricks in the oklahoma magazine and heading west to new mexico we made this our dinner stop great food large menu and the prices were very reasonable if ever back in the panhandle of ok this would by a stop once again
a great casual spot in downtown guymon i enjoyed lunch and look forward to going back for dinner or nighttime fun

i had planned to eat here when i was in guymon because of the good reviews however i couldnt find the place even with gps it said i was there but i didnt see any signs to indicate where it was and didnt see enough cars around to give me a clue sorry i missed the opportunity to try your food

we ate in the front part of the restaurant which is more family friendly but we wished we would have gone to the bar area its large with plenty of tvs pool tables etc and the atmosphere seemed more like something we would have enjoyed but the front part was fine the food was good bar food actually we felt it was a little above average for a barlike atmosphere it was clean and the waitstaff took care of our needs
i have been in guymon many times and i most often choose the bricks as my eating place they know how to treat and serve you right at the bricks
if youre in guymon and want a place to relax or watch the game this is a really nice place i love the ceilings the service is quick and friendly
reviewTitle: Really nice place for a small town.

reviewText: an employee of the hotel we were staying at recommended this as a lunch restaurant the food was great please be aware that this is a bar that happens to serve food and not a restaurant that happens to have a bar seat yourself find the kitchen and order and then head to bat for drinks you have to listen for your name over blurry speaker to get your food and the traffic can be busy inside the food is worth it though
awesome atmosphere cool looking bar good burger looks like it would be a fun place for drinks in the evening

unique decor with tasty food lots to look at while enjoying your food and beverages dont know if it was just the day of the week but no waitresses or waiters sign on table let you know had to order food at a window then order drinks at the bar not a problem though just added to the atmosphere they called out your name when your food was ready fun and unforgettable experience
lindo bar con decoracion tipica de bares universitarios buenos platos de comida rapida bien ambientado terraza para fumadores

i liked the side salad the dressing and the fixings on the burger im no fond of highfat burgers and refined white bread so i guess i wont be back anytime soon the beers were great and the atmosphere is fun
we stopped here on a monday afternoon the place is huge we were seated on the far side by the pool tables the service was excellent they had quite a few local beers on tap and the burgers were great

great place with cool atmosphere good service and good food last time i was here was 20 years ago and frankly do not think it has changed a bit still have steel tip dart boards which is a rarity these days took my boys here and told them it will probably be just the same in 10 years
the food was excellent here but make sure you take a look around the building so many cool and unique decorations definitely worth the stop
perfect place to visit for lunch super friendly bartenders and excellent burgers also tried the fish and chips local beers on tap highly recommend

just stopped in to watch some nfl football had aome beers and appetizers if applebys hired a drunk biker gang to decorate this would be the result and i mean that as a high compliment fun crowd decent food and drink totally worth a visit

dark closed in venue that smells badly of moldy hvac beer breath and bodies burger was small and raw fries were greasy some tables waited 45 minutes for food found cigarette butts in the outdoor table cracks

i stayed in boulder 3 days being alone the night before flight back home i checked dark horse bar to enjoy some company and it worked the bartenders were sociable and fun guys i ordered a burger from kitchen and had it at the bar with a couple of local beers the burger was delicious

a perfect complement to the white widow we had in the parking lot this afternoon at 420 or your drinks at the bar put them on the first table you find walk over to the kitchen window order some killer food go back to your table they will shout your name in a very strange way

this is a one of a kind restaurant and bar that is worth checking out the food is good barfood at a reasonable price this is self service so pick a table then order your food at the kitchen window beer at the bar they will call your name when your food is ready the decor is hard to describe it is like an antique store exploded inside leading to a fun and interesting visit if you like a unique college atmosphere this is worth checking out
reviewTitle: A good classic college town hole in the wall bar

reviewText: dark horse has a great atmosphere total college town hangout food is pretty good good burgers lots of seating area families are welcome before 9pm afterwards its 21 and over
reviewTitle: Great College Tavern Food and Bar

reviewText: maten var riktigt god och utbudet av öl var väldigt bra många lokala öler och öler som de brygger själva enkelt att boka bord online väldigt trevlig personal
i tried the flatiron steak and they made it perfectly to my liking the potatoes tasted amazing and the asparagus was perfect great business meal
nice and huge sportsbar in lodo beers brewed on site and really goodlarge choice good food too

we stopped by after walking around the neighborhood we were disappointed that pattys chili beer was sold out so we tried the pale ale mile high not disappointed hoppy malty well balanced our other family members got a margarita and a lemonade vodka sat outside under the cover as it had started to rain

we visited the wynoop brewing company on our first visit to denver we stumpled upon the place looking for somewhere to eat and drink after a long flight from london and was not dissapointed friendly staff greated us and took care of us into the evening recommending beers and serving us great food i would definetley return and that we did on our next trip to denver great location too in the centre of denver near the station

recommended by touring guide who said wynkoop had a great beer selection she was right and the food was tasty we went on a tuesday night at 630 pm with 14 adults and 4 kids and the place was busy waitress did a pretty good job handling multiple tables and our large group they have a kids menu so its family oriented everyone seemed to have a good time and were happy with their meal its loud when the restaurant is full so if you want to have a conversation it may be difficult
reviewTitle: Good Place for Pub Food and Beer

reviewText: its a brewery so gluten free options arent plentiful food was good too loved the bacon wrapped shrimp

you will totally love this place i was the only nondrinker in my party of 38 so i personally did not enjoy the evening however that does not take away from the appeal of the pool hall saloonatmosphere that was well done the food was very good and the 30 minute beer brewing tour was interesting
reviewTitle: If you are a beer drinker...

reviewText: we had an awesome time having dinner here great beers and wonderful food including many vegetarian and vegan options service was friendly and helpful great time

stopped by for a beer and stayed for three great atmosphere and quiet enough to actually carry on a conversation building is said to be haunted but did experience the young girl or cat during our stay history of the building is interesting with some articles in the lower level a must stop in denver

stopped by here to try the beers and just relax while in the area i tried the cowtown milk stout which was delicious loved the fact that they had quite a few choices and werent too heavy on the ipas sat on the patio and people watched while enjoying our beers very knowledgeable and friendly wait staff
this place is crazy busy on game days great beer great food but be prepared to wait when its overrun with rockies fans

we had a very enjoyable lunch here sampling a few of the wynkoop beers we also had the brewhouse sampler to eat which was plentiful and tasty with good variety it was nice to sit outside in the sunshine on the terrace which was a prime spot for people watching service was friendly and prices were very reasonable

we stopped for a few beers and a snack a decent choice my sour beet juice beer was unique i couldnt drink it very fast but it was good i snacked on queso and chips they were good pretty spicy my husbands first beer was to sour for him but really enjoyed the second lager style a pretty popular place with not many seats remaining at the bar on an early saturday afternoon
had a drink here and did not know which beer to start with great choice and taste ended up eating here as well if you want burgers etc then this is the place to go
the bar was very busy and quite noisy but they found us a table at the back good menu of normal pub food with decent portions

while doing the brewery tour this place was our last stop so we decided have lunch there hamburgers were tasty i loved the sweet potato fries friendly staff good service great atmosphere reasonable prices

came here with my mom and uncle for a brewery tour we werent expecting much but had a really great time our tourguide brought us some beers to taste while explaining a lot about the process of brewing but also the history of wynkoop and downtown denver then we got a tour it is not a big brewery but very interesting and they have some interesting things to see our tourguide was great and we had lots of fun would definitely come here if you are thinking about doing a brewery tour in denver
excellent burger and tasty beers a short distance from coors field plenty of food for the money and good atmosphere will definitely go back
reviewTitle: Stop here on your way to the game!

reviewText: this is by far one of the most interesting and entertaining places i have seen in colorado or pretty much anywhere else for that matter the food is very good and fairly priced and the selfservice vibe is perfect the drinks are similarly priced fairly and the bartenders are attentive and polite you will love the decor and there will be something new to look at every time you visit i was there for two nights on this past visit and ate there both nights
this is a good college town dive lots of beer options the food was actually quite good the noise level was high great patio in back

we were a little surprised by the level of scrutiny of our identification at the entrance note for overseas visitors passports are the preferred id as a group of senior middle aged folk from the uk we havent had that challenge since we were 18 or 16 we loved the tasty mexican beanie burgers and curly fries the local microbrewery beer was excellent the staff were very friendly and that atmosphere was excellent with live music saturday night and lots of curious pub knickknacks adorning the walls ceilings and just about everywhere a very enjoyable experience
reviewTitle: Eclectic pub with decent vegetarian food

reviewText: good food unique style especially when ordering food with quality beers not necessarily found everywhere fun spot for a bike stop motored or not
地元の人が良く訪れるお店でしたハンバーガーはとても美味しかったです旅の思い出にお訪れてみてください
reviewTitle: アメリカンな庶民派レストラン

reviewText: attending graduation my son took us here for lunch great hole in the wall food is very simplebasic bar food with burgerssandwiches a fun place to take in the college atmosphere
reviewTitle: Hole in the wall college hang out

reviewText: im really giving it 35 stars the atmosphere is a lot fun with all sorts of things hanging from the ceiling in an almost carnival fun house type of setting the food is darn good for tavern food and theres a great beer selection as in most good places these days screens everywhere for sports and make sure you choose the right door when using the rest rooms

within walking distance to our hotel what a cool typical college spot great decora mix of everything on the walls and ceiling the burgers were really goodmade better by the fun atmosphere totally makes me wish that i had a place like that where i went to college
this place is the real deal nestalgia fun and a gear place to hang lots of room and rooms to hang out its the wild west all over again
awsome place great atmosphere family friendly video games for the kids happy hour 4 to 6 good beer selection
great bar with typical bar food prices are reasonable and atmosphere is relaxed great place to unwind with some good food and drink
reviewTitle: Great Place for a Bite and a Drink

reviewText: we bring the kids here when out of town guests are around on a weekend afternoon burgers and fries are great kids love the games we love the beer and atmosphere in our experience adults here dont really mess with kids at all in case youre reluctant to bring your kids into what is essentially a drinking establishment though i would not bring kids on a weekend evening
reviewTitle: A Boulder institution, great for out-of-town visitors

reviewText: great place to have a low key grilled no frills burger and beer ordering is done at the bar and kitchen but dont forget to listen for your name when your order is up nice low lighting quite sports tv and my fav air hockey
great specials good bar food fun games super great place to watch sports too would totally give them 5 stars if their pool tablesdart boards were replacedjanky but still fun
great local bar and walking distance to the hotel sports bar with great hamburger which is what the front desk told me quirky but with lots of televisions to watch sports on
