we really enjoyed the burgers here but the one disappointment is that they have no gluten free buns in todays day and age in a town like boulder there is really no excuse for this they are now cheap to keep on hand with freezing not even being required by many of the vendors and the air packed last weeks i think they need to get with the times and get them in stock to make everyone in the party have good choices and enjoy their wonderful burgers
reviewTitle: Great quality burgers and fries, not great for gluten free

reviewText: great food but a confusing and chaotic chore to get it no table service you must go to the order pick up window located in a crowded hallway the food was quite good and very reasonable priced but almost not worth the effort adult beverages are available from two separate bars but not at the food window quite noisy as its a popular destination for the college crowd lots of interesting stuff to look at throughout much like the old minder binders in tempe az not recommended for young ones though they are allowed in the dining area
reviewTitle: Interesting place to spend an adult evening.

reviewText: wings were changed to much larger cheaper chicken wings boulder born and raise blocks from heregrew up in this place its sad to see this

i stopped in on a saturday both the bar and food were selfserve you have to place your order no wait staff the burger took a long time to come out i ordered a well done and this was just raw no excuse for that the kitchen was not that busy the whole restaurant is a historical site with many contractions on the walls and celling i have been there a few times and have always enjoyed it but this time was just a little below average
reviewTitle: Used to be a good place

reviewText: we just happened upon this restaurant in our recent travel we had a great burger there however pay great attention if you have to make a stop in the restrooms it can be tricky as i learned when coming out of the stall and there was a gentleman leaving from washing his hands i questioned myself on being in the right place was a nice place and great food

love this place cant even begin to cover all the strange things on the wall a rube goldburg machine behind the bar follow the story written on the walls food is decent happy hour goes until 8 during the week careful when you use the restroom art on the wall runs from old carnival pieces wagons and porn from the 70s
reviewTitle: Unique dive bar with great food

reviewText: really liked the atmosphere and the burger was very good as well id recommend this to anyone in the area

we stayed in boulder for couple of days and got the place recommended by some locals its the place to get peanut butter burger with bacon well its a bombn of fat and flavour with fries as a side you can t bearly move afterwards

this place seems like more of a place to go drinking or for a one time visit to check out the kitschy decor the food wasnt bad but rather average one of these places where you go retrieve your own food probably a fun place to go for drinks but my guess is there are better places if youre just looking for some good food
been here a couple of times staff is friendly and prices are reasonable travel to boulder on business every once in a while always stop by
reviewTitle: Fun place to chill by yourself

reviewText: not bad atmosphere great burgers are burgers good portions and good music service was friendly would recommend seems like they have activities at night but lunch was fine

the food was awesome and the drinks were great great old movie and country bar and grill theme pool tables and darts also live band we bought a shirt and sweat shirt to have cool memories of this place we will be back
stopped for lunch while dropping our son of at school the burgers are great everyone enjoyed theirs atmosphere is a bar server was good
you have to go to understand what a great environment and visual collection is here and the quesidias are good too they have a student menu and offerings beyond burgers and fries
welcoming staff good burgers and great atmosphere day and nightamazing collection of film memrobelia
i like their burgers on burger madness a beer and a burger that are decent is awesome in my book so i cant complain

nine of us showed up starving and ready for lunch after spending a few hours in boulder canyon we settled in and started checking out the menu and ordered drinks ranging from beers to margaritas to water and iced teawe ordered burgers wings and fried cod and everyone liked their food i stuck with a basic cheeseburger with fries and it was perfectly cooked and delicious i drank a couple of cold coors to celebrate my first visit to this pub since 1979 it doesnt appear to have changed much and is holding up extremely well
nice little place to hang out with your best friends or family burgers made to your satisfaction with great selections if your going to boulder you have to eat at the dark horse
very tasty beer and delicious burgers extremely friendly staff and fast service went there both nights we stayed in nearby rodeway inn
awesome alive bar amazing eclectic decor is a must see great friendly and helpful staff and really good pub food well worth visiting if youre in the area

ive never been to a bar like this before tons of character and the bartenders were probably the nicestbest ive had in years and years no smug hipsters at all and right next to our motel definitely hang there again
bistro vendome offers a delicious meal friendly and attentive staff and inventive cocktails the souffle which happens to be glutenfree was amazing
reviewTitle: Great meal at a fair price

reviewText: i was disappointed in the food at this restaurant and felt that it expensive for what we got my husband and i had the salad de chicory and that was very good but my husband and our friend got grilled hangar steak which they both said was very tough i got pan seared scallops and they were good but they were small and there were only three of them the service was very good and manager did give a us a discount because of the steak

what a lovely spot to have a meal so much better than their downtown location full of light and great acoustics hard to fine now a days the eggs in purgatory were spicy and perfectly done but too much grilled bread as a side the steak tartar was an hit with potato chips best omelets in town the only down was we forgot to order the bacon crispy the sangria was really really delicious if anyone that reads this review has the recipe for it i would love to have it
we are a family with children and this was a very good experience for all of us we had everything from french fries to roasted scallops and pork grille

excellent service great atmosphere fantastic food i had been there before this experience was is good or better than my first experience to us ordered the scallops which were wonderful appetizers were delightful third guest in our party ordered steak au povre which was also outstanding highly recommend for anyone visiting denver
this brunch was wonderful one of our guests had many dietary restrictions and the restaurant was very accommodating staff was very welcoming and friendly i highly recommend

great brunch we were on the patio server courtney was amazing a real pro omelette was perfect pain et beurre and tomato bisque were delicious and my wife loved her crepe us citron the ladoucette pouillyfume complimented perfect love the new location the restaurant is beautiful cant wait to come back

we ate at this restaurant when it was located downtown it used to be very good pasta tagliatelle was cold very salty and the pasta way undercooked the rabbit was cold and not very tasty the service was very good

this restaurant has moved to park hill from larimer square 2267 kearney st denver co 80207 my wife and i had brunch here yesterday and we both loved it fabulous food and coffee were going back for dinner soon
reviewTitle: Great French food in a cute corner of Park Hill

reviewText: love the new location of this iconic restaurant beautiful space and the food is better than ever had the french onion soup steak tartare and sweetbreads all were awesome excellent wines had the ott provence rose that was suggested by my server beautiful and a great pairing with the sweetbreads service was great excellent experience
reviewTitle: New location is better than ever

reviewText: we never had dinner here because we were not aware of the new location when we called we thought they were still located on larimer wish they had said something when i made a reservation over the phone they need to communicate better

awesome spot to get food after a long ride the brisket sandwich was the best brisket i have ever had in colorado our friends had the burgers and they said they were good as well we will definitely be back

ate here three times during our stay in pitkin the burgers and chicken sandwiches were both excellent enough fries for at least 2 or 3 people love eating outside under the cover large tables to accomidate families
worth the stop came here on my way north like the open atmosphere and the service was exceptional
on our recent trip to taylor park we ate here on 2 occasions we both had the burgers very good and large the first trip and brisket sandwich the second trip both very good fries are soso

stopped at this place while riding motorcycles through the mountain passes and trails with a couple of friends you order from a food trailer and then eat at picnic table under a semi enclosed canopy attached to the food trailer simple food like burgers and pulled pork sandwiches fries etc everything is made to order and reasonably priced
great food when coming off a day or morning of atv riding we love the silver plume and will be back again and again
reviewTitle: Best Burgers come from the Mountains!

reviewText: then try a burger or a hotdog here at the silver plume grillmaybe its just me but i think they taste even better because of this sweet mountain air
great hot dogs burgers and smiles with your service a must stop when atving in the rockies prices good and service top drawer

this is a great pit stop for your day in pitkin the burger was fantastic and the general store had most of the basics and then some the covered outdoor dining area is just the ticket for a surprise down pour or relief from shade highly recommended
food is good and the service is great nice open air place to eat and relax i had a great time there while we stayed in pitkin
covered pavilion is nice with picnic tables had blt bacon was abundant well cooked people are friendly knowledgeable about area lots to see nearby check out general store chairs on porch
reviewTitle: Dining in Pitkin, slow down, enjoy

reviewText: the brisket sandwich was really good and we know brisket the service was great a perfect lunch stop if youre in pitkin
good food and fun for my daughter with board games at each table the service was very friendly and respectful

the grill is next door to the siver plume the people make this stop in pitkin great the grill you can pick up a meal and visit with other outdoor folks while waiting the plume trading post offers a number of things including gasoline ice cream information collectibles clothing etc
we were hungry after a day out on the rzrs and the burgers and fries were great we had great service too and my kids enjoyed playing checkers too thank you

this grill is like its adjacent general storehigh quality in every way the burgers were fresh the accompanying fries were homestyle very tasty yes one might consider the fare a bit pricey but it avoids a trip to gunnison not exactly uptheroad and one pays for convenience love the adjacent eating area with fresh plants on the tables cheerful atmosphere staff in the grill kitchen friendly and hospitable they want the best for the area and do anything they can for the guest just love everything about the silver plume

its a beautiful ride along quartz creek and when the pavement stops youve reached the silver plume grill it was loaded with dirt bikers and offroaders when i arrived but the grill handled the rush well and everyone under the tent seemed very happy with their lunches good burger friendly people
great burgers and frys friendly staffalways accommodating the store is also great and its nice to find gas for our atvs and utv
the fries were yummy during our stay in pitkin we enjoyed the hot dog and burgers nice stop before or after hitting the trail

such a fun little place the burgers are wonderful but this was the first time to have the brisket wow very tinder and tasty like melt in your mouth tinder also had an order of fries they were also freshly cooked the service was also very friendly will definitely stop in for a bite any time we are in the area also be sure to check out all the fun stuff they have in the little general store

we enjoyed an impromptu dinner here on a friday night the place was fully booked but the host managed 2 seats for us at the bar we enjoyed delicious moules frites a favorite of ours in france accompanied by tasty appetizers and a good bordeaux we enjoyed ourselves so much we returned for brunch on sunday fun atmosphere pleasant staff lots of charm

hot stuffy air slow waiter very average overpriced food trying very hard to be french but not even closeonly plus is the the charming facility itself and location in larimer square if you have been to france and liked it theredo not go to this restaurant like many restaurants it is faux french

starts with a great happy hour menu 46 mth bargains on drinks and apps courtyard in summet inside in winter either way the atmosphere is tops knowledgeable waiters who know their menu well the moules are excellent as is the country pate you could easily make a meal just off the happy hr menu for the mains trout roasted chicken duck confit or steak and frites are all on point cheeses and dessert also do not disappoint always a pleasant place to spend the evening

nice little bistro with simple menu done well inside and outside dining in an arcade off larimer offers a range of slightly different choices we didnt have starters but would have had the steak tartare or the pate or the yellow fin tuna if we hadnt shared a seasoned dressed green salad we enjoyed steak frites duck confit with peaches leeks and mushrooms and boudin sausage with pear and cabbage we had brussel sprouts with almonds as a side we enjoyed excellent cheese a ginger and lychee dessert and a glass of good chilled sauternes very nice and recommended
this is such a charming location sit outdoors i uncharacteristic ordered the flank steak i hardly ever eat beef it was wonderful our server was informative and personable perfect evening

came in unexpectedly for a late afternoon drink when we saw the inviting courtyard from the street and we were so happy we did well prepared drinks excellent appetizers and genuinely friendly and attentive service hidden away inside the courtyard its got a real european feel not traveling to france much these days so this place is the next best thing
very cute bistro had the onion soup steak tartar salad mussels duck and steak frites all were very good some dinner plates came with apps so that was annoying but otherwise no companys

off the beaten path one might miss this gem lovely ambiance wonderful cuisine excellent staff solicitous helpful their recommendations were outstanding the perfect pairings of dishes with wine i cant wait until my next visit to denver so i can enjoy the food and service of this fine establishment

what a french gem tucked away on larimer st greeted and served by the most friendliest and attentive waiter matt french onion soup and steak frites were excellent get the champagne gastric seasoned frites compliments to the pastry chef the chocolate soufflé was one of the best weve had not a surprise that this bistro has been around for 20 years already cant wait to get back to denver to dine here again

bonne restaurant quaint spot off larimer with friendly staff and excellent food enjoyed brunch offerings of crepes drinks and duck confit the cheese options are unique as was the fig spread will definitely return

we loved our visit to bistro vendome the food is prepared in a traditional manner with some innovative touches no one in our party of six was disappointed with any of their choices which included items from all of the food groupings on the menu the prices were moderate considering the recent rise in all food pricing the wine list was extensive with many wines also available by the glass service was professional and attentive with the waiter prepared to answer all of our questions about the menu we will return

waitress neglected to tell us about the daily specials drinks took forever steak frites was undercooked pork belly was still cold in the middle waitress never checked in with us to find out how our meals were significant delay in arrival of second glass of wine

nice french bistro vibe and the food was excellent the staff knowledgeable and accommodating we had the special starter for that day and split a dessert my husband had the duck which was suburb and i had the pork belly wed definitely go back

steak frites were served raw when they were ordered medium rare and the bearnaise sauce was hard and cold the duck was good but not great the steak tar tar and the onion soup were excellent the manager made adjustments to discount the check and offered a desert on the house for the problems with the meals
great place to be beautiful seating especially outside food was great staff very nice and accommodating would definitely come back whenever we visit denver

nice tucked away french restaurant off festive larimer st this was our 2nd visit and did not disappoint very good and knowledgeable waitress nice wine selection we started with mussels had pork loin as entrees and very tender and tasty chocolate soufflé is a must to cap it off
enjoyable sunday brunch with delicious food especially enjoyed the bottomless mimosas the outdoor area is lovely
enjoyed a good hot meal after a long day of riding if youre lucky enough to get to these towns definitely plan on eating here

been here in 2014 and 2016 it is a great stop after being on the trail all day the burgers are great bbq brisket and sauce is made there and excellent everything ive had has been excellent ice cream and gas is available at the accompanying silver plume general store stop its worth it
always great food served with a smile the hand made picnic tables are the perfect touch for the mountain setting

if youre traveling through the mountain passes near pitkin or just passing through to gunnison i would highly recommend the silver plume grill the food is amazing and the service is really nice definitely a doover
a little pricey but when you consider the cost to truck everything over 20 miles from the nearest town the massive amount of food per order and the quality of the food 100 worth every penny
great burger pulled pork sandwich and fries the owners are there cooking and visiting with guests the food is delicious and you should stop by and try it out

i stopped at the silver plume grill for a carry out burger so i wouldnt have to cook dinner the burger was huge on a fresh bun and the fixings were delicious what a joy to find an amazing burger in the mountains and the service was quick and very friendly

i ate lunch there the weather was great and i sat in the picnic type area they had setup could see the mountains and tree around talked with some friendly locals and other travelers the grill is close by the room i stayed at i came back this way again during a break in the day cheese burger and fries in the mountains was nice cant wait to bring my family on the next trip

we ate at the grill multiple times during our stay in pitkin the brisket was perfect and the breakfast was quick and delicious a perfect way to start the day the family that runs silver plume is really a nice group of people the kind of people you like to be around thank you silver plume
reviewTitle: Great Great People - Great Great Food

reviewText: best food and service on the mountain i feel like i sample half the menu and everything was like a home cooked meal

this french bistro hit the spot during a record colorado heat wave the adorable courtyard is shaded and cool we had brunch and it was delicious classic beignets with apricots and dream crepes florentine and eggs benedict made for the perfect sunday afternoon mmmmmmm
reviewTitle: Adorable European courtyard in the heart of Denver.

reviewText: this good looking little restaurant is located in a very nice area of larimer street where options are plentiful the food was ok but simply did not meet our expectations service was below the widespread standards of restaurants of this status where you anticipate that at least wine should be served after the first pouring by the waiter and suggest if you want more wine especially when there are four persons at your party

service and food is always excellent this time round celebrating an anniversary staff was very attentive and spoiled us with a free desert to share we let our server know we were attending a show later in the evening they inquired what time we needed to be done and made sure we enjoyed our starter entree desert and coffee without feeling rushed and with time to spare bistro vendome is our go to restaurant when we we are in denver

a denver local highly recommended this charming restaurant in larimer square i loved it bistro vendome is cozy elegant and relaxed the service is superb our server aaron was very attentive and made excellent food and wine recommendations from their wonderful menu the scallops were light and tasty and the pavlova and blueberry tarte were wonderful cant wait to go back

just off larimer square there is nothing nicer than having a sunday evening meal outside the mussels and pomme frites are a great way to end an afternoon of seeing the sights in lodo serive is good but get there early if you want to dine al fresco
i have always liked but never loved french food however this restaurant was amazing the escargot was delicious the serving sizes were perfect and the duck and steak were to die for highly recommend
one of the best hidden jewel in denver top class french cuisine and extensive win list very cozy and excellent service will go back
went there two consecutive nights duck and steak frites both excellent with a small but terrific desert menu all well prepared and reasonably priced well definitely go back next time were in denver

the atmosphere of bistro vendome tucked away in larimer square is perfect for a sunday brunchvery french with scenic gardens and cozy tables but the food is the star here fantastic onion soup so nice that they split one order into 2 cups flavor balanced root vegetable and bacon crepe with herbed hollandaise sauce and superb quiche with veggies and cheese the french press is super flavorful too service is helpful and attentive prices are commensurate with the food quality

went here for our anniversary after seeing the monet exhibit the chicken was the most tender juiciest i ever had and the roquefort steak was incredible the pommes frites had so many layers of flavor my husband had the creme brulee and i had the chocolate souffle delicious after all that plus drinks and coffee it was surprisingly reasonably priced cant wait to try this place again

had brunch here on sunday with long time friends one of whom was in for a visit from new york everything was excellent the food the service the atmosphere made for a truly enjoyable gathering and the courtyard served up the opportunity for some nice postmeal photos

escargot good but seasoned with pernod so a new taste sensation onion soup ok chicken special was delicious potatoes and kale served cold but wait staff delivered new order of hot potatoes and kale no happy hour price on house wine 15 a glass wish waiter suggested a bottle but was delicious

a group of 8 of us had dinner while in town for a conference the staff were very friendly and the food was delicious i had the trout with a cider everyone seemed happy with their food the only down side was they spilt the wine everyone else drank between all of us so i was charged 15 extra but seemed like too much of a hassle to make them correct it
my wife is from germany lived in paris a year so when she says it is the best mussels she has had in the usa that is a compliment brunch so i had omelette croissant which were great
doesnt get any better service and great food exactly what you want other places might give you flashy and good food bistro vendome is classycjjust pprprovides you with
très déçu par ce restaurant francais à denvercuisine bien moyenne peut être nous navons pas réussi ce jour en retenant au vendome mais ce restaurant ne restera pas dans nos mémoires

great weather for outside brunch delightful would recommend salade nicoisemoules and crepes du jour saff said the most popular plate was oeufs benedicte and witnessed several during serving plate presentation looked awesome
a group of 8 and we stopped at this restaurant a good choice overall service was top notch very attentive and friendly food was very tasty and definitely a place to come back to

i had a wonderful dinner at bistro vendome it was a beautiful evening i sat outside on the patio the bartender made me a wonderful cocktaila classic negroni then i had some small plates the beef tartare roasted carrots and a salad all were very good even though i was dining alone the servers treated me with respect and allowed me to dine it was a wonderful meal

very french ambience and beautiful outdoor courtyard seating when the weather permits great location on larimer square very comfortable casually elegant not a wideranging menu but very good food and great service the fries are very decadent
reviewTitle: A corner of Paris in downtown Denver

reviewText: a very sophisticated and friendly restaurant we had a group of 5 who wanted to talk more than eat the wait staff was very patient and accommodating if you want the chicken please know that it takes 30 minutes your colleagues may be eating before you the bread was warm and delicious the meal was beautifully presented we jared desserts which were delightful to behold as they were to consume
this restaurant is tucked away and quiet it is elegant with wonderful menu i so enjoyed the atmosphere and the staff is amazing a great restaurant in a great location try it
reviewTitle: Wonderful French restaurant in the heart of Larimer Square!

reviewText: the patio is beautiful and quiet we ordered small plates and thoroughly enjoyed every one of them the cheeses were interesting and flavorful and the melon salad had such a creative combination of elements it was so much more than i expected the creme brulee was delicious and paired with the fresh french press coffee a fantastic finish to a great experience
reviewTitle: Great for small plates and patio conversation

reviewText: great location you really feel like being in paris had the steak tartare which was very good although i would like a little more intensity kn the flavor creme brulee was great and bug portion excellent service
my husband and i went there for our wedding anniversary the food was fantastic the atmosphere was good and the service is superb i recommend this place
we just stopped in for a glass of wine they have a nice selection of wines by the glass the pinot noir is very good we also had the cheese plate with the wine a great combination

this was one of the best meals ive had in a long time we had duck that melted in your mouth vegetables in an amazing sauce escargot that was perfectly made and creme brulee to top it off all paired with perfect wine choices im getting hungry thinking about it

we were walking past this place during the sidewalk chalk festival and it looked so cute the manager was very friendly and said to get the chicken but it takes 30 minutes and also the chocolate dessert which takes 20 all 4 of us got both of those and really that chicken was fantastic i wish i lived there just so i could go back

such a cozy little place to escape from the hustle and bustle my husband and i both had the steak frites which were prepared to perfection as well as sharing the carrot dish from the appetizers wish we could have stayed for dessert but we had places to go afterwards

we stopped into bistro vendome to see the restaurant when we spoke to the maitre de he had suggested the chicken and chocolate souffle we decided to go and act on his recommendation our party of four all ordered the same thing and all agreed it was one of our top five meals of all time the chicken as absolutely delicious and worth the 25 minute wait for it to be prepared you will not go wrong ordering this
reviewTitle: Best Chicken I Have Ever Had!

reviewText: service was excellent great wine list the food was good but not outstanding best cup of coffee weve had for a long time
reviewTitle: Classic US take on a French bistro

reviewText: the restaurant is pleasant in appearance and very nice in many respects we enjoyed it three and a half stars is about right very good service we had the duck confit salad as an entree and steak frites the salad was nice and the beef was excellent and well cooked a word about the frites french fries in all my years visiting and occasionally living in france i never had frites with sugar or some other weird concoction on them as far as i know the french dont do that and it was not good in our opinion
reviewTitle: Not exactly French in terms of food sensibility

reviewText: yesterday before the theatre we were wondering around looking for a place for lunch we happened into a small courtyard and found this cute little french bistro we couldnt have planned a better brunch the food was amazing and the serrvice was great i know well be going back

happened on bistro vendome by accidenton a recent sunday afternoon i am french so have a good idea of what i want from a french bistro great service very good food great value bistro met all plus half price bottles of wine on saturdaysunday brunch highly recommended
ive only been there for happy hour fantastic wine menu and service will definitely go back again

in denver for a show at the buell wanted to eat somewhere different and read about this restaurant we didnt have a reservation but sat in the courtyard the food was excellent and the staff was too we had the steak with frittes cheese appetizer and it was really wonderful we will definitely come back

the vendome is a great restaurant service is super and the food excellent i had the onion soup which although a small serving was very good i then had the steak tartare which although very good was a little salty for my taste and could have been more spicy something to remember to ask when i go back enjoyed the meal very much

we had dinner here on some patricks day evening the place was full so we sat at the bar the service from the excellent bartender and the meal was excellent we also enjoyed a halfprice bottle wine deal which even made it more appealing

our party of 8 sat for over an hour before getting served when we queried what the issue was the employee stated they were serving a large party and were very busy the food was only fair with one dish being seriously undercooked no managerial staff seemed to be concerned with the issue this evening out was a spectacular disappointment

the food was phenomenal we had a steak tartare crispy duck leg confit braised beef and steak frites and all the mains were delicious having visited france several times we found their food to be very authentic great ambience quick service and delicious food highly recommended
reviewTitle: The best Steak Tartare we’ve ever had!

reviewText: we picked this particular restaurant because the menu was excellent with a diverse party of 6 each person was able to find something they enjoyed we loved the restaurant and larimer street was beautifully lit we used the valet parking which made parking stress free during the holiday season
reviewTitle: Lovely restaurant, great service, great food

reviewText: what a lovely lovely restaurant nestled in a gorgeous alleyway off the main thoroughfare of larimer square when eating at a french restaurant why did i order steak i could not resist the steak au poivre and found it a bit too peppery as did a companion who ordered the same meal the ladies ordered more french cuisine and were delighted with their choices i did have an accompanimant of the frites and they were delicious as advertised and would eat here again just for another try

i was invited to bistro vendome on a first date and it made a wonderful first impression it is a quaint little bistro that could very well have been on the streets of paris in addition to the lovely romantic ambiance i was thoroughly impressed with the food and service we tried the escargot and halibut found them both to be delicious and delectable
reviewTitle: A slice of Paris in Denver!

placeAddress: 3401 W Airport Fwy Ste 112, Irving, TX 75062-5931
reviewText: i have been looking for bakery like this for a very long time it is a kind of bakery you see on every corner in southern american countries everything is so fresh and delicious i shop there every time when i am in the area or on my way to somewhere i wish it is near where i live so i can go there every day

try the texas toothpicks they are tasty the ribs had plenty of meat but a little over done like the bones disentigraded otherwise they were still good there are two separate areas to eat up front which has no personality or back in the bar where it is a little more friendly

always sit in the bar unless you are with children the atmosphere in the back is great and i always get great service back there the front feels too open and exposed food is good no matter what i love the burgers
good service great food nice place this was a nice place to meet some friends over beer and food
reviewTitle: Best Philly sandwich outside of philly

reviewText: this is a fun sports bar with great service i eat there regularly and have never had any issues with the food or the service they have daily and happy hour specials the atmosphere is laid back a great place to watch the game and grab a beer

we had lunch at the bricks at the suggestion of trip advisor and we were not disappointed we ordered the club sandwhich and the reuben the beer was cold the tea was fresh and the service was good the owner mike was the bartender and was very friendly this is a good stopping place in a town you might think has nothing to offer we just had sandwiches but they were both well prepared and the food came quickly
neither my friend my motherinlaw or i really care for the food here the service is something to be reckoned with but my hubs ate there with a friend and said it was better catfish was good
this is a very nice place to eat great service and an adequate menu the pull pork sandwich with regular fries hand cut is my favorite though the philly and tacos on taco tuesday are very good as well
reviewTitle: Everything I've tried has been good.

reviewText: the bricks is a great place to eat and have a cold beer the service is excellent and so is the atmosphere and food the owners are there everyday helping wait tables serve drinks and visit with the customers we go to the bricks frequently and have always had a very positive experience i highly recommend the pub on the bricks
great service great food and great atmosphere do you need anything else when out of town for dinner
chili bites fried pickle and steaks were great wings need work service was great
food seemed cheap or generic not overly expensive but would go elswhere for the food

placeName: Norwich Meadows Organic Farm - Tompkins Square
reviewText: norwich meadows is a certified organic mostly nospray farm that comes to the grownyc tompkins square greenmarket on sunday year round from 9am4pm the farm is very popular with chefs from top restaurants such as jean georges and home cooks around nyc norwich has green vegetables throughout the year and fruits including melons and berries in the summer there is an extensive vegetable variety more extensive and fresher than grocery stores including kale collards mustards spinach herbs lettuce beans cauliflower tomatoes and melons

placeName: Norwich Meadows Organic Farm - Abingdon Square
reviewText: norwich meadows is a certified organic ny farm coming to abingdon square greenmarket 12th st 8 av on saturdays from 8am2pm from midmay through thanksgiving the farms practices are even more natural than certified organic standards and norwich has many special varieties of very fresh vegetables including dark leafy greens the farm also sells to many of the top restaurants in nyc including jean georges and union square hospitality group restaurants to attest to the quality the staff are very friendly like the rest of the greenmarket

reviewText: first time at this establishment service was not excellent some of the food was cold and they took long to bring out the food when it finally got there it wasnt bad the servers were pleasant the manager at no time came over to address or apologize for the lack of service hopefully other folks have had good experiences this restaurant didnt make a great expression on me

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W Green Acres Common, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText: first time visiting a bj restaurant and certainly wont be recommending or returningthis one at least tables were available yet long wait line form at the entrance took over 30 minute to receive anything drinksfoodgetting the waitress attention yes even getting a menu took this long pizookie which we were most excited to receive seemed under cooked and not what we expected items that we ordered but did not receive were added to our bill not a pleasant experience and dont think it will get any better soon

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W Green Acres Common, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText: i had a family dinner there we heard about the other bjs restaurants and this was the first time we were eating at one so we thought it should be really good we were sorely disappointed it was obvious they had recently opened and they were still figuring out how to cook and how to serve maybe they should just borrow the playbook from the other locations it took 3 attempts actual requests to get a glass of water the cutlery was dirty the food tasted old or stale for most parts we just paid and left

reviewText: homophobic management i went in with a group of 10 friends and my service dog and was quickly told that apparently my dog had entered the kitchen when he had been in our possession the entire time i was never asked whether my dog was a service dog and never issued a warning when i spoke with their team member they mocked my last name and called me a slur as a local dumbo resident i encourage others to spend their dollars at a more supportive location in the neighborhood horrible people

reviewText: stopped here recently for a cocktail or 2 on a nice sunny day enjoyed the good pours from the bartender and the tasty large pretzel
a great sports bar the menu is good and the atmosphere is very friendly the bartender makes all the patrons feel special

tap house has a good locationmore so if youre walking the food is good but its basically bar food they have a good asst of beers and the prices are good its a good atmosphere and friendly staff good music bear in mind its a fairly small place

i went here with a friend for a burger and beer to watch game i was generally good my only issue was that it was very very loud i dont generally like loud places so a bit of a bummer the noise was from the music and televisions not the people in the bar the burgers beers and service was good i never went back so i guess that sums it up pretty well because i eat in the area frequently

reviewText: i end my morning workout with nice hot coffee the cold brew is good too for a special treat try the brownie vegan carrots muffin and honey croissant they rock pastry my son is an addict now i am trying to limit the joy to twice a week very nice people make you feel welcome

reviewText: aunt helens coffee cake chocolate croissants chocolate cherry scones ham and swiss everything croissants are fantastic closed monday cash only everything else looks wonderful tootake a bag of goodies to the surfer beach and watch the showgood beach on a budget for local nyers the a train all the way to broad channel the shuttle to 90thholland walk towards the beach make a left on rock beach blvd

placeAddress: 8710 Rockaway Beach Blvd, Far Rockaway, NY 11693-1610
reviewText: stumbled upon the 2for1 sunday happy hour 3p4p and what a delight i had the best ham and swiss on a croissant followed by grandmas plum cake which was amazing it would have been a steal at 5 for the sandwich but with the 2for1such a deal we ate in the darling little cafe inside although theres plenty of backyard space too super friendly service and delicious baked treats
the bread here is fantastic the fancy cookies are delicious well worth the price ive ordered cakes from here before and they are delicious as well great place in a changing neighborhood

old school small town bakery from a time when quality and the customer came first delicious mouth watering breads fresh baked i we finished a loaf of their famous prosciutto bread and were looking for more you cant find this kind of quality and taste in any supermarket we havent tasted a better pignoli cookie soft and tasty the rainbow cookies the biscottis the semolina bread makes it all worth the trip the owner rocky a fourthgeneration artisan baker is handson and has been for almost 30 years enjoy

its hard to find an authentic baker nowadays but if you are in brooklyn and you want to sample the best there is then you owe it to yourself to stop at kingshighway bakery fantastic freshly baked italian bread cookies and cakes fresh and hot all day fast and friendly service and the price is right you wont be disappointed get over there today
what could i say i own the place come on down see for yourself baking fresh italian bread in this location for 30 years

we visited randolph beer after walking across the brooklyn bridge before heading back via the manhattan bridge just the thing for a couple of folks with tired feet in need of refreshment the place was absolutely packed a beautiful saturday afternoon but we found a table outside to enjoy the day i was impressed with how familyfriendly the setup inside was games and spaces for children and others worked into the seating areas very cool place to spend an afternoon oh and the beer was good too
reviewTitle: Perfect spot for a pick-me up!

reviewText: we were walking around brooklyn seeing the sights when we fell on this place a great concept of a beer wall with 24 micro breweries to sample you get a card and then you pick up a glass and go and sample there were some nice ales and cider that our party enjoyed if your in the area and like different ales give this place a go great beer staff and atmosphere

i loved the self service beer tasting and like that you could buy an ounce or two or 12 or 16 wash your mug put you little card on the machine and taste away while you pay by the ounce and it tallies right on a screen to let you know what it cost the beer is very very expensive considering that you are really serving yourself
reviewTitle: Nice place to get a craft beer

reviewText: first trip to brooklyn but met a friend who lived in the area so therefore knew of good places to visit loved it i drink cider only one to choose from from but wow it was good we were there on a monday afternoon so very quiet but must be a really buzzy place at busier times worth the walk
reviewTitle: Unusual location great choice of drinks

reviewText: por alguma razão não fiquei com vontade de voltar mas o lugar é bonito decoração impecável autoserviço bacana de cervejas mas falta algo
reviewTitle: Lugar bonito, tudo certo, mas falta clima.

reviewText: micro brewery and saw the tanks on the other side of the building decided to go in hidden entrance but when inside great atmosphere fantastic place and beer

i cant say that this place is anything spectacular even though it can be hard to get reservations on a sunday the food is ok and the ambiance of the place is fine there are some decent dishes on the menu but doesnt compare to many other french places ive been to this is one of the only french places in the area so if that is what you are craving it may be your only choice

although french mominette put out some wait for it delicious fried chicken everything is prepared perfectly like a solid bistro in paris the charming courtyard polite service and delicious food we enjoyed at lunch is like a secret discovery although mominette is well known in bkln because is it located on an out of the way otherwise anonymous block of bushwick recommend

reviewText: nous avons été dans ce restaurant parce que lon ventait son calme dans une cour intérieur cuisine française la cour est plaisante ombragée calme cest important car à new york tout est bruyant la nourriture cest bien moyen et la carte variée coq au vin cassoulet salade niçoise saumon le vin français beau nom beaujolais châteaux de bordeaux une chose est sur il ne vient pas de france

our niece was married under the canopy roof in the rain surrounded by family and friends mominette provided fabulous appetizers and specialty drinks along with a selection of 5 entrees and 4 fabulous desert cakes service was impeccable and only surpassed by the food

very authentic brooklyn restaurant established in 1939 old world french charm with comfortable seating within the bar setting specials were generous and the seafood pasta was perfect paired with the bordeaux carrot fennel soup was the best everas it warmedthe palate and the soul service team worked well together and made our family visit comfortable to celebrate nicks running the brooklyn half marathon and many birthdays and happy moments wonderful experience

we had an absolutely lovely dinner there on christmas eve i had the escargots the ratatouille the buche and some sparkly rosé and it was all really good the service was great as well with a french waiter who took great care of us and was really helpful and fun to talk to to be recommended in williamsburg

went for brunch last weekend and it was fantastic our party got the pancake the eggs benedict and an omelette and each one was excellent also has a great french ambiance wait staff was attentive and also very good would definitely go back

it doesnt hurt that mominette is a few steps from my sisters apartment but this is one of my absolute favorites in brooklyn its a beautiful little gem with a hidden garden and a funky interior i almost licked my croque madame plate clean
very hipster but beautiful garden and very tasty breakfast at an affordable price we were five people and they accommodated us very well service was fast and friendly
decent french food though i am not a fan of french food its more of a new american french combo hipster style waitstaff are nice cocktails are great and its likely youll have a good dinner here
the brunch menu was varied food was well prepared service was cheerful and attentive would go back again

reviewText: ive eaten here three maybe four times and i wont go back because of the atmosphere i tried and failed at being comfortable at this restaurant the owner is a jerk and the staff is very uneven there is nothing wrong with the food its pretty good but im generally not treated very well by the snobby elitist hipster waitstaff thats all

reviewText: i was lured into the place as the manager said there was happy hour i had to wait for 30 minutes to get a drink although the place was at 25 capacity the food was very average for turkish and extremely small in quantity i was finally charged my full glass and the manager refused to connect she walked away the entire experience was dissapointing

reviewText: weve had late lunch on last weekend august 30th weve sat on the outside due to the situations of covd19 it was great releasable to fill up our tummy service was great clean and the best is yummy i would love to go back

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: food is always so fresh and delicious we have visited the restaurant many times throughout the years and have ordered in and have never been disappointed a wonderful delicious friendly neighborhood gem the entire team is always so welcoming and helpful perfect experience and now during the pandemic it is definitely the cleanest restaurant we have visited everything from cutlery to tables to food to masks and gloves is strictly kept according to cdc guidance we cannot thank bodrum enough for being so responsible delicious safe and fan especially during these gloomy times

reviewText: indian restaurant we found from our guidebook good value buffet lunch menu very tasty especially the dahl very lively busy restaurant where we had a nice meal

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the food is very authentic and prepared fresh i was there with my family and enjoyed the tandoori chicken and kababs chicken biryani is good however the service is very poor even before you finish your food the server waiting to pick and they just pickup the plate never checks back and ask feed back and i feel its kind of rude

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this is a good indian restaurant with good food decent service but somewhat cramped and congested its hard to get around in particularly at the lunch buffet hour when mobility is a necessity the buffet has a somewhat smaller number of items than most indian buffet spreads but they do bring you naans and bhel poori to the table i guess i was sated but not blown away by the place and somewhat uncomfortable in cramped quarters

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this one is a sad turn for lovers of authentic indian food the venue looks great and well decorated the lighting is perfect the crowd is not loud a great place to hang out the service needs improvement though they promptly served papad with chutney papad was crunchy and fresh and chutneys were good too the food was great but the service completely ruined the experience the server was disinterested and unfocused just felt that they overcharge where they can because they know they can

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: nel quartiere di little india in mezzo a tanti locali di cucina locale abbiamo provato questo attirati dalla location curata e sicuramente un ristorante con prezzi più elevati della media del quartiere ma considerando le porzioni molto generose in pratica si può davvero limare il conto stando attenti a non ordinare troppe portate il cibo è indiano doc con buona qualità degli ingredienti piatti saporiti e ben cucinati in modo tradizionale attenti a quelli piccanti perchè lo sono davvero

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: tasty well spiced meal great selection of curries including vegan and vegetarian and the lunch deal is cheap although staff could have been a bit more friendly

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: located between 27th and 28th street on lexington avenue walking distance from madison square garden small area but well managed restaurant very reasonable price for lunch buffet 12 some items they serve on the table bhel puri naans and tandoori chickens are some of those awesome taste fish curry and chicken tikka masala was good

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: went here for a business lunch with a coworker and we had a 60pp budget ended up spending it all incl tax and tip we went for the lunch and did look at the buffet but decided that we would rather order a selection of things from the menu we got the butter chicken soso the lamb phaal very spicy a little vinegary very tender lamb incredibly good peas pulav rice naan amazing aloo mutter a nice complement to the heavier curries chicken korma absolutely heavenly and mango lassis delicious

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: in the area of nyc full of indian restaurants and grocery stores dhaba really shines true authentic flavors brought to us the tastes and scents of india service was excellent and our server contributed advice

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i have been here twice my indian friend recommended this restaurant i then invited my tea friends for a dinner gathering since theyre vegan they loved this place and said it was a good choice i love the potato veggies and the spices that was part of the the dishesservice was very friendly and nice my favorite drink is the mango lasse at this restaurant i had two drinks delicious and fresh mango yogurt drink

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we had a light dinner here at 8pm on a weeknight the weather was perfect and the restaurant was open to the street although we sat inside the hummus and pita bread are so good ive never had such great pita bread we shared a kabob which was a healthy choice i found the chicken a little well done but my husband said it was perfect we had a wonderful red wine with it all and it was a wonderful place to be able to visit with our friends

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: walked over to bodrum this past sunday at 600pm and got the last table before the restaurant was filled lively spot with outdoors tables and doors that open onto the street looking for a great lamb shank with couscous or a beautifully cooked roast chicken or a pizza try bodrum very tasty food excellent service and a nice buzz

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: good quality food at reasonable prices efficient staff and pleasant recommend this restaurant and will certainly go back

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we went here late on a saturday night definitely get a reservation through open table or by calling ahead as it does get busy now that the sidewalk seating is not available because of the cold weather there are less tables but the food it still great we had the mezz platter for three of us and loved sampling all the different items the lamb tagine and steak kabob were great and the baklava dessert was perfect highly recommend trying here for dining in or delivery

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: piccola realtà quasi familiare in una città di stucchevoli e non sempre credibili grandi chef nel piacevole quartiere residenziale intorno ad amsterdam avenue il clima tiepido di ny allinizio del mese di ottobre ci ha permesso di cenare nei tavoli allaperto sullavenue antipasto mezé assortito fatto in casa e abbondante carne al forno di buon livello prezzo contenuto per nyc una bella sosta clientela locale servizio cortese ottima birra efes turca

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: humus i think stuffed cabbage leaves lamb patties a salad an ok bottle of wine and one desert for 3 all mediocre and horribly overpriced at well over 120 service too casual and lackadaisical does not live up to the reviews by any stretch

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: stopped for a coffee the other morning friendly and efficient and in a land of bad coffee it was at least drinkable

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: informal upper west side spot with plenty of outdoor seating mediterranean menu with inventive pizzas tagines moussaka and many turkish specialties unhurried

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: a great menu with all the classicsand some things for the vegetarians as well i had the vegetable tagine and it was a really decentsized portion desserts were also greatespecially the milk pudding cozy dining room and good service as well great place for conversation

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the poster said vindaloo went inside no vindaloo and their rice was hard and old they should keep the buffet fresh i went there for lunch buffet on the sunday i feel it was not a great experience and the service station it was very dark it was hard to see the food

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: dhaba is the real thing not fancy but a great vibe and the food is superb try the sizzling chicken malai but whatever you do dont miss the sarson ka saag which is pureed mustard greens that ive only ever found done right at one other place in manhattan tasty and bitter fabulous chef hemant mathur owns several restaurants on curry hill lexington avenue in the 20s but this is the most fun for a more sedate quieter meal try his haldi but for a raucous crowd and great indian go for dhaba
reviewTitle: Great Indian food by a Michelin star chef

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: prix très intéressants pour les quantités servies pas mal de choix dans la carte comme dhabitude jai commandé un plat et jen ai eu un autre et pourtant cest mon collègue américain qui a passé commande le problème ne vient donc pas de moi service un peu sec et impersonnel cuisine délicieuse cependant

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: conheci o dhaba por indicação de um guia de viagem e fiquei maravilhada no almoço funciona como buffet pelo qual se paga u1295 há cerca de dez opções de pratos mais uma sobremesa e tudo é muito gostoso e bem feito adorei os temperos indianos e gostei muito do fato de todos os pratos estarem bem quentes há opções com frango e cordeiro e opções vegetarianas todas inclusas no buffet o local é agradável e bonito e os garçons são educados e solícitos para mim foi um achado e tanto em meio a little india recomendo
