placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: picked this place at random among a number of indian restaurants clustered around lexington and 27th glad we did large menu with dishes both familiar and not so much small but stylish space comfortable a little dark and a little loud service was good the food came out quick delicious large portions as spicy as youd want it the only minor disappointment was the onion naan which didnt have much flavor prices are fair and reasonable i will definitely return although id probably also try some of the surrounding places to compare

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: authentic punjabi food and certainly cant complain about the portions prices good for nyc given the quality not sure why the staff give the impression that they are doing you a favour allowing you to eat there
reviewTitle: Good food, generous portions, miserable staff...

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: dhaba in nyc offers excellent indian cuisine at very reasonable prices the atmosphere is pleasant and the service was great it is located in an area that is saturated with indian restaurants markets etc and would be easy to overlook since it isnt as large or flashy as some of the others we plan to make this a routine stop when we visit manhattan in the future

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we went to dhaba indian cuisine at lexington avenue the food was extremely bad the naans served were lumpy not freshly made not even toasted well one of the worst naans i ever ate could not even eat the service has been pathetic all the time they were arranging the tables repetitivelynot even asking or looking at the customers no service at all neither the food nor the service is goodvery disappointed just a ripoff i would definitely not recommend and i would never ever visit this restaurant again
reviewTitle: Very bad food and bad service

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: wide menu great for vegetarian many choices well cooked food very noisy restaurant not suitable for business dinner fair prices

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: with so many choices nearby why subject yourself to this totally unprofessional restaurant that doesnt even honor reservations the food is not good enough to warrant such an underwhelming experience

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: good restaurant slightly cramped in space the dishes were good and authentic opening the door was letting the cold air in

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the restaurant seating is a bit cramped we tried the paneer pakora and the traditional saag with maki ki roti the helping are very generous two of us shared the meal and it was more than enough

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: abbiamo provato questo ristorante perché consigliato dalla nostra guida locale non molto grande affollato ma con servizio rapido cibo buono cè il rischio di ordinare piatti molto piccanti forse meglio chiedere consiglio ai camerieri molto gentili se si hanno difficoltà ad interpretare il menù vastissimo buono il pollo con mango di cui non ricordo il nome indiano interessante quello con melanzane affumicate sebbene decisamente piccante prezzo medio

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: our favorite indian restaurant in nyc excellent cuisine wonderful service a pleasure to visit every time

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i tried the chicken kalimirch with garlic naan the spice levels were optimum giving a good taste of indian spices the chicken was very well cooked and soft as well the quantity was very good as well and one plate could be good enough for 2 people i would surely recommend this place they are also usually full always and there is some waiting
reviewTitle: My favorite Indian Restaurant in NYC

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: this restaurant was a great meal i was here with my fiancé for date night we sat outside and the service was incredible the mushroom pizza was thin crust and delicious but the moussaka main course stole the meal

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we ate here last week and it was authentic turkish food well priced also everything was well prepared and cant wait to go back hard to find foods great
reviewTitle: Best Turkish food outside of Turkey

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: in a friday night at 630pm we had to wait about 20 minutes for a table for two service was attentive without hovering if you sit outside you are right on the sidewalk as with many city cafes while they were busy service was prompt and polite we had a babaganoush kebab shrimp casserole and leeks all wonderful but nothing topped the bread served as a free appetizer many locals seemed present

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i have been longing for turkish food for a while as a child i lived in istanbul i made a mistake in not making a reservation but we were able to get a table although not fully turkish we enjoyed our borek phyllo cheese pastry red lentil soup salad and salmon our young guest had white pizza we ordered a bottle of argentinian malbec and enjoyed the evening prices were okay but of course the wine inflated the tab

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: if you love turkish food you cant beat bodrum really nice environment very attentive staff and service and the food of which we ordered several dishes was delicious loved our time at bodrum and would definitely come back

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we loved the food at this little restaurant the chicken kabob was tender and nicely seasoned the baklava was worth the calories unfortunately the waitress was snippy perhaps because she was the only waitress on duty for saturday lunch seriously understaffed

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: enjoyed the food at bodrum and the service was quite good as well lots of good menu choices served quickly

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: the bread served with olives and olive oil when you arrive hard not to fill up on that it is divine the rest of the food was executed nicely i had imam bayildi and stuffed grape leaves the restaurant has a nice varied menu and according to my dining partner it is very reliable a good choice for a weeknight meal

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: this busylittle turkish restaurant on amsterdam ave is a gem of a place to run into from the pouring rain as was the case for us recently we were made welcome immediately and offered service quickly even though the place was extremely busy we had some delicious humous and bread a pizza a chicken kebab that was incredibly tender and tasty a couple of other side dishes too it was great value for money for food of good quality we will be back there in a day or two for sure

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: after an hour perusing restaurant menus on line for recommended restaurants in the neighborhood where were staying upper west side my teenage traveling companions and i agreed on bodrums i was happy with their mediterranean options the girls were happy with the gourmet pizzas and the ambiance was cozy the service excellent
reviewTitle: Great Food to please diverse palatesb

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: well prepared mediterranean food with a turkish accent and a wide range of pizzas are what draws in a steady clientele for lunch with more than a few moms and kids and dinner a destination probably not but a great asset for the neighborhood if you are looking for good food decently priced and thoughtfully served
reviewTitle: An ideal neighorhood place on Upper West Side

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: bodrum is a small turkish restaurant which offers a variety of mediterranean food there is a nice assortment of appetizers and great warm turkish bread friends are not adventurous so we ordered babaghanoushsalad pizza and chicken shish kabob cooked to perfection dessert was baklava not too sweet perfect this is a small restaurant and a local favorite prices are very reasonable will return if in the area
reviewTitle: Great Turkish restaurant in West Side

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i dont have anything bad to say about this place very polite and friendly staff good and quick service reasonable price nice interior the food was delicious we were on a 7 day trip and ate in many places and this was the best remember to book a table beforehand

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: my husband daughter and i had dinner at bodrum a few days ago it is a small casual restaurant that was busy we were lucky to have a table after waiting 15 minutes everything was very good we had the large salad of tomatoes and cucumbers a pizza and a moussaka the ingredients of the moussaka were different from the expected lacked potatoes and a lot of ground beef yet it was quite good the service was prompt and friendly we will return to bodrum in the near future

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: после двух дней в ньюйорке разочаровался в американской еде невкусная пластмасса эти ребята меня спасли за несколько дней в первый раз я поел с удовольствием оставшиеся 5 дней буду есть только у турков турки я вас люблю
reviewTitle: Снова убедился, что турецкий - это эталон!

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: everything we ate in this restaurant was delicious i arrived before my friends ordered the appetizer samplerit took all my self control to leave some for them to eat it didnt help that the waitress kept bringing hotfromtheoven bread that i used to eat the sampler with we had the moussaka which was deconstructed so dont expect the usual recipe the chicken sis kebab and the fish tangine all full of flavor very friendly wait staff in this small restaurant that is warmed by the oven i highly recommend eating here

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: a great neighborhood find with wonderful warm service and excellent mediterranean cuisine the 4 of us tried most things on the menu and it all tasted delicious drinks were prepared to perfection and the bread is wow small simple but wonderful place will for sure return

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i spend two times with friends here and all of them world travelers who agreed with me that the food was exceptional
reviewTitle: Better than Turkish food in Turkey!

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we were here for lunch today the staff was very good the menu as well we had have hummus to start which was wunderful also the main pizza lamp kebab and sandwich absolut great definatly a place to come back

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i went here with my family for sunday brunch the city seemed unusually quiet but i guess even in the city that never sleeps sunday starts slowly the restaurant filled up around us but i never felt crowded or overwhelmed by other diners or noise the service was attentive from the first moment to the last the menu had enough choices for meat eaters and vegetarians and we took advantage of the diversity no skimping on these plates each dish was a full and tasty meal and priced quite nicely
reviewTitle: Sunday Brunch - good food, good service, pleasant environment.

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i could rave about the lebne a thick mild yogurt with walnuts or the homemade bread or the olive oil on the mediterranean salad or the baklava or any number of other items i and my friends had tonight but what blew me away was the service in a full restaurant we were treated as if nobody mattered more than we did the staff genuinely cared about the quality of the food and the service the prices were very reasonable this was my second visit i will definitely return on my next visit to new york

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: despite late hours service was good and shepherd salad was as it should be turkish sis kebab was also nice it was not much expensive

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: some of the dishes on the menu are delicious and others are ok i think it is worth an extra few minutes to choose carefully from the menu and you will be rewarded for the effort i like the bureks and wine by the glass are also good outdoor seating is great in nice weather

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we enjoyed our dinner at bodrum we sat inside as it was too humid outside the tables are on the small side and close to each other but the food makes up for this fresh hot pita with olives in olive oil are brought to table right away very tasty we shared a shepherds salad with feta which was delicious for main course we had the chicken adana and the moussaka both were excellent we were too full for desert hopefully next time all in all this is a welcoming restaurant with delicious menu choices

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: very nice neighborhood restaurant my criteria for giving this a very good rather than an excellent is that i dont think i would want to travel across town for this restaurant as a destination my biggest complaint about the meal was that i enjoyed the woodfiredoven bread and dips too much so ate more bread than i should have we ordered various dishes including wood fired chicken and fish tagine and enjoyed them all the service was good would definitely return
reviewTitle: Very nice neighborhood restaurant - outdoor seating, wood-fired oven and good food

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we went for a family dinner and were not disappointed the service was wonderful the bread was really great and for the five of us that went there all ordering something different there was no complaints well maybe my chicken was a little cold we will certainly be back great prices great service and great food why would be not go back special shout out to the yesik salad super yummy
reviewTitle: Left feeling like we had a great time and a great meal.

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: wife and i went for lunch we enjoyed everything from the delicious bread to the filo and cheese appetizer to the mediterranean pizza which we shared service was very good ambiance was fair because of the closeness of the tables the menu was large and prices were reasonable

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: often in upper west side to visit family bodrum has quickly become my favorite restaurant delicious food good beers outdoor seating and incredible homemade bread i love the lamb shank and their baba is incredible it is a small venue but i love it for date nights and for late dinners very reasonably priced for nyc as well

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: bodrum has a laid back atmosphere that is a plus but it was carried too far during our brunch the food good took a long time and then only those who ordered from the lunch menu were served while the two who ordered breakfast had to wait awkward

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: great dips especially the labne and manti delicious fresh bread good flatbreads and kebabs something for the whole family

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i went with a group of 8 we had some delicious pizza hummus and baba ganoush the restaurant was small it could be open to the sidewalk and made for a nice open air setting the service was excellent

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: four of us shared hummus and babaghanoush as appetizers this was followed by lamb tagine turkish braised lamb shank and a margherita pizzafor drinks we had 2 cokes one wine and a cocktail i believe we also shared yesil salad romaine olives dill scallions cucumbers and fetaall was good along with the delicious bread my rating would be a b for food a for service and b for atmosphere not overly noisy and fair pricingabout 78 per couple including tip would return
reviewTitle: Good Bet for a Casual Dinner

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: оточный ресторан для семейного или романтичного ужинаприятная атмосферауют и отменные турецкие блюдацены очень приемлемые я бы даже сказала дешёвые по американским меркам вино тоже не дорогое очень советую посетить
reviewTitle: Один из самых лучших турецких ресторанов нью йорка

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: cheap and fast as long as you dont have to wait for a table richly spiced without setting fire to your mouth they present a buffet with a selection of dishes that changes each day
reviewTitle: Best Lunch buffet on Curry Hill

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this place has a good luncheon buffet with very good food but i found it a bit stuffy very crowded and some of the staff were less than friendly if you like a good bargain indian buffet this is the place if you can put up with a noisy spot probably good with office mates and then you might deal with some rather dour people there
reviewTitle: Good Luncheon Buffet but crowded and some attitude

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: große erwartungen hatten wir naan ok bis gut und zwei currys ok für den preis aber nicht uneingeschränkt zu empfehlen imho auch mit das teuerste indien resto in der straße

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we were staying at the hotel giraffe and asked for a recommendation for indian food and they oh you are lucky there are some amazing indian restaurants a block away we have eaten in many indian restaurants all over the world and sri lankan and bangladeshi and pakistani so we arent innocents dhaba was great authentic huge portions great service the place was packed and full of real ambience

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: very good authentic indian food open late meat dishes are excellent as well as vegetarian convenient downtown location

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: excelente chiken masala y samosas restaurante que a la hora que yo fui y contrario a lo que afirma mucha gente acá estaba muy desocupado si vas a la hora de almuerzo o cena en nyc no esperes ningún sitio vacío la atención esmerada siempre pendientes de servirte agua necesaria para las especias de la comida no es de las mejores comidas indias que he probado en la vida pero el sitio está bien 30 usd por persona
reviewTitle: Buena comida india a precio aceptable.

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we went for a lunch buffet to the dhaba on a sunday surprisingly even at 230pm it was rather full with a fair buzz we had the buffet while the spread was good and the taste of most of the dishes was ok there was nothing exceptional the chhole was below average but the chicken tikka masala the aloo matar and the punjabi kadhi were good it satisfied my urge for an indian meal but it did not have anything which would stop me from trying another restaurant

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: really very nice food in foreign country very very delicious foodand sarso da saag and makke di roti very tasty

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we had a fabulous dinner at this friendly reasonably priced indian restaurant the food was top quality and every dish was superb try the lasuni gobi spicy cauliflower appetizer punjabi cabbage w cumin turmeric chilies and chicken chutneywala chicken curry w mangos green masala fantastic

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: their malai kofta is a must for those who stick to vegetarian food its our goto place for indian food in nyc
reviewTitle: Best Indian food in the city!

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we enjoyed a number of delicious fresh dishes from the lunch buffet at dhaba the place was packed soon after they opened at noon but the service for beverages naan bread and complimentary tandoori chicken delivered individually was without flaw and fast some nice touches here the tandoori chicken and a fresh well stocked buffet the selections were varied spiced as they should be well be back for a more leisurely dinner to enjoy the selections they offer off menu

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i live a few blocks away and dhaba has become my goto spot for indian cuisine the space is lively but not usually loud and very casual i have never been disappointed and their london curry house menu is particularly good price is moderate compared to some of the cheapeats offerings nearby but the quality at dhaba is far superior
reviewTitle: Best Choice for Indian Food on Curry Hill

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: three of us went for dinner it was very spicy but they brought us some yogurt and a mango drink to help cut the spice staff was friendly and helpful this was our second visit to dhaba we enjoyed it both times

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: food was good and very tasty i am pure vegeterian but really enjoyed paneer tikka and also lunch buffet salted lassi is a must try
reviewTitle: Food was good and very tasty

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: das restaurant ist unscheinbar von außen das für new york preiswerte essen war allerdings jeden dollar wert das naan war frisch das mango chutney und die dips sehr sehr lecker wir bestellten chicken tikka masala und reis es war sehr geschmacksintensiv einfach genial einen tipp beim inder reicht meistens eine portion für zwei personen vollkommen aus ich bin mit einem lächeln aus diesem restaurant gegangen und schwärme jetzt noch davon einfach nur lecker

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: great service great food excellent location worth the penny go for it we had lunch buffet

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: no creo que un restaurante lleno hasta los topes pueda ser considerado bueno el dhaba tiene fama en nueva york y la comida está rica pero está hasta la bola se puede ir pero hay que saber lo que te vas a encontrar

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: the service here was some of the best we had in new york not in your face but very pleasant and attentive the food was very good i had the lamb tagine and my wife had the mossaka both very tasty a couple of glasses of very nice wine and a dessert to share excellent fare all round

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we happened upon this restaurant on the tuesday evening looking for some brick oven pizza first off the toasty warm bread they gave at the beginning was great foreshadowing of what was to come it was up there with the best breads ive eaten in restaurants in nyc then we split the babaghanoush which was smokey and as spoton as the bread was we also split a primavera pizza which i loved as well the waiter was nice and the washroom is very serene with a lovely shade of blue overall a wonderful dining experience i will return soon
reviewTitle: Lovely place with great food and service

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we visited for a luncheon service is attentive not intrusive the food is well presented there was a brunch menu which was reasonable and full we had a combination of dishes including a pizza the soups were plentiful

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: an individual pizza serves two normal people way too easy the place is great and the food is so good

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: cant say enough positive things about this place pizza is off the charts delicious turkish fare is yummy kebabs are melt in your mouth fabulous

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: went here based on a a tip from a friend both appetizers were good but my main course was just ok i had a pounded and rolled piece of chicken with rice which was good quality but lacked flavor the other diner had a lamb dish kebob which seemed better

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we have chosen to go the the bodrum restaurant many times it sits about 36 people its cozy pleasantly designed and comfortable the open brick oven is a delight not only do they bake pizzas in the oven but roast chicken and lambbut also shish kabobs yum i like the earthy red wines and mint teas among the many beverage choices you may need a reservation for evenings or weekends but that should not be a problem
reviewTitle: An Absolute Favorite!  Excellent food, pleasant atmosphere, and good service.

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i have been to bodrum two time in each instance it was a bit last minute on a friday night reservations are definitely required but i had none i called and they kindly found a place for my son and i we just had to limit our time to 90 minutes no problem the food is delicious and a very good value i highly recommend bodrum and will undoubtedly make a third visit with reservations next time
reviewTitle: Very good food and accommodating service

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: ww went for lunch quiet nonpretentious friendly and efficient service and good food of course reasonanly priced

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: buono il cibo cucinato con cura e soprattutto il servizio delle ragazze è stato impeccabile forse troppo considerato che non è un posto di lusso comunque gentile la ragazza che appena si è liberato un posto dentro mi ha liberato dalla brezza autunnale del dehoor

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: when i saw shakshuka eggs poached in a tomatobased sauce on the menu i knew id found the right place for brunch wellprepared turkish dishes with fresh ingredients reasonable prices lots of outdoor seating pairs well on a sunday morning with a visit to the museum of natural history and a stroll through central park

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: restaurante extremamente agradável decoração rústica em madeira preços excelentes muitas opções e combinações de pratos mediterrâneos e árabes atendimento atencioso e uma bela localização para se andar depois azeites com especiarias combinam bem com pão sírio

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: our food was really delicious the service was attentive without being cloying i am not a connoiseur of this cuisine but the interplay of some of my favorite spices was superb
reviewTitle: The Mediterranean food you love done really well!

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: lets begin with very attentive service bread was often offered and quite delicious fresh from the oven combination mezz is very delicious though a little skimpy on the savory pastries offering only 1 each for a platter that should serve 2 for the money kefti and stuffed eggplant dishes were mouth watering med salad ok but needs a more interesting dressing
reviewTitle: Reasonable neighborhood Turkish/Med restaurant with good food.

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: dinner at bodrum was really good had the chicken kabob with rice delicious my husband enjoyed a personal pizza one of my favorite things about this place was the smells all around you the tables are close and the scent of everyones orders fills the air and its all good you can dine indoors or the little sidewalk cafe outside prices were reasonable service was good and our server in particular had a very good sense of humor we also shared the homemade chocolate pudding which was tasty

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: the upper west side is a real family neighborhood and it is filled with many casual restaurants the bodrum has tables outside so that the people watching is part of its charm the food is very authentic and we felt as if we were in turkey they bake their own bread which is not a pita but is chewy and delicious this is served with turkish olives and olive oil we sampled several meses all of which were delicious and enjoyed the tasty shepherds salad the wine list was adequate and the service was friendly and solicitous
reviewTitle: Delightful cafe in upper west side

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: it is always good to know that a neighborhood place is maintaining its level one sign of course is that it is busy bodrum was busy last night as always we shared the plate of sample appetizers along with the focaccia olive oil and olives that arrive immediately our mains were fourseasons pizza moussaka and fish tagine all were enjoyed we drank a bottle of the house turkish red pleasant we will be back

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: found this gem of a restaurant service v friendly atmosphere great and the food was very very good the kids loved theirs and they know their curries just to make us brits feel at home the menu has a page of uk curry dishes will definitely come back here when next in ny
reviewTitle: A real find. The family loved it

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: funky nice indian restaurant good service superb food the food was really delicious very fresh and plenty friendly service

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: elaborate north indian food options with options of drink makes this place unique with other indian food joints bread and preparation is above average and hence quite a popular restaurant in midmanhattan area

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we were looking for an indian restaurant on lexington dhaba had a mix of reviews in various sights but ranked near the top on each so we decided to go service and food were very good the majority of the guests appeared to be indian which is always a good sign i would definitely recommend and would go again

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: one of the best indian food i have tasted in usatry lunch buffet as you will be able to taste varietymango or salty lassi is very goodif you are in new york and try indian foodcome hereplace has indian music playing so of u like it thats a plus

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: dhaba is a simple yet modern looking restaurant located in lexington ave and perhaps a good one their food is just cooked to perfection i have tried both the buffets and al carte and have never been disappointed except for the wait which can be annoying but then its all worth it at the end they also have have kingfisher in draft

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i never understand why desi restaurants need to be rude maybe its a thing waters dont care about you they throw cheap crumpled napkins on the table it is very noisy here but thats not the restaurants fault just the kind of people who come here forgive me if i sound racist im a desi myself place is cramped very cramped and not in a nice way painful to the ears

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: selv om atmosfæren i restauranten er travel blir man ikke stresset av å spise der restauranten er liten og intim og det var nesten fullt begge gangene vi var der noe som er forståelig forde maten er svært god med hyggelige betjening bordene er små så bestiller man mye blir det fort lite plass

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: dhaba has delicious indian food we usually order take out from here but we also have been several times in the restaurant we love the sag paner the chicken tikka sag the naan the okra the cauliflower dishesand alo paratha the food tends to be spicy and hot so be prepared prices are modest by new york rates if you love indian food please visit and check out kalustyans food store across the street namaste

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: was blown away by how delicious the food was and for the price best deal all around for food in the city if i lived here id make this for sure one of my spots

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: standard north indian fare loved their rose lassi kababs were succulent curries had a lot of flavor and naanbreads had nice variety

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: in a neighborhood with a zillion indian restaurants this one is worth a stop extensive menu and accommodating staff excellent chips and dips served gratis when you sit down yummy

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: great food reasonabley priced i recommend the vendeloo with a king fisher draft hot but hot too hot

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: realmente delicioso lo recomiendo ampliamente los niños salieron encantados con la comida la atencion super buena un poquito caro pero vale la pena

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: reserved a table for 4 for dinner we arrived early and were served our drinks and delicious warm turkish bread with excellent olive oil for dipping we then waited and waited and waited for our friends to arrive which they finally did 35 minutes late not a single sign of displeasure from our friendly waitress who kept plying us with bread and kept our water glasses full the food is classic eastern mediterranean well cooked attractively presented and also good value
reviewTitle: Small, lively and with good food and service.

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we had reservations good move hummus was made on premises incredibly delicious shepherd salad and moussaka were more than 2 ladies needed wonderful flavor husband had turkish braised lamb shank so tender it fell off the bone with out of this world taste definitely recommend a return meal

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we have eaten here several times for dinner weeknightsweekends and lunch as well yes it is dark at night and the tables are close together but not more than most other ny placesthe bread is delicious and the entrees are generally good especially the lamb dishes last night we sent back one salad so doused in vinegar it was inedible and the manti dumpling appetizer was gummy and was not eaten they gave us a complimentary dessert chocolate caramel cake that was tasty lastly try not to sit under the speakers the music last night was bad middle eastern disco

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: the reasons i cannot give this place a better rating too noisy to hold a conversation or even to hear the server too dark to see what i was eating tables too close together even for spacechallenged manhattan this was ridiculous perhaps it does better on weekday evenings than it does on weekends it is a shame because the bread which was replenished regularly without having to ask was divine didnt stay for dessert

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: overall its great i ate greek moussaka and otherwisesoo nice if i visit to nyci wanna visit there again thanks for good time and good meals
reviewTitle: The Best Turkish and Greek restaurant in NYC

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: was attracted by the decor and the menu from the website and was not disappointed cozy quaint contemporary interior with great service and excellent food lamb was prepared well and subtly spiced salmon with cardamom was perfectly cooked with well chosen spice mixtures service was attentive but not invasive and prices were very good for amsterdam ave highly recommended

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: been here twice in the last month first time we ordered amazing turkish dishes including the manti appetizer lamb dumplings with yogurt and two entrees chicken adana shish kebab and oven roasted half chicken the appetizer and two entrees were excellent service was very friendly and efficient in our second visit we had their pizza with lamb meatball although good it couldnt compare to the quality of the turkish entrees we had on our first visit my recommendation is to go for their authentic turkish cooking but if you are looking for pizza go elsewhere

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: as an upper west side resident we have plenty of options for good food and this is one of our favorite restaurants its cozy and the food is amazing

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we enjoyed every bite of the delicious mezze and shared the chicken kabob that was quite tasty as well waitstaff was attentive and helpful atmosphere pleasant and inviting this is very good value for the money if you are not familiar with items on the menu ask for suggestions and youll end up with a very delicious meal
reviewTitle: Tasty food in a pleasant atmosphere

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: among the many mediterranean restaurants in the area this is really a cut above while smallcrowded and noisy it still makes for wonderful dining because of the excellent food we ordered way to much but everything sounded so good and didnt disappoint some of the meze plates were a little small three items but main courses were more than ample there are many regulars and we will be back

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i have been there many times with friends gf never been disappointed there are making their own bread the sample plate to share is amazing definitely worth it the pizza are thin and crispy the meat dishes are so tasty everything is fabulous there i really recommend this place and for sure the service is perfect good job guys thomas

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: the salad was pretty good and that is the only reason we are giving it a 3 the waiter had almost nothing to say about the menu except he mentioned one appetizer was mostly oil so we chose another appetizer and that one was extremely oily as wellthey did not give us bread or offer bread with the meal other tables received bread around us the restaurant looks nice inside and the pizza looked good but our experience was why eat here when there are amazing restaurants everywhere in nyc

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: if all you order here are the humous and baba ganoush with their wonderful bread youll be in heaven but we also had their pizzas which are thin and crisp and delicious the classic pizzas were great but so was the pear gorgonzola and arugula pizza the rice pudding was yummy but the strawberry cake had frozen strawberries on top so it was unappealing aside from that it was a lovely dinner and you cant beat these prices in nyc

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we came here with friends who live in nyc otherwise we might not have found it and it was one of the best evenings we had on our trip we shared the mezze sampling plate and a big salad to start both very good then i had the moussaka which was just amazing the staff were very friendly and attentive we sat inside but the windows were open on a warm ny evening so it was just fine im looking forward to coming back

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: excellent food and service always very busy but the food is very consistent 1295 a steal for lunch

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: si vous aimez dîner tranquille oubliez ladressemais on y mange très bien je nai peutêtre pas eu de chance en ce dimanche soir cétait plein de familles avec de jeunes enfants ça brassait dans tous les sens sans parler du niveau sonorele pauvre couple à côté de moi devait littéralement hurler pour sentendre attention à la taille des portions même avec un bon coup de fourchette jai regretté davoir pris une entrée avant le plat

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: packed to the brim at lunch time but the service was still really good 1295 lunch buffet excellent food and selection second time here
reviewTitle: Definitely on of the best Indian Buffets in NYC

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: although us indian is a bit different to the uk indians that we are used to dhaba did an excellent job and all dishes were excellent including my vegetarian ghobi keema would visit again

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we visit this restaurant twice in our 5 day visit we really enjoyed the food and the environment the staff was very attentive and the price was good

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: restaurante serve comida indiana muito bem preparada frequentada pelos locais e pelo nativos varias opções no cardápio

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: restaurante indio tipo buffet muy ricotambién se puede comer a la cartacomida diferente todos los días por lo que no te cansas y puedes probar cosas distintas el local es muy agradable y el personal muy atentolos fines de semana siempre lleno relación calidadprecio excelente fuimos dos veces en una semana y en un viaje anterior también

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we made a last minute reservation and had a good meal i had the goa fish spicy but good naan bread delicious service very efficient reasonable too would go back

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: starting with jars of water and buttermilk a unique way of serving the food is very good service i would say a bit lacklustre had a keep standing and waiting for the attendant to come and talk to us alsoonce seated the service was decent the food is very good really hot there was buffet also but we went for the alacartepannerdal all was of good standard

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: opens till late when other indian places are closed great north indian food we were there past midnight and our server was either too tired or drunk orders were mixed up with the next table still no complains as long as the food continued to be as good as it is

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: after reading good reviews and in need for a good indian restaurant we tried dhaba food is average and flat where are the flavour spices service is poor and impolite i do not recommend this place and certainly wont come back

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: great atmosphere be prepared to wait to get a table food is very good although a bit pricey but everythng in new york is that way

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: really liked the food here their mango lassi is really good we order a lot of appetizer my wife like the paapdi chaat stuff a lot must go to this place if you happened to be in nyv
reviewTitle: Must visit if you are in NYC

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the food for the price and location is pretty good tasty even the service however leaves much to be desired it is slow nonattentive and virtually nonexistent after youve ordered it wasnt that great prior to ordering but even worse after the fact its a shame because the food is actually very good the restaurant wasnt even busy so really there was no excuse for the lack of service i would maybe order something to go from here but highly unlikely that i will return for dinner at the restaurant
reviewTitle: I'd give it 4 on food, but the service did them in.

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this is one place where tripadvisor reviews did not help me make the right choice what a waste of time and effort if you know good and genuine indian foodyou will figure out that this is passed off as indian but probably run by bangladeshi chefs the place has a terrible stale smell as soon as you enter food and service underpeforms

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: delicious fabulous dips nice ambiance open to the patio superb bread fresh out of the woodfired oven which just kept coming attentive pleasant service a real find in the neighbourhood

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we met some friends here and picked this restaurant because of its location great if you are on your way uptown it was very good service was good and the food was very good too great bread lovely tomatoeggplant dishes outside seating is available

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: great local restaurant with good food service and wood burning oven its a smaller restaurant so come early or reserve fresh hot bread is served first our favorite mezze is the tomato eggplant dip though all the food is good the mains weve had lamb stuffed cabbage etc are flavorful and good sized but we prefer to order several apps then split a pizza tables are a bit close together and a glass of wine a little pricey however we always come back since food is so good

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: chose bodrum mediterranean for sunday brunch with our children who are at columbia it was a real winner for the guy who will only eat pizzas as well as for the more adventurous eaters in our group the mezze was superb the chicken baharat excellent the lentil soup and poached eggs with garlic yogurt and greens made me feel i was visiting istanbul again the friendly attentive service added to the experience topped by the moderate prices for what was really quality food

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: this place serves mediterranean food with a turkish accent and does a great job of it we started out with three of their appetizer spreads with delicious warm bread and it was just wonderful i had striped bass and the others had beef cheeks and lamb stew served in a clay pot the three of us went through two bottles of excellent red wine ask the owner to recommendations he knows what hes doing the waiter was a lot of fun and the place was buzzing with all sorts of people best meal in nyc on this visit

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: love this local mediterranean spot food is consistently goodbread and olives mezze or shepard salad and consistently good little lamb chops at a great price other meat or fish main courses may be the weakest but the pizzas from the brick oven are first rate go on monday for 12 price bottles of very drinkable wine
reviewTitle: Upper West Side fare and a fair price

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: the turkish sis kebab and the chicken sis kebab were tender and had a great charred flavor the best way to judge is often the veggies and these were outstanding try the turkish coffee it is quite an experience mondays are price wine days which adds value to an already good choice

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: with glasses of turkish wine we began with the appetizer sampler six or so of the menu choices paired with fresh baked bread choosing then two of the favorite appetizers and a lamb and a chicken entree we were delighted with the quality and quantity no need for dessert and a desire to return for another meal sometime soon service attentive

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: we were the family and some friends for dinner the food was fantastic everything we ordered was perfect the musaka and lamb tandir were great i highly recommend this restaurant for everyone the owner is very nice as well
reviewTitle: Excellent Food for an affordable price

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: our appetizers came aftet the entrees except for my wife who didnt get her kebabs for another 15 minutes the food was soso with only some of the food of turkish origin super noisy means no quiet conversations

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: delicious food at an affordable price i will definitely go back dont pass up the fresh warm bread really fantastic service was also very good

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: good turkish mediterranean cuisine in a relaxed setting wood oven and great bread is a definite plus one of our goto places for lunch
reviewTitle: Good food in a relaxed neighborhood venue

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this is 4 and 5th time to this wonderful restaurant i recommend this place and the food that i had with friends two days in a row purani delhi ki papri chat lamb chops chicken kali mirch beware it is hot and goat curry delightfully prepared and very delicious please go and try it out and it is not expensive by ny standards

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i took my son to museum of mathematics and on the way we ran into dhaba he asked to go there so we booked a table near the window for 4pm to avoid lunch craziness and insanety of dinner time we both ordered favoritesfamous dishes both were just ok i ate less than half my son did not like his choice at all weve eaten in at least 2 dozen indian restaraunts and this one in our opinion not higher than a middle not the worst one but way far off from the best either

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we have been to this nyc restaurant twice and enjoyed memorable meals here each dinner choice was so tasty we had a cauliflower appetizer samosas potatoes w green peas chicken tandoori madras curry and veg paneer basmati rice dish exquisite flavors every table was being served and its obvious why make this your nyc indian selection

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the reviews for this place were good so i followed the reviews the place is a bit crowded went for the weekend buffet it was for 13 i was not impressed i like my indian food spicy this was a bit toned down there was some variety though i have seen more

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: good good not too spicy a bit overpriced great hangout for a friends night out the mango lassi was great

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i thought the food was above average in quality and quantity but its certainly overpriced service was poor we got there while they were still open and a lot of the dinner options were not available the staff has gone i think our server may have been tipsy but not sure

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: very good food made right not too spicy i never heard of this place before till now when my friends told me about this place from jersey it is a little bit far but it seems like it worth the trip to ny

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this restaurant is a bit crowded and not very spacious but they make up for all this by the excellent food they serve good cleanlinessthey have a wholesome buffet with a good variety of indian cuisine the lamb biriyani was delicious an excellent chaat counter good and pleasant waiters their prices are reasonable and they serve good tasty authentic indian food would recommend this place

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we really liked the food and the service too food was excellent specially panner kali mirch and lassi

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: nice to have a decent indian curry but the place is very crowded and the food comes fast so not a real dining experience if you want a enjoy the nice indian flavors it worth a visit reasonable prices and good taste
reviewTitle: nice indian food but very crowded

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we went for buffet lunch this restaurant is too congested and limited options in buffet 1 butternaan was not properly cooked 2 only one dessert and that too was very bad i was extremely disappointed and would not recommend anyone to go to this place

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: lots of delicious indian food for a reasonable price great variety every item is tasty fragrant and served at the proper temperature

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: went to this place a week ago for lunch as it was rated one of the best restaurant for indian food but the food here surprised me the expectations with which i went was far way ahead then what i went with amazing delicious etc will visit again n again

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: my husbands favorite is indian this was a good choice for the family although typically i have a problem with overly spicy food we had chicken and lamb birany and it was good considering the crowd service was slow but ok

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we tasted a number of veg and nonveg dishes and all were not too spicy and amazingservice was promptthe dimly lit restaurant creates an inviting ambiencehowever one does experience difficulty when trying to read the menuall meat is halali will visit again
reviewTitle: Indian food that makes you want to eat more!

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: weve been to this little mediterranean place several times in feb mar of 2013 freshlymade hummus served with a warm bread is a great starter the medium sized wood burning stove pizza is deliciousa thin crust with topoftheline ingredients from italy and surrounding countries the chicken or salmon is a great choice for lunchcooked with precision so it is moist flavorful the salads are generous sizedtry the greek with feta we love the wide range of moderately priced wines enjoy 12 price bottles on wine mondays
reviewTitle: Great food & service in a lovely, small space

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: bodrum is a great little restaurant many interesting menu choices the appetizers and main courses that my wife and i enjoyed at our recent visit were great this restaurant is not very expensive and provides very good value also i must eat gluten free and they have many selections that met my needs the only negative is that this restaurant is small and the tables are very close together so you do have to contend with other peoples conversations not a place a romantic dinner but a definitely a very good choice for a good meal and interesting food

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: i went with my wife and two friends they had been several times for us it was a first the first courses the four of us shared five were more than satisfactory the entrees we had branzino in a bed of fennel were excellent the dessert rice pudding was very tasty no complaints about the service however unless one had mastered sign language andor lip reading it was virtually impossible to hear anyone else at the table and we had been placed in what we were told was the quietest corner of the restaurant
reviewTitle: Excellent food, fine service but obnoxiously noisy!

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: eclectic menu with excellent moussaka a dish i had given up on years ago because it was so mediocre at restaurants we have visited at bodrum it was a down to earth feastbthe lamb dishes are terrific pizza delicious a great discovery

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: this would be a definitely thumbsup if a little less pricey as it is it would be more appropriate as a fancy place which it is not anyway food here is nice i went there with two friend and we all ordered differente dishes all were good and plentiful the small sampler appetizer plate did not taste as good as i had in turkey should it but was fair enough all in all i would recommend it to anyone living nearby and looking for a convenient option
reviewTitle: Nice turkish food, a bit pricey

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: nice service good selection of mediterranean items and good turkish wine kind of pricey but an interesting change from the usual italian fare upper west side is is great family location

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: mixed appy platter best deal in town and absolutely delicious another appetizereggplant with carmelized onions ate every crumb lamb shank dinner beautifully seasoned waitstaff is super attentive i would go back and just order lots of appetizers didnt have pizza but it look wonderful really nice neighborhood restaurant with gentle prices

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: wonderful lamb tagine grilled clams prosciutto and arugula brickoven pizza and the best ricepudding this side of town
reviewTitle: Wonderful lamb tagine, grilled clams, prosciutto and arugula brick-oven pizza and the best rice-pudding this side of...

placeAddress: 584 Amsterdam Ave between 88th & 89th St, New York City, NY 10024
reviewText: yummmm

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: wonderful indian cuisine we enjoyed the sunday buffet a variety of options and all were delicious my only complaint s that it is very small and the tables are very close to one another but cant beat the food

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: when in the mood for some nice spicy food and authentic indian flavours dhaba will do the trick being indian myself i can say that this place is above average nice atmosphere and clean restaurant as well reservation required as it can be packed at times

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this was the best indian food ive ever had and the service was excellent the restaurant is small so reservations are needed

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: abbiamo scelto questo ristorante con alcuni colleghi dopo aver sentito qualche amico che vive a ny il locale molto affollato ma il servizio è veloce e la qualità buona consiglio la prenotazione

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: glad we had reserved a table as the queue was all the way out the door on friday night small cost noisy place quite dark and very lively the food was truly delicious very authentic flavours and also a british curry section which was a real treat for expats in the us
reviewTitle: Delicious. Worth booking at the weekend!

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we were told that the chef grinds the spices daily and boy howdy does it show we had chicken lamb and the paneer and all were excellent with exciting spicy flavors could this be my new favorite manhattan indian joint i think so

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we were referred to dhaba by a work colleague tried it loved it we are definitely going back the food was very good freshly prepared hot spicy delicious and the price was right
reviewTitle: Our new favorite spot for Indian

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: our family ate here on the wednesday night before thanksgiving it was a good sign that every table was full when we arrived even so we were seated within 20 minutes all the dishes were very good we ordered 3 different chicken dishes 1 lamb dish plus rice and bread for the table the stout i was drinking was a perfect accompaniment to the lamb the noise level was energetic but not too loud to be able to hear the others in your party we definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for indian cuisine in the area

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i dont remember another time ive been so full and thats a good thing i seriously loved this restaurant we went there and ordered a variety of things just to try the flavors it hit the spot multiple times over it is a little dim in the restaurant but that really adds to the ambiance and spirit of the place the service is above par and the food is worth every penny i highly recommend a visit to this restaurant just make sure you have time to walk it off afterwards

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the restaurant is good i visited in 2012 i was impressed with the food nothing great with taste but then i remembered i was out of india and given the choice i think it was a good one i wish the restaurant was brightly lit the reason i remember this restaurant was that i was one of the last diners late in the evening and the guys helped me out with a taxi the hotel could have been brightly lit its a bit dark but its good

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: food is excellent staff is great and prices are very reasonable went with a customer who travels to india often and a business partner who is from pakistan both rated the food excellent

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: nothing special the food is decent but none of the dishes stood out for me the service was slow for a weekday

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i ate at dhabas with 3 friends our food was excellent but plates were large and we should probably only have ordered 3 dishes instead of 4 the restaurant had a stylish decor but was a bit noisy still i think its the best indian restaurant in the neighborhood and i would definitly eat there again

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i have been to a lot of indian places in nyc and this place has got it right their kali mirch chicken and paneer is something i order every time and is always amazing the seating area could be a little tight on busy nights but the food would not disappoint you try it

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: after you get over the initial feeling of being completely disorientated as the noise really hits you as you walk through the door you soon settle in to your comfortable seat and are treated to great service and one of the best indian meals youll ever have seriously perfect portion sizes great quality food and the favours wow your taste buds are in for a real treat

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the best indian restaurant i have ever been to outside india a bit overcrowded the service is pretty good

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we got in just in time the food was good although the extra spicy curry was just to hot to actually taste anything the service was good but got a little slow once every spot in the restaurant was filled overall a good place with tasty food

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: enjoyed the food very much and would go there again not so much for the ambiance though as it was very loud and seating was very tight service was very good and their recommendations were appreciated

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i just planned to visit indian restaurant in lexington ave upon the reviews on dhaba i decided to hav lunch over there lunch buffet was awesome chicken tikka masala tasted good the creamy sauce used was nice naan was best i ever had n the shrimp curry is a spicy home style dish service was good and attentive this was sure a hang out place i will plan to visit this restaurant again with my friends

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the restaurant was packed and ergo kinda loud hard to carry on a conversation at times also in late january every time the door was opened it was freezing on the other hand its the best indian food ive had in a long time perhaps ever go in spring and either early or late and youll be fine
reviewTitle: Great food, but loud and cold

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the food nice and they have a long confusing menu but over its nice but i dont know why the long lineit wasnt worth the wait
reviewTitle: wonder whats the crowd here for

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: nice place good food good tunes playing and not too loud like some reviews said we were early evening 6pm and was busy the kids were made welcome not bad price for nyc
reviewTitle: Cool atmosphere, good food. Nearly as good as a UK curry, and that's saying something!

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: my husband and i enjoyed this one of many fine indian restaurants in the flatirongramercy park neighborhoods it was some of the best naan and saag paneer ive ever had take your friends

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: went here with my wife during a brief visit to nyc for a concert at madison square gardenwe arrivedin the restaurant to be presented with a buffet lunch menu at the cost of 1095the food on offer was classic indian cuisine of a high standard the service was lightning quick and it was very busywould return here tomorrow no complaints from either of us

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the food was very interesting and tasty most things were not that spicy and the naan was wonderfully fluffy the decor is not very indian like its a bit clubby which is ok but the music was a little much pretty good though the lemon soda was good
reviewTitle: Tasty curry - great naan - a bit too much club atmosphere perhaps

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this is a nice restaurant with good srrvice and food the problem is that it is dqrk and very noisy dont plan on a romantic dinner or one thwt you can easily converse in the food is good but spicy

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: although we had a couple of recommendations for good indian restaurants in this area the dhaba was the busiest by far the food was excellently spiced and delicious service was speedy attentive and efficient the meal was excellent value for money delivered in a stylish and atmospheric setting we would definitely return

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the food was of high quality and was fresh the main dishes were spicy so you may want to ask that the heat level be toned down be aware that the place is busy and noisy the atmosphere is festive but its difficult to hold a conversation

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: they had 9 selections on the table including a shrimp dish they bring out fresh naan bread after you sit down they also serve tandoori directly from the kitchen so the chicken is moist rather than being dried out on the buffet table i tried 6 of the dishes all quite tasty however they only have rice pudding for dessert some better restaurants have 23 choices for dessert

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: delicious authentic northern indian cuisine at a good price how can you not like this place originally introduced to it by an indian friend who vouches for its authenticity we now go back regularly the only criticism i would make and its a small one it that it can become quite crowded and noisy

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: nott recommend anbody to go there as food was not as per the standard and it was cold and customer service was bad more over bit expensive

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: loved the chicken tikka masala garlic nan my friend had the lamb korma and a rose lassi enjoyed my mango lassi highly recommend

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we saw this place and picked it for dinner as we wanted indian and it was getting more traffic than any other similar place around the place was full with mostly young people the atmosphere is lively service was very good and we really enjoyed the food i would try to avoid a table in the middle of the dining room to avoid being in the hustle bustle we would go back
reviewTitle: Busy, busy place with very nice food

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: recommended by a friend this place offer excellent value we ate there for lunch and found the food to be very good there were 2 choices of ordering a la carte or buffet style menu the buffet at 12head is hard to beat with at least 8 menu choices including a number of vegetarian options

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: the s indian fare is authentic and delicious here even the lassi mango stands for itself miles ahead of junoon in sincerity and honest simple indian cuisine dont expect any floral or frilly atmosphere
reviewTitle: Solid food amid tired Bollywood background.

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: small and a bit noisy restaurant but it was not a problem because the food was excellent

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: place was quite small but we managed to have table for two in saturday night without reservation food was excellent and very authentic

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: ive been to india many times and eat the food often in the states we sampled a variety of dishes including raita papad chicken butter masala dal tadka and chicken dahiwala everything tasted fresh and well seasoned and the ingredients seemed top notch our waiter was attentive and the staff was on the spot with water refills plate clearing etc id definitely go back

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we went there based on the many positive reviews but sadly the food is simply not very good very bland lacking in spice as authentic as you could get from a trader joes frozen indian dish i used to live in india so i have a decent read on quality this isnt it very disappointing

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: wonderful place to eat enjoy indian music and a perfect atmosphere

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this restaurant is extremely popular so if your heart is set on eating here a reservation is required otherwise you will have to wait for an indeterminate time for your table the tables are cramped together and we have experienced all varieties of service here from great to awful however this restaurant is a good option for vegans dining with carnivores they have excellent vegan options especially the aloo jeera i have always been very happy with the food here its good fresh and tasty but the service is hitmiss
reviewTitle: Great Food, mixed service, reservations required

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: a terrific new place in curry hill we had a vegan appetizer of cauliflower and peas with many spices a chicken tandoori that was ambrosial and an excellent lamb jalfrazie we also had a couple orders of the excellent masala tea a spiced indian beverage with milkand finished up with soupy but very tasty rice pudding have the onion chili naan it is described as hot but is merely spicy and very tasty a great meal but service is odd

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: un locale piacevolmente colorato nel cuore del quartiere indiano su lexington ave e 27th street ma affollato e rumoroso difficile chiacchierare con toni normali e difficile anche leggere il menu che e ricchissimo ma scritto in caratteri talmente piccoli da rimanere misterioso nella luce volutamente bassissima dellambiente il cibo e buono anche se a volte troppo piccante i camerieri gentili ma lo spazio e stretto e alla fine lesperienza complessiva non e da ripetere a meno di andarci per pranzo con la luce del giorno e il locale non pieno forse allora lattenzione potra essere solo sui piatti

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i went with friends and had the pav bhaji and it was a bit greasy the ambience is nice and the service is good i went again and ordered rotis and indian vegetarian dishes and again the vegetarian dishes were floating in oil
reviewTitle: Good Food, North Indian, a little greasy.

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: during a week in nyc we went here twice amazing food nice servers basically amazing but on our last day a guy who sat besides waited for his food for a loooooong time he was upset and asked whats where going on the server did know what to do and instead of checking just ignored the guy the made a scene lateron nevertheless we were very satisfied
reviewTitle: Very good! But everyone makes mistakes...

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i would recommend this restaurant to travellers who are keen on having good food i have now been there many times and have not been disappointed do try the purani delhi ki papri chaat also i would recommend the chicken kali mirch it is not a place where you would go for a romantic or business meal enjoy

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: not heavy like the other indian joints felt like home cooked food

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: goan fish is my favorite but my kids like chicken makkhani make reservations or be prepared to wait i only wish there was a place to wait other then outside the restaurant like a bar

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: this restaurant was absolutely awesome i have never been to an indian restaurant where the food the ambiance and the service were spectacular i ordered the chicken curry which is definitely something to try it is very good my two sons ordered a mango lassi and also enjoyed that very much too i recommend this to anyone who wishes to eat here it is a great places for couples and families alike
reviewTitle: One of the best Indian restaurants I've ever been to!

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: we went for lunch and the service was great the food was excellent and we werent disappointed loved the indian techno music unique decor great choices on the buffet an appetizer was included and they even brought just cooked dishes to our table well be back next time were in new york

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927
reviewText: i have gone to many indian restaurants in my life in various western cities but have not found such authentic food at such reasonable prices you must try the purani dili papri chaat it is truly authentic as it should be crispy not too much tamarind or yoghurt and with just the right amount of spices it is very busy so you must book
reviewTitle: The best for good food at reasonable price

placeAddress: 108 Lexington Ave, New York City, NY 10016-8927

reviewText: one of our go to places is cafeteria in nycs chelsea area the mac and cheese sets the bar for all other places if you sit at the bar be sure to ask for karl his great service and friendly personality make for an excellent experience
