reviewText: this place holds the bar for the best mac and cheese in nyc the chicken pillard is fresh and amazing if you sit at the bar ask for karl amazing bartender and superb service we live in the neighborhood and this is our go to restaurant on the weekends

reviewText: the burger was crazy expensive and not even grass fed over 300 4 for bacon on the burger seems a little steep even for new york i had the french toast which was good but the fruit was a little mushy service was good and they dont rush you which is very nice would i go back probably not fyi the steps to the bathroom are incredibly steep and the bathroom is very dark

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: food and service was great a really nice and lively atmosphere so not sure i understand some reviews lots of energy in the place we were not given the best table but were moved when we asked the meat loaf is delicious

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i cannot say enough about our server nick r was fantastic the food was amazing i had the meatballs and mac n cheese spring rolls i did have to use my flashlight on my phone to read the menu because the atmosphere is darker but i love my experience at cafeteria

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: great for any night out the food was delicious and the service was impeccable ambience was super cool and very upbeat joe the manager was topnotch as well as justin our server we were a large group and they met our every need with a smile and ease making everything look effortless one of the best restaurants highly recommend
reviewTitle: A yes for me!!! Excellent choice!

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: my daughter brought me for dinner and it was delightful our server nick was so personable warm and funny the food was excellent and different but it was nick who made our night

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i used to go to this place all the time before covid happened and let me tell you was a place to be now god no its just boring with no energy basically mediocre at best and on top of it they add 20 gratuity on your check for not reason table of 4 now i understand why at 10 pm on friday was empty never again

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: amazing place i havent been here in a long while and so glad it is still around the ambiance was upbeat and friendly the energy was great and appropriate for catching up with friends without yelling across the table the food was as i remembered great presentation not overly salty and perfect portions i happen to be there on a friday when the local dj lina was spinning the tunes will return again soon

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: friends reunion at 7 pm on a thursday night full but not overly crowded the open walls really bring in the feel of being outside we were greeted by a gracious hostess our wait person nick was pleasant friendly funny af and generally made our evening more special he even took photos for us and jumped in one himself we absolutely loved the food and highly recommend the poached peaches if theyre on the specials menu again would definitely come back with family to enjoy
reviewTitle: So glad we found this place!

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: met friend for dinner here and was not disappointed its a busy and energetic place with lots of energy friendly and unobtrusive service staff provided the right amount of attention throughout our meal pork chops were perfectly cooked and full of flavor definitely will be back

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the cafeteria is a fun combo of american family style cafe and also a great place to meet friends really good menu esp love the brunch options they have many healthy choices but also delicious waffles and fun foods too cute bar even the restrooms are fun had multiple different meals here this week and loved each one best ginger shot in town miguel was our server and helped with a special needs guest who was with us excellent place dont miss it
reviewTitle: Visited 3 times in one week. Reliably excellent every time.

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: not only was the atmosphere and food incredible but our server was phenomenal i highly recommend this establishment and hope you ask for anjail to be your server shes so passionate about food and sharing the experience with you that she will go an
reviewTitle: AMAZING.  Anjail was the BEST Server I’ve had in all of NYC the past week. She was so  knowledgeable about  entire menu

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: great food and shawn is a great server so much fun the menu is diverse and well presented the food is aesthetic and very well executed from starters through dessert fun crowd but not overly noisy

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we went to cafeteria a bit by chance it does have a look of a nice cafeteria but it is a real restaurant the menu is very classical we enjoyed particularly the artichokes and one of us had the pork chop which is amazing we paid 70 pp incl tax but not tip with half bottle of wine each we felt that it was very reasonable by nyc standards
reviewTitle: Excellent food - the best pork chop  ever - reasonable prices

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: after being let down by other places i had researched online where to get great mac cheese in new york cafeteria was one of the recommendations and rightfully so my husband and i both ordered the cheddar fontina version it tasted lovely as did the garlic whipped potato side dish the ice cream was also very good service was friendly and efficient from all staff we encountered and the restaurant had a positive vibe which made us feel relaxed this was one of our best mealout memories from our honeymoon

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: havent visited this place so cant comment on other foods or service but just wanted to give them a positive review as a group of volunteers was fed their pizza and although sometimes i find it difficult to get a decent regular slice non specialty i found their pizza to be quite good and would recommend

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: the place is decent for any occasion and the food is good it just became my choice for a quick bite i prefer the grandma pie but all there food is good

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: the food is excellent the specialty slices remain huge and are really a meal the slices with chicken or calimari have an amazing amount of chickencalimari and the specials that i previously wrote about remain very special my only added suggestion is to add 250 to the 6 special and add pasta and an amazing marinara sauce to your order still a great value were always happy to stop here for lunch or dinner
reviewTitle: Yet another year gone by, and La Piazza is still outstanding!

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: a day out with friends and their children usually ends with a trip to their favorite pizzaria restaurant our children love the food so we come back often staff is helpful and curious food is delicious

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: this restaurant makes the best calamari over pasta of any place i have ever been to the pizza is also delicious it is clean and friendly the perfect local neighborhood pizzeria and restaurant

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: big selection of slices rolls etc i dont know where bridgette g who wrote the terrible review went but its not this place the staff are super helpful and friendly and have been for the almost 5 years ive been coming here and the large pies are bigger than deninos and other places around love their crust

placeAddress: 1445 Richmond Ave Ste H, Staten Island, NY 10314-1563
reviewText: they are all very nice always they have a pizza that is out of this world and calzones too the best are the lunch specials more than 30 dishes all prepared with very fresh ingredients and at 6 each it cant be beat and for 2 more they ad pasta with marinara sauce incredible prices for this kind of quality delicious food all served with fresh made bread and for 1 you should order the plate of 5 garlic knots the best i ever had
reviewTitle: Excellent prepared dishes and the best attention to customers

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: einfach unglaublich unverschämt vom hotel erhält man voucher für das frühstück der angeschlossenen bäckerei die 10 wert sind haben wir ja bezahlt man wird hier als tourist dermassen unverschämt abgezockt und verarscht mir fehlen die worte man erhält für den voucher ein getränk und ein teilchen holt man nur einen kaffee bekommt man mal geld zurück und mal nicht möchte man dann cash bezahlen oder noch ein teilchen dann geht es auf einmal nicht mehr ich sollte mit meinem voucher einen cappucino für 10 bezahlen da ist uns der faden gerissen dermassen unverschämt

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459

reviewTitle: What lovely to start my morning.

reviewText: when you want a quick bite delicious dessert or fine bread this is ideal i ordered a slice a quiché lorraine today with a bottle of perrier and a brioche bread just perfect

reviewText: the macaroons were excellent i dont recommend the eclairs they are good but not the best and for the price i dont think it is worth it the coffee was really good its a small place and you have to find a way to sit if you want to stay there otherwise it is a grab and go i liked the food enough to recommend it to friends

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: someone has mentioned this place to me it was definitely worth the 45 minute walk from our hotel excellent coffee amazing pastries a super friendly lady at the counter a great way to start our short trip to new york cherry danish is as delicious as it is beautiful

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my almondchocolate croissant was the real thing i miss the french patisseries so much but here it is in greenwich village bonus there was a pastrymaking class going on at the same time we came in envy

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: this wonderful place opened right down the block from where i lived initally all the cooking and backin was done on the premises now since they have expanded to supply other shops and restaurants it serves as a stopping off place to get wonderful pastry and coissants
reviewTitle: I know this place from the day it opened and it is a gem

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: après une petite balade à washington square nous y avons dégusté un excellent brownie accompagné dune très bonne tasse de café sur une petite terrasse

reviewText: this is my third time going to mille feuille for a class after the first macaron baking class i knew id be back i attended the croissant baking class as well and it was even better the chefs are so kind and patient the place is small but its nice the perfect place size for a laid back baking class its perfect for everyone in the family

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: a great class fun but also informative vincent was an excellent teacher and we walked away not just with lots of delicious macarons but also the confidence to try them again at home

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: if you want authentic pastries this is the place you will not be disappointed i truly thought they flew in the pastries from paris which is a great complement
reviewTitle: EXCELLENT!!! The best I have been to in NYC

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: what a fun experience to learn to bake french macaroons in a sweet little bakery in the village the cookies came out perfect with a bit of help from the teacher thoroughly enjoyed the experience

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my sister and i brought my mother for mothers day and we had such a wonderful experience vincent was great and very helpful this is wonderful activity for a small group and even individually cant wait to go back for croissants

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my mom and i took the croissant making class on sunday the instructor a young french guy cant remember his name was sweet and took his time showing us all the steps such fun and we took home nearly 50 croissants plus dough to make more its not a cheap class but well worth it highly recommend

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: it was a wonderful experience the baking class was a great learning experience and helped me polish some of my previous skillsknowledge the chef was amazing and would love to take another class with him

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my son and i thoroughly enjoyed learning how to make macarons at this cute french bakery highly recommend the class to learn proper technique for making delicious macarons

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i dont know what there was about it but i had the most perfect english muffin ever at cafeteria i also loved my omelet with gruyere and avocado along with my english breakfast tea i know this is a very popular place for lunch and dinner and it was nice to be able to enjoy it at a slower time for a weekday breakfast it was nice to be able to sit inside in the air conditioning on a hot morning and still experience the open exposure to the street which was also good from a covid perspective

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: entrés par hasard poussés par une averse nous avons trouvé un restaurant plutôt branché tout en restant cool les serveurs avec de jolies bretelles sont charmants le bruit ne nous a pas dérangé ça fait partie de new york la carte nest pas très longue plutôt positif et les plats choisis étaient très bons seul bémol sur le prix 4 cocktails dont 2 sans alcool 2 burgers et un steak 180

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: big thanks to joel who greeted us warmly at the door of this hip very busy restaurant on a rainy friday night on mothers day weekend not being hip and worse yet having no reservation we would have understood had he said no dice instead he asked if we wanted to wait at the bar for a bit less than ten minutes and we were seated at a great table we had calamari and salmon and both were excellent the artichokes were the star service was efficient friendly and quick would return

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we stopped for breakfast the menu had lots of interesting options food was great and we had wonderful service they have outdoor seating but the entire restaurant was open to the outdoors i would recommend this place

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: had lunch here the other day salmon tartare and the meatloaf both excellent and in sufficiency to go home with a doggy bag my only complaint is finding a recipe for the meatloaf that is terribly written and from the nytimes cooking app of all places the topping is what makes this meatloaf special and i dont think youre supposed to add it to the meats id go again after saving up some bucks first

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: saw the recommendations online and after seeing the menu we knew we had to visit made booking for last night and it didnt disappoint amazing service and the food was spectacular definitely recommend the mac and cheese spring rolls

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: enjoyed a delicious dinner with friends celebrating a birthday the menu is full of comfort food done right had the meatloaf and mac and cheese and i expected my grandmother to come strolling out of the kitchen after we were finished liked it so much that we went back for breakfast

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: be prepared this restaurant requires you to provide proof of your covid19 vaccine for both indoor and outdoor dining food was just okay nothing special service was mediocre but gave us time to enjoy the outdoor patio which was comfortable and well maintained

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: obligatorio brutal el espectáculo después de tomar unas copas por chelsea o por hells todo un circo que hay que disfrutar un regalo para la vista

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: found this lovely always open place totally by accident great interior very good music selection and big portions of delicious food not too mention excellent front of the house customer service highly recommended for both meeting with friends as well as having an excellent meal or drinks

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: went with my one year old granddaughter and three other adults for a sunday breakfast seating was fast and comfortable all food came promptly and as ordered i shared the silver dollar pancakes with the one year old and she gave me a thumbs up food was good service was great

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ive tried this place for a second chance and again they surprised because of food quality regularity despite a little bit noise place mac and cheese options are a must

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: waited in the line for 45 minutes and they didnt even let us in because we are not somebody thats the most unprofessional manner i have ever experienced

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we had the mac and cheese burrata and mussels all very reasonable for mains the crabcakes where good and the tuna was ok the pricing is fairly high over 70 per person

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we took a family vacation to nyc and this restaurant did not disappoint a friend from jersey recommended it the atmosphere is clean white and modern our waiter was very helpful in recommending something my daughter may like as she had trouble deciding my husband said its the best shrimp and grits hes ever had two thumbs up from us

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this old familiar spot is still reliable and the food is good as ever the al fresco seating is best in the warmer new york weather and yesterday was an especially kind day service was good and our food came quickly the drinks were goidtoo though my table mates inferno bloody mary was just that nearly too hot to enjoy

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: its a cute trendy place food is pretty good service is always horrible they are friendly but inefficient been this way as long as i have been coming which is 5 years never improves too bad

we stopped here on the way home from brooklyn and it was the perfect place to stop it was poppin there were a decent amount of people great vibes staff music the food was very delicious and at a great fair price and it is halal i came in craving a bacon egg cheese but my mind immediately changed when i saw tried the worlds best pastrami sandwich delicious definitely worth trying out
reviewTitle: Great Food, Great Vibes, Great Prices!

reviewText: clean modern simple cafe atmosphere good food and its always served with a side of greens which is refreshing for this area im looking forward to trying some of their smoothies and dining outside as the weather warms up my only complaint is that its a bit pricey

i have been to cafe juliet a few times now and ive enjoyed it every time ive tried many of their menu items and everything so far has been delicious their fig and apple grilled cheese is amazing i also love their pancakes and avocado and harris toast so so good their selection of lattes are really good as well rose petal latte is my favorite i highly recommend this place will definitely keep going back

stopped in here for a bite with a friend its located in a strip mall so it could be difficult to park on occasion light and airy interior friendly and helpful staff you order and pick up your items from the counter my friend and i enjoyed a breakfast plate and an avocado and burrata toast i really liked that the egg plate came with a side salad along with potatoes and sourdough toast they had some delightful items on the menu would recommend stopping in here i look forward to returning and trying their cardamon pancakes

atmosphere was quiet and pleasant and the food was a treat excellent guacamole and choice salads good fresh food at very good prices a pleasant change from the inflated prices you sometimes find in the neighborhood
we stopped here two days in a row the food was very good and the staff was very friendly they even remembered us from the day before very cozy atmosphere will be coming back
reviewTitle: Very good food and great atmosphere

reviewText: our meal started with chips and guacamole the guacamole was outstanding but the chips were thin and small and couldnt hold the guacamole the rest of the meal was outstanding my turkey burger was very tasty my wife said it was one of the best pieces of salmon she has tasted the staff had no problem preparing our meals with specific request they also have a wide variety of fruit juices make sure you bring cash they dont take credit cards
pas facile à trouver mais vaut le déplacement dans un cadre agréable un service de qualité et des plats excellents

íbamos de camino para el downtown de brooklyn y encontramos este sitio que parecía muy agradable ordenamos la sopita del día un tartare de atún un wrap y sándwich las porciones generosas y con un sabor exquisito lo único que pudo haber sido mejor fue el tartare pues el atún no estaba tan fresco como esperaba y desmejoró en algo su sabor todo lo demás estuvo genial si no hablas inglés y eres hispanohablante no es problema el personal habla español perfectamente

con luz tenue y un decorado simple esto es auténtico brooklyn comida excelente a precios razonables no com manha la tilapia es increíble y la hamburguesa es deliciosa se siente la calidad de los ingredientes y el cariño en su preparación este lugar tendrá siempre un lugar especial para nosotros
dropped in for a quick breakfast food was good and gluten free options as well coffee was good service very good
reviewTitle: Quick Breakfast.... Decent food and value

reviewText: venus en famille pour prendre un brunch nous avons été déçus par la qualité des plats proposés mis à part les jus de fruits frais qui sont bons les assiettes sont assez moyennes selon nous
reviewTitle: endroit plutôt sympathique mais brunch moyen

reviewText: it was a good stop on our way to a concert at the barclay center for a concert a nice cozy place with wraps salads burgers apps etc we had the buffalo chicken cubes to start which were good maybe a tiny bit overcooked but good the sandwiches were good as well as the mashed and baked potatoes its a healthy place so there are glutenfree and vegan options the service was terrific

down the street 5th ave from the barclay center are several blocks which contain small restaurants pure was the only one i saw with breakfast all day a very neat modern serving area and very good service was an added benefit so at 630 pm i was able to order a very good reasonably price omelet and very good coffee toast and a few greens came with the omelet my spouse ordered a chick wrap which was also well prepared free water served in a jar was also a nice touch would return
we just walked in and had the best burgers of our stay in nyc lovely staff and nice atmosphere straight 1010 big big up
people were nice and helpful food tasty not expensive went back 2d time it was that pleasant they feature wraps and salads we enjoyed both dinner and lunch there
we waited a very very long time for our food but we understood because there were a lot of people trying to eat once we got our food we were all pleasantly surprised at how delicious it was

ótima comida atendimento simpático e ambiente agradável fomos ao pure bistrô por acaso é a satisfação nao poderia ser maior além de ótimos pratos o cheese cake e dos melhores que já comi mesmo sem cobertura
this is one of my favorite places to eat in brooklyn the menu is great and inexpensive the food is relatively healthy and the staff is attentive and kind

we went on a sunday night and it was pretty dead but we still enjoyed excellent ipas no sleep til brooklyn flatbread gotta love a beastie boys reference and the best meatballs ive ever had the bar itself is a gorgeous artistic wooden masterpiece
reviewTitle: Went for the beer, stayed for the meatballs!

reviewText: the room has a high ceiling and comfortable seating in addition to beer they offer an interesting assortment of cocktails the pizzas are also creative everything was very good and the shishito peppers alone are why we will return the service is attentive our only complaint is that we asked for the peppers to come out as an appetizer before the pizza but they were served at the same time
reviewTitle: Rounded up to 5 because the Shishito Peppers were so good!

reviewText: been to this diner about 100 times lol a delicious breakfast spot standard menu plenty of parking lunch and or dinner cant go wrong with a burger or wrap either

we had a great meal with 12 people the service was fantastic and all 12 meals were served at the same time so we could all begin eating together the food was great very large portions and there were no errors with the order i wish that i could have the same dining experience when i go out to more expensive restaurants

i will never order from this diner again i order at least once a week and 80 of the time the order is wrong i call and the owner is never there i speak to the manager who tells me he will make up for it next order and it never happens i am really tired of paying for food and i dont receive it this is the last time they will be receiving my money good bye

dont let the label diner fool you this is a bona fide restaurant with nice decor comfortable seating and good food we have found it is easier to get accommodations for dietary limitations at nonchain restaurants and they were great about my sons limitations very nice breakfast would go again in a heartbeat
had lunch here with the hubby clean diner with friendly staff good food large portions you will not be disappointed
waitress did not come around food was overpriced and tasted just okayno refills poor customer service and didnt bring check

do not order any food from this place i know someone who use to wait tables here and from what i heard the kitchen is not kept clean at all they leave food out at room temperature and some of the cooks dont wash thier hands i was also told that certain workers including a couple of the managers would even eat food sometimes customers behind the back of the kitchen or in the bathroom just so they wouldnt get caught i cannot believe that they have not been shut down yet

o local fica numa região não tão conhecida em ny staten island porém a comida segue o padrão de hambúrguer gigante americano gostoso bom atendimento um pouco cheio nos horários de pico recomendo e volto
mikes unicorn diner has very good food is clean their egg omelettes are really quite good staff is very polite also staff is very polite
reviewTitle: Mike's Unicorn Diner has very good food & is clean

reviewText: the food here is excellent and so is the service always love to pay a visit here when visiting staten island

μας πήγαν φίλοι που γνώριζαν το μαγαζί ποσο τυχεροί είμαστε που βρεθήκαμε εκεί τέλειο πρωινό αυγά τηγανητά πατάτες τοπική σπεσιαλιτέ και επιτέλους the best nes cafe frappe φιλικό σερβις πλούσιες μερίδες ωραίο american style περιβάλλον μακάρι να ξαναπηγαίναμε

my cousin recommended this diner for lunch it has a large parking lot we were seated immediatelyeven though the diner was crowded our server gave us excellent attention the food was awesome tasty and large portions

the menu was quite extensive in terms of food and beverages the serving sizes were very generous most importantly the food was delicious our server was so nice and helpful fantastic breakfast experience and everything this country girl thought a diner in new york would be like
reviewTitle: Typical NY Diner in a good way

reviewText: it was breakfast nothing special nothing fancy in short they delivered what we ordered service was just a little slow but not bad worth it for a diner breakfast

when we got there we had a 30 minute wait we were seated all the way in the back in a nice private little table it was perfect our food was very good and the staff was great i also liked that they have a parking lot

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: excellent service food was prepared as ordered and the atmosphere was relaxing good italian dinner two nights in a row

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: first time to staten island and chose to stay at the hilton garden inn for convenience when checking in noticed lorenzos and decided to have dinner her we started with the maryland crab cakes and they were actually really good did not expect this to be so good and included two great sauces my colleague ordered the veal chop which he enjoyed and i had the short rib the short rib was perfect along with the carrots and polenta wish polenta was softer and the sauce was excellent was quite surprised at the entire meal great place

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: evening out with other adult family members great food pork chop with gnocchi talented piano player attentive service the small bar would be great for a pre dinner cocktail but unfortunately for our visit a group of boisterous beer drinking guys were a little too loud for us the bar scene later in the evening was great good people watching too dog friendly hotel so be prepared to see the pooches

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: my wife and i came here for brunch the day after her birthday excellent polite service beautiful serve yourself appetizer bar our entrees my wife had crab eggs benedict i had chicken and waffles with a peach and blueberry infused maple syrup both were delicious next time we return to staten island well visit again

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314

reviewText: my husband and i as well as my best friend and her husband have made it a tradition to go to lorenzos every valentines day or weekend of valentines day there is a prefix dinner with three courses and a piano player in the background the price is reasonable about 55 not including drinks and gratuity

reviewText: beautiful restaurant friendly and attentive staff the only thing i would complain about would be that the buffet was in the bar area it really was not a huge deal but i felt that it should have been somewhere in the same room we were seated it was no big deal their was a tremendous selection of breakfast items two carving stations eggscrepes and pasta made to order a full dessert table with chocolate fountain the two hour seating was more than enough time for our group i would recommend lorenzos for brunch

a very friendly neighborhood restaurant with fresh foods that are well prepared i love the greek wrap with grilled chicken comes with a side salad they deliver and are always nice
this is a great place for lunch i had the hawaiian salmon burger and it was sooooo good they deliver too

very fresh ingredients cooked well to bring out the flavour of the fish salad is very tasty and certainly big enough love their emphasis on healthy foods a thoroughly enjoyable lunch attentive service
pure bistro is a nice little neighbourhood restaurant the burgers are terrific friendly service family oriented a little noisy

reviewText: the gluten free menu is almost 100 served with fries from a nondedicated fryer therefore this really isnt a gf menu that anyone can count on bummer because the fries smelled delicious i highly suggest that bxl just make their fryer dedicated to fries since they come with absolutely everything and skip the one or two other menu items that ruin it all with crosscontamination

reviewText: a cool belgian bar and restaurant with great draft belgian beer food tried both the carbonade flamande beef stew and the stoemp chipolata sausage plate both were very good would have been nice to have some greens on the plates beer fantastic draft belgian beer the cuvée bxl is a nice amber ale the chimay cinq cents is excellent and the st bernadus abt 12 on draft is liquid perfection too bad no chimay blue label on draft service decent service nice folks ambiance small european pub overall cleanliness average bathroom cleanliness below average

reviewText: great selection of beers however i thought the food even the carbonade and the mussels was a weak imitation of real belgian cuisine very noisy in the bar area toward the front but its somewhat quieter toward the rear

reviewText: it has been a while since my last visit to this institution all is how i remember amazing food great service but it is loud definitely not ideal to have a conversation

reviewText: è il posto dove carrie bradshaw protagonista di sex and the city con le sue amiche storiche andava a mangiare per colazione cena e pranzo spesso posto molto carino personale giovane e friendly
