yuuuge menu we ate here for breakfast but the other meals coming out looked greattoogenerous quantities piled on large plates breakfast was fine and reasonably priced one of our party didnt care for the homefries thought they werent crisp enough but i thought they were good good for large groups and families
good size portions would highly recommend the eggs benedikt as it was delicious they have a huge menu which is very reasonably priced as a londoner i found the food portions very generous indeed

the menu is a small novel with so many selections and variety from sandwiches to surf and turf every table gets a slaw and chickpea starter complimentary service is exceptional food was okay i can see how breakfast would be stellar but dinner was okay filets mignon was ok the portions are mammoth but as mentioned taste is ok

we have been here before and are completely satisfied with the food sometimes the service is lacking but today it was spot on i had the reuben very lean corned beef my motherinlaw ordered the fried fish this is not the first time shes had it she is always happy with this sandwich my husband had the italian chicken panini he enjoyed it good food good portions fair prices
we has lunch the food and service was very good the hamburger was very big along with a lot of french fries my wife enjoyed the eggplant wrap also with a large amount of french fries

very nice and quaint place to eat i love the older style dinner layout cant say enough about how delicious breakfast was eggs over easy with corn beef hash artichoke omelette and egg bagel sandwich were delicious will was great very helpful and not pushy thanks will a place that we will visit again

typical greek diner with a huge extensive menu evreything here is always good we always get served very large portions it always seems crowded no matter when we come but never seem to wait for a table this place is very family friendly with a stack of coloring books and crayons for kids to pick from only down side is mikes unicorn seems to keep getting more expensive every time we go the servers are always busy but pleasant i would absoulutly recommend this diner to freinds and family

6 of us had breakfast there yesterday waitress was very friendly and service was very quick coffee and iced water just kept coming food was plentiful and delicious pancakes waffles eggs over easy bacon etc normal and sugar free syrup strawberries and cream we loved it

well i have to admit ive been here quite a few times for breakfast and the service never changed they are always so welcoming and attending the atmosphere is great and so is the food they have a grand menu so its a bit complex to just pinpoint exactly what to eat when you have nothing specific in mind again great service great food and very lax atmosphere cant ask for anything in the morning
receptionseating friendly efficient waitress got the job done to a mediocre level food was very good and also a very good value unicorn is still a good bet
reviewTitle: Unicorn Diner still a good, solid diner experience

reviewText: i have eaten at this diner with myself and a friend or as a meeting place for ten of us either way the service and food are on target my favorite is the beef stew the portion is so large i take the extra home for another meal the wait staff is very accommodating with requests and corrects any errors immediately when you have a large group order mixup are bound to happen a friend of mine eats here twice a week with her husband good pricesespecially with specials lots of dessert choices too

i have been here couple of times people working there werent very nicedishes and especially portions were pretty bigand also tasted good i was there for breakfaststhey were pretty pact the fact that they are working open for 24 hours doing its job and also the location not bad too busy area

our family of 4 ate here for breakfast service was prompt and efficient i enjoyed corned beef hash and eggs which came potatoes and toast my husband enjoyed the lox and bagels lettuce onion tomato the food was flavorful and the portions were large i ended up taking half of mine home a diner atmosphere with plenty on the menu for variety a nice change from the usual chain restaurants

hadnt been here in a while and used to love it the service was terrible the waitress was impatient and disinterested i ordered grilled cheese which was supposed to come with cole slaw and a pickle i got neither my friend ordered pancakes which got cold before we could get the waitresss attention to bring syrup coffee and water refills were nonexistentent probably will never go back
we have our union retirees meeting here every 2 weeksnever had a bad breakfast herethe waitresses are always on the ball
went too christmas eve dinner with my lady and my dad food and service was good it is always good to come to this diner when on staten island

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: reminds me of the old time cabaret settings excellent venue for music and good food wife and i attend often seen many great acts

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: after several stays at the hilton garden inn on staten island ive never been really impressed with the lodgings after a recent meal in their fancyschmantzy restaurant i havent changed my opinion my dish chicken martini was slightly driedout while my partners short ribs were completely overcooked the prices here do not include any sides other than a garnish of carrots and string beans so i ordered a side of sauteed spinach for 7 this was a large serving of awful tasting greens the staff is strictly highcaliber wish the food was
reviewTitle: The Staff---Great, The Meal---Fair to Middling

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: went for a dinner show service was good venue is nice the food could be bettervery nice place and atmosphere

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we went here to listen to a cabaret music style venue the food was really good and it was extremely crowded night that we were there wait staff is extremely friendly i felt like i was at some kind of a wedding or something thats the vibe i get it reminds me of a catering hall which is essentially probably is i enjoy the music and the vibe and i would recommend this place
reviewTitle: Great place to hang out and have fun

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: located within the hilton garden inn this restaurant is definitely a nice surprise a glamorous setting and fine italian cuisine menu had a lot of variety and some interesting twists on traditional favorites wine list was good too this hotel is located in a wooded area so unless you knew about this place you would not see it from the highway and so its a hidden gem of a place that is worth seeking out
reviewTitle: A hidden gem on Staten Island

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i was here for a private party this past weekend the room food and decor were lovely service was efficient and helpful and the food was of fine quality from my experience this appears to be a great place to host a party or special event lorenzos is conveniently located at the hilton hotel and not far from the staten island expressway exit parking is plentiful
reviewTitle: Really good restaurant for a hotel

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: a restaurant thats inside hilton garden inn hotel variety of breakfast and taste good friendly waiters

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: after a long day of driving it was nice to have the option of a nice restaurant in the hotel food service were all very good at dinner

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: went in to get a quick bite the chicken noodle soup was so good ate breakfast there two mornings they have a buffet i ordered a special nonfat omelette each morning and they accommodated me with no problem staff was very nice and remembered me from one morning to the next

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: hubby and i stayed at the hilton before our cruise so we went into lorenzos for dinner i had the linguine bologanise and hubby had nonnas chicken soup i want that recipe at first i wasnt sure about our server alex but he ended up being very attentive i highly recommend eating there
reviewTitle: Nonna's Chicken Soup was the best.

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i was not expecting the hotel restaurant to be so good and found that it is actually a destination restaurant for some of the islanders the ambience is terrific and the food was very good service was excellent as well and i was so surprised to see this level of service and food in the hotel would definitely eat here again

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: food was delicious and plenty of variety the service was excellent and the restaurant is very cozy highly recommend

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we had my moms 80th birthday here a party for 25 people from the time we arrived the service was impeccable the staff is excellent and even the owner stopped by the food was delicious everyone had a great time
reviewTitle: Was Not Expecting This Level of Service Excellence

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i expected more i have been to brunches all over and i just expected that lorenzos would offer more variety more choices and it didnt just your run of the mill bunch not that there was anything wrong with it food was good hot for the most part which is nice the gent making the omelets seemed put out that he had to make them maybe a bad day who knows
reviewTitle: Standard Bunch was disappointing, Just lie any other

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the hotel we stayed at contracted with lorenzo for a full breakfast the break fast was just ok when food is kept in steamers it sort of over soften the food especially the patotos

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: very nice brunch here selection of foods was very large something for everyone lots of delicious desserts i am partial to tiramisu and it did not disappoint very busybut not overly noisy the piano player was excellent servers very attentivetaking plates and refilling glasses promptly fairly expensive at 8600 for two including tax and tip good for now and then richard and lois nicotra are excellent hosts
reviewTitle: Curtis High School 50th reunion farewell brunch

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: while staying at the hilton my husband and i thought wed try this restaurant it was terrific the food was delicious i had the pappardelle ribbon pasta like egg noodles with shrimp and scallopsi cant say enough good things about this dish excellent service as well i was pleasantly surprisedwe went to the brunch on saturday and the amount of food choices was one of the best ive been to will definitely go back

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: my wife and i went for a late dinner after seeing a taping of the late show full disclosure we lived in antwerp for 3 years so we know our belgian food and beer tons of great belgian beer options my wife had a kriek and i had a leffe we both had mussels and fries mine were thailandese and hers were traditional marinieres we both got a huge pot and a lot of fries the food was delicious server paul was fast and friendly
reviewTitle: A taste of Belgium in NYC!

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: oudejaarsavond gevierd bij bxl lekkere menu goede bediening vriendelijke mensen eten goed warm en lekker een aanrader in new york

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: les cocas étaient servis au verre et noyés de glaçons le tout pour 10la bière consommée une chouffe denviron 30cl était facturée 12les boissons sont particulièrement chères les plats étaient moyens sans plus mais plutôt à prix corrects dommage que les frites étaient trop cuites les tips nous ont été imposés sans que lon ait eu à choisir il y a de bien meilleures adresses à nyc pour manger en tout cas et ce moment à table a plutôt été une mauvaise expérience contrariante on est en tout cas très loin de ce que lon peut trouver en belgique malheureusement

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: les ribs étaient bonnes mais pas exceptionnel les sauce sont vraiment bonnes la marguerita juste délicieuse le lieu est typiquement newyorké a faire

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: wat een geweldige zaak bomvol zonder reservering en toch een plekje krijgen zelfs een groep van 8 moesten andere gasten even verhuizen super vriendelijk en gastvrij een soort van even thuiskomen in hectisch ny

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we didnt eat here but we did stop off here for a nightcap on several nights on the way back to our hotel good choice of beer expensive of course this is manhattan but its nice little bar and though we didnt try the food it smelt amazing

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: fantastic service and delicious food and yes the french fries with mayonnaise are fantastic i will be back to try the incredible belgian beers on tap
reviewTitle: Great food Great Value Great service

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: veel te veel lawaai om rustig te eten eten en drinken was veeeel te duur voor wat het was 1x mosselen 1x steak stella 05 l cola 107
reviewTitle: Veel te duur voor wat het was

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: découvert par hasard en nous promenant étant belge et légèrement chauvin nous avons réservé une table après avoir constaté une très bonne note sur tripadvisor a la carte entre autre les carbonnades à la flamande nous nous laissons tenter une excellente cuisson une viande de qualité la sauce aurait pu être légèrement plus épaisse mais cela nest quun détail pour la petite un spaghetti bolognaise avec un vrai hachis excellent repas je recommande cette adresse

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: 2 karmeliet 1 kriek bijna 50 euro te gek voor woorden uitbater hautain bediening zelf was meer dan in orde

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we ate at the bxl read bruxelles with our 13yo daughter one evening did not really know what to expect and were happily surprised the owner was super friendly explained the various options on the menu some being standard eg pasta carbonara others typical dishes from belgium eg carbonate flamande beef stew with brown beer everything we had was excellent so if you are looking for a good reasonably priced restaurant away from the times square tourist traps here is a great option for you to consider

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: staying at casablanca or any area hotels or in for a day good option great pub ambiance bar seating and tables great service nice selection of beers we had hamburgers very good french fries were not up to par mushy times square pricing will be back on our next trip we were too early for all you can eat mussels on sun next time
reviewTitle: Tasty Pub Option EZ Walk  Times Square

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: before i went to new york this is how i imagines a new york bar would be its buzzing the atmosphere is electric the owner i think thats who he was was charming and engaging the table staff were lightning quick the food is delicious we were only in ny for a few days but if i had been there for longer i would have gone back lots well worth a visit i would revisit in a heartbeat i just cant get that lamb sausage baguette out of my head it was divine

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: what a cool little place we went to eat and have a couple drinks before seeing our first show what a great place food was excellent and drinks were good service was the best weve had in nyc

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: el lugar súper ambientado de europeos queríamos desayuno y a pesar de que no tienen en el menú nos hicieron lo que queríamos delicioso

our second time at this diner good service and friendly waitresses we love their greek salad everything tastes fresh and their tzatziki sauce is the best ive ever had i havent have the opportunity to have other dishes there but if you are in the mood for a good diner salad this is the place to go

starting first with the waitress sheila very funny nice and she knows what is good at this diner there were 3 of us and we each ordered different dinners monte christo excellent the best french onion soup ever waffles with ice cream and whipped cream and chocolate wow we took her advise and it was yum will go again and again we will request sheila plus they have a bakery on site we got oreo cheesecakefantastic
the oreo cheesecake is to die for the turkey club is huge and filling even the chocolate strawberries are sweet and delectable
the food was very good and portions were large we were a rather large group and had 2 waitresses one was excellent but the other was short on patience and had a bit of an attitude

by far the best diner on staten island it is newly renovated i had the fish dinner the waitress recommended and it was better than any fancy restaurant i have been too over the years check this place out
if your in the area this is the place to go great food great service and all around great experience
i always sit at the counter because my kids like to people are friendly and professional food is good and steady

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: nice place small so wait time is long good food we had the fry chicken and avocado toast all the meals were good a little issue in the beginning as we were waiting to take our orders but waiter apologized and was awesome for the rest of the lunch

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: fun casual environment split up into three areas main dining private room area for big groups and lower level secluded and small bar the service was really great and food had interesting twists mac chz spring roll lentil tacos chickpea fries make a reservation on weekends

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: use to be trendy many years ago but now is a local classic food is good they have amazing mac and cheese in many styles and variations i recommend that is a simple menu but full of new ideas of classics

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: great friendly attentive crew food is amazing best mac ncheese ever like their wine menu a bit pricy but hey thats nyc definitely again special thx to michael for the nice table last night

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: restaurante 24h ótima opção pós shows e eventos que vão até mais tarde local barulhento e serviço um pouco lento peçam os rolls de mac and cheese e o mac attack que é uma combinação com os três sabores do cardápio original trufada e com bacon recomendo

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: wir kommen bereits seit ca 15 jahren regelmäßig in die cafeteria das ambiente die speisen und die cocktails sind gleichbleibend perfekt über diesen zeitraum kann ich das nicht von anderen restaurant behaupten die bedienungen sind sehr zuvorkommend auf die laute hintergrundmusik muss man sich einlassen wir können die cafeteria nur empfehlen

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: best place to have a maccheese after club not the best service but after 45am and few drinks more than happy

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: a new yorker suggested we meet at the cafeteria for dinner the food service and incredible chelsea atmosphere was fantastic wonderful evening with family and friends

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i am currently staying in chelsea and ive eaten here a couple of times a breakfast and a lunch the servings are huge the food delicious and they make the best bloody marys i have had in a long time well worth popping in they are always open and super friendly

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: amazing food and service i had the benedict eggs with avocado they were delicious also the coffee was very good brunch is not a brunch without mimosa so i added to the list bathrooms are really cool unisex and with lights no reservations for brunch

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: my wife and i visited cafeteria to entertain friends from out of town for lunch the restaurant offers a great atmosphere for lunch on a summer afternoon the dining room was cool and breezy from the open windows and brightthe restaurant is simply but attractively decorated service was attentive and friendly without being intrusive the quality of the food is excellent the cost is not inexpensive but equal to the value offered

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: you may remember this restaurant from sex and the city i used to go here years ago and it was a total scene its calmed down a little but still great people watching the food is pretty good the service is generally good i love the cobb salad the mashed potatoes are very good i was a little disappointed with their signature meat loaf dish its still a great restaurant and i highly recommend it

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: stopped in here based on remembering sex and the city had filmed some scenes here and we were very pleased with our food the french roast and waffles both were amazing portion sizes are good and service was veru very well hats off to the water servers who kept our waters topped up would come here again

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this is a nice restaurant to go to with your family we arrived without reservation on a friday 7 pm and they were able to accommodate us although the place was busy they have a kids menu with 4 items to choose from and then a choice of side order the kids burger is made fresh and is delicious the regular menu is very diverse and food gets made with fresh season vegetables all dishes we took were very tasty tuna salad meatloaf

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: being a certifiable macandcheesaholic i decided to try their sampling of three different mac and cheeses cheddar and fontina smoked gouda and bacon truffle oil all three were amazingly delicious and worth every penny
reviewTitle: If you like mac and cheese check this place out!

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: table wasnt ready for our reservation food took over an hour to come and waiting staff was not very friendly food is decent but not a great experience overall

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i recently took the hands on croissant making class at la mille feuille had a wonderful time and made delicious croissants our teacher clement was adorable he was so french he needed us to help with his english between our limited french and his phone we managed to communicate just fine a great group of students took home tons of croissants plus more laminated dough to make at home highly recommend

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: ottimo posto per prime colazioni colazioni o brunch sia dolci che salate da non perdere le baguette alle olive o al bacon
reviewTitle: Piccola chicca per momenti dolci e salati

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: whether you want to learn to make croissants for a future brunch or just want to have a fun morning and walk away with a delicious bag of warm croissants this class is great for anyone olivier was a great instructor showing patience and clarity to the group of diverse skills i will savor every croissant with new appreciation but with the confidence that i can make them at home too will be taking other classes in the future
reviewTitle: Greater appreciation and love for croissants now

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: took the macaron making class with my bf was surprised and thrilled to see there was only 8 of us in the class i have taken cookingbaking classes before that were overcrowded and felt i didnt get enough attention from the instructor that wasnt the case here this class was totally hands on the chefinstructor was patient and informative we left with a big box of macarons each and the recipes to make them at home i really enjoyed the class

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my daughter and i had a wonderful time learning to make french macaroons the chefowner was polite and professional the space is very small but we managed i would recommend it to others

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: instructor olivier was amazing and class was really fun i would def take another class again you get to take home a box of macaroon you made afterwards

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my mom and i recently took the macaroon baking class and had an amazing time there were 7 total bakers in the class and we made 3 different flavors everyone walked away with their own box of selfmade macaroons great as a gift for a mom in law or girls trip

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the opera almond based pastry was excellent but the cappuccino was all milk if id wanted a latte i would have ordered one

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: very fun class olivier the instructor was helpful and knowledgable left with 15 delicious croissants

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: loved learning to make macarons mille feuille the pastry chef was wonderful kind and patient 8 pupils was a very nice class size and the finished products came out looking and tasting pretty good too

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i attended the macaron class and thoroughly enjoyed the experience i learnt new tips and tricks and made 25 delicious macarons after class i had a hot chocolate and pan au raison which was delicious the hot chocolate was a stand out the cafe is very small but the fare is very good

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we went in for a quick cake i found the mille feuille a bit dry but the chocolate mousse cake was really goodwould visit again and try more things

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my husband and i had a great time taking an eclair class the instructor was wonderful very knowledgeable and helpful

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we were a group of 8 it was great fun and we all learned so much olivier is awesome the bakery serves fabulous breakfast and lunch too

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: everything was perfect especially the chef instructor and the macarons came out fantastic what a lovely shop and what a great experience

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my 13 year old daughter and i took the french macaron class this weekend and had a great time it was a small class and we learned a lot it was hands on which was awesome and chef was great really informative patient and we were even able to go home and make our own the next afternoon when the class was over we strolled around the village and had an awesome motherdaughter day i highly recommend it

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: perfectly authentic french bakery they offer an amazing array of macaroons as well as lovely tartes croissants etc their flan is unexpectedly good

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: had a reservation and was seated quickly ordered our coffee and drinks and it took 20 minutes to get them ordered our food and it took another 20 plus i had to go find salt on another table probably wont go back
reviewTitle: Food was good, service, not so much.

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we stopped at cafeteria based on a locals recommendation and she raves about the food she was right the food is delicious the mac cheese is a must we arrived at about 1pm and it was still really busy after 2 when we left great place and we highly recommend

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: stopped in for an early lunch and waited forever for our food the wait staffing was confusing we had 3 different servers stop by our table when we first got there but after placing our order we saw nobody until our food arrived almost an hour later not even a refill on our drinks the food was fine and the ac was nice so we didnt mind the wait much im just glad we didnt have a tight timeline i hate to think of the wait time during the busy hours

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the food was really good my only complaint was my fries came out cold and my friends pancakes and sausage did too but they replaced them and it was delicious drinks were not that great but could have just been the bartender

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: on the way from midtown to the holland tunnel you will pass this place on 7th ave south interesting menu poached eggs on french bread and salad were good fresh squeezed orange juice was fantastic

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i spend nearly 4 months a year in new york and live on 24th and 7th when im here so just 5 mins walk i generally visit a lot the food here is mostly excellent but the service can be so horrendous ive actually decided to stop going there both the woman on the front desk and the manager were so unamerican in their attitude to service on my last visit i dont see any reason to go here when there are so many great options in this city a shame wouldnt waste your time or money
reviewTitle: Horrendous waitress and manager such a shame

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: consiglio questo locale per il brunch in particolare per i pancake davvero ottimi se prendete un piatto però non riuscirete a mangiare altro anche le insalate sono fresche e non troppo pasticciate ottimo servizio piccola chicca sono state girate diverse scene di sex and the city

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: my wife and i were in nyc for an extended weekend and met a family member here for brunch the service was great the food seems expensive but the portions were huge if youre near 17th st and 7th ave with some time on your hands the cafeteria is a great place to eat

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the mak attack was really great fun vibe and great prices upscale but very comfortable we enjoyed our visit

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ambiente agradável e moderno o restaurante é muito movimento e geralmente tem fila de espera visitei na hora do almoço a comida estava muito gostosa preço justo vale a pena conhecer

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: good food nice music good service recommend отличное место для ланча вкусно хорошее обслуживание отличная музыка не тихое а скорее молодежное рекомендую

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i love this place and visited twice this time during a 3days stay in nyc food is so delicious and service is always very good love it during springsummer when you can sit outside portions are very generous and my favourites are the sesame tuna poke to die for salads burgers and the waffle banana split cant wait to come back

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: u want breakfast at 4pm any day of the week this is your place we came here for lunch on a sat brunch on sun food and atmosphere is fantastic

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we ordered a variety of appetizers and main dishes and out of the 6 dishes not one of them i would recommend the mac and cheese spring rolls were tasteless which was highly disappointing given all the instagram attention they get the drinks were good and well priced and the service was meh overall i wouldnt return and wont waste your time or money

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we arrived at 11am and it was somewhat crowded but manageable we sat at a long communal table by the time we left there wasnt room to move food was good and service was decent good brunch menu
reviewTitle: Good for brunch if you get there early

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: a great spot after the nightlife highly recommend the mac and cheese which is their specialty great evening crowd ambiance can be lively so would not necessarily recommend this as a family place after 9p or so if the main dining room is filled ask for spots downstairs

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: enjoyed a sunday brunch with a total of four couples for my wifes birthday vast variety of food selection food and service were excellent mr and mrs nicotra stopped by our table inquiring about our visit and conveyed well wishes and a special birthday surprise for my wife they are a class act and are to be commended for their business model and commitment to the community great value and experience highly recommend

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: pleasantly surprised at hotel the service was great and the food was absolutely delicious the server ozzi was fantastic the maitre d was excellent a very warm welcome had the calamari off the hook delicious the veal chop was out of this world i would recommend taking extra effort to make sure you visit the restaurant if anywhere in staten island ny thanks so much for the dining experience

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: had a lovely lunch alone with hubby ambience was lovely and perfectly relaxed for conversation food was very good fresh and tasty i had lorenzos salad with grilled shrimp delicious my husband had portobello mushroom panini our server was very attentive and explained all the specials they have a 1695 pre fix menu which is great value we went a la carte and i felt my salad was a little over priced especially since it only had 5 shrimp overall i am giving 4 stars

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: had a great timethank you meal was yummy device was excellent always a very nice experience would highly recommend

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: lorenzos is nothing to write home about with all the places to eat on staten island that are much better than this i am going to leave the dining here to their overnight guests

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: excellent food service but you need to ask at the hotel checkin first for the breakfast voucher if you made the reservation via hotelsonecom and maybe some other reservations systems you need to print out the page where it says complimentary breakfast becasue if you dont you are going to be charged for the breakfasts at the downstairs restaurant

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i couldnt make it until dinner so we stopped in on our way to our room i had calamari and mommy had mussels bith were very good flank steak came out perfect with a spicy aioli gravy chocolate volcano for dessert made this an unbelievable lunch
reviewTitle: Late lunch that was more like a dinner

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: our group had 2 pasta dishes a pot pie and i had the swordfishdeliciousthe breakfast had made to order omelets and a buffet for 1495

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: hotel front desk recommended us to try this place this place was within walking distance from our hotel it was thursday evening the place had plenty of room the menu featured fine dining dishes and the waiter provided us with a list of specials of the day i ordered a scallop dish from the list of specials and enjoyed it very much the service was okay and was comparable with others in that price range

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the appetizer of polenta was disgusting not any kind of polenta ive ever tasted the sauce wasnt bad but the serving was small and tasted almost like a bland custard the files marechiara was a dried piece of frozen not freshfilet with some tomato sauce came out ice cold sent it back some cheesy veggies and a limp salad im amazed that anyone can really eat this lowest quality of food it cant be that hard to get a new chef who prepares really delicious food try it out lets see if im right
reviewTitle: Fine dining?? That's a joke, right?

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: free dinner was just ok salad was good entre was sosodidnt finish it bland no taste chicken desert was cookies perhaps the actual restaurant menu would be better but i wouldnt go back to try it

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we have been to lorenzos only for breakfast once a year with friends following a high school reunion consistently the service at breakfast is just plain unacceptable we had to beg for coffee and tea and when we tried to serve ourselves from the side table used by staff we were scolded back to our seats and then had to ask twice more never again

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we were at lorenzo for sunday brunch many times last visit 2 weeks ago party of 10 as the increase in price is understandable as years goes by but the reduction of the items offeredthe advertise of prosciutto di parma and served local prosciutto plus other items isnt fare plus the carving station with cook in charge that looks at you if you ask for more i guess was one of those days but i will go back again

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i went to lorenzos on october 28th with a group of friends the host was very rude and looked like he did not want to accommodate a party of our size once seated we waited over 10 minutes for a server the server then took drink orders we ended up getting appetizers before drinks the food ranged from being cold to tasteless once we finally received the check we noticed some over charges for drinks we never had i would not recommend this restaurant

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: te duur voor wat het iseten is echt wel lekkermaar je kan goedkoper en soms beter eten voor minder gelden in bxl cafe veel lawaaiverstaan elkaar niet door de muziekde zoute is rustigermaar daar trek de manager op niet veelveel te veel toneelwil amerikaans overkomen en heeft naar mijn meningteveel strekendaarom blijven we daar weg in de zoute
reviewTitle: Te duur voor wat het is,eten

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: what a great find in the theatre district not the usual pub food or bad italian cuisine is belgian whatever that is and it is really good breakfast lunch and dinner very attentive staff really good food at a moderate price
reviewTitle: Hidden gem in the Theatre Distric

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we came into the city early and needed to grab a quick breakfast someone next to use had a waffle and it smelled so good i got it without the whipped cream which i really did not need

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: had food here a few days ago whilst on visit to nyc fantastic servicegreat friendly atmosphere and the food was superb at a very reasonable price
reviewTitle: A Really Gem Of A Place

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: our large group enjoyed the cafe all of the meals were tasty and felt traditional european our group loved the mussels and the belgian meatballs the service was very good and especially friendly they were fantastic with the kids it looked a little divey when we entered but that feeling soon passed the only complaint was the music was so very loud that is was hard to have a conversation the location was very convenient a block off of times square though it felt a world away
reviewTitle: Great Food for a Large Group

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we have been here several times i asked for my birthday dinner to be here since i loved it so much the mussels are great this last time my son who doesnt like seafood ordered steak and it had to be sent back because it was so rare ordered medium well the server was appropriately apologetic and accommodating the servers are always congenial and helpful we had a great time with great people great service and great food

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: burgers and mussels here are amazing also the fries with the dipping mayo are delicious when i came to nyc on a school trip i made reservations here and took all my friends they loved it

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we picked this place because of a recommendation from a friend who lunched there often and because of the reputation of its burgers most of the crew went for those burgers and they all enjoyed their selections the steak tartare was delicious the service was on spot we would definitely eat here again

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: my family and i had lunch here before going to the rockettes christmas spectacular show the location was perfectit was warm cozy bar style great food too

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: first and foremost as far as i am concerned that you should know about this place is that they have kwak on tap in addition to numerous other belgian beers had passed thru here numerous times but had never stopped in before had a show nearby so came in and sat at the bar had two pints of kwak which hit the spot and an order of poutine which was pretty good before heading off to my show

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: een heerlijke hangout met een goede kaart met belgische bieren en gerechten alsof je in brussel een bent de bediening is ook deels belgisch de prijs kwaliteit is dik in orde dat zie je in new york wel anders echt een aanrader
reviewTitle: Brussel in the Big Apple! Een heerlijke Belgische bar - restaurant

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: got seated right away servers were very attentive food was average i had the spaghetti carbonara which i would rate 4 stars my husband had the meatloaf dont remember its name on the menu and he would rate it 2 stars

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we walked into bxl almost by accident and what a find amazing selection of belgian beers as well as a few locals knowledgeable staff who can talk through the options and great food served incredibly fast weve tried the buffalo wings chicken sate and frites all were delicious definitely give bxl a try you wont be disappointed
reviewTitle: Great atmosphere, great beer, great food

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: need a good restaurant to go to before seeing beautiful in ny was not disappointed in bxl cafe great bar and cozy and fun food was great had the bouchée à la reine puff pastry with chicken bacon mushrooms frites spaghetti carbonara spaghetti with bacon onions cream sauce

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: great little bar vibe with outstanding food and quite possibly the cutest sweetest server i have ever seen he gave me a deconstructed irish coffee that was just perfect and we got a veggie burger and croque tomate unbelievably yummy
reviewTitle: Gourmet comfort food and relaxed dining

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: nous avons très bien mangé la carte est bien fournie et les plats sont copieux le choix de bières est top et le personnel très sympathique ne pas hésiter

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036

reviewText: the macaron class was amazing learned how to make them and took about 25 home they were delicious

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my wife and i went for a croissant class we had a fantastic time learning from the owner olivier the croissants were delicious right out of the oven and you go home with a lot of laminated dough to bake at home on top of the 1015 croissants you make at the bakery

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: took this class with my 13 year old daughter great bonding class and the instructor was awesome we brought the cookies home and they were gone im a day just wished we could have made more

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we attended the macaron making class with head chef olivier and had a wonderful time highly recommend it the chef was hands on while also allowing us to do a lot of the cooking so we could learn the macarons came out so well i brought some into work to share and received many compliments on them merci beaucoup

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we loved this macaron class i brought my 7 year old and the class kept both of us engaged highly recommend

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i had the cream mille feuille and it was really good the pastry wasnt that crunchy though but even so it was really really good

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the french macaroon class was amazing there were 8 of us in the class which created an intimate baking experience the chef was very patient and helpful he also had a great sense of humor i took my mother for a motherdaughter experience i would recommend this class to everybody

reviewText: a must do classes on line were all booked but they arranged for a private class with less than 5 days notice our authentic french chef jon was incredible he took us through all the steps from making the pastry dough to baking fluffy buttery decadent croissants with all kinds of professional tips throughout we thought it would be a once in a lifetime experience but we are already planning a trip back to nyc solely to take the macaron class yes its that amazing

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: macarons class was so much better than expected sean the pastry chef was professional gave detailed explanations and assisted each of us when needed he also had a great sense of humor oi course i purchased additional pastries on my way out how could i not the greenwich village location was charming will visit the shop whenever i am in nyc
reviewTitle: The service and french pastries were magnificent

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: found this little bakery by chance as i waited for my wife and it just so happened that we were craving flan a french pastry and they had it was delicious and it really hit the spot the consistency of the custard and the freshness of the doughuhmmm scrumptious we ended getting a baguette and an almond croissant as well so good if you are in the area stop in you wont regret it nice staff polite and courteous we will definitely go back next time were in the village

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: it was a small class of 8 care and attention was given to each guest we all went home with the recipe and knowledge to make macaroons we each left with 25 macaroon of our making wonderful

reviewText: the chef is great provides simple instructions really personable and easy going yet professional with excellent technical knowledge of french baking definitely will sign up for more classes all worthy

reviewText: we had an early dinner after a matinee at the sondheim theater we were welcomed by a friendly young woman who continued to provide us with friendly efficient and attentive service its a small relaxed establishment with very good food

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: what a lucky find i came here with my mum and my nan the breakfast was delicious and the prices were amazing best breakfast weve had in new york this place is a must if you are looking for a well cooked breakfast

reviewText: as a belgian in new york we found this belgian pub typical belgian dishes and beers on the menu for a fair price cozy interior close to time square highly recommended also for nonbelgians

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: are here regularly when i worked in n y during a business trip back to ny i was at bxl for dinner again and was not disappointed the menu has something for everyone for lunch try the steak frite this is also a great restaurant if you like mussels also a great bar for happy hour

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: do wonders food was just right for the buffet sunday brunch we are invited to celebrate a birthday a complimentary drink mimosa was included in the fare the jazz pianist kept playing during most of our stay the staff were on their toes surely because of the table hopping just to greet and get the opinions being done by the husband and wife owners even with the freezing temperature the place was packed and its obvious that a lot are regular patrons would be glad to be back

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: upscale environment with affordable prices nice open dining room for guests of all ages variety of food

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i ordered a basic meal at dinner and it was beyond my expectations but breakfast blew my mind the staff treated me like a queen and the food was amazing

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: absolutely fantastic beautiful old school italian restaurant superb service and the food was delicious recommended

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: as a traveler i am writing as a traveler this place has a very nice atmosphere but that is all that is the reason for two stars the food is horrible even though wait staff is trying but it appears to be chaotic and untrained i usually never eat at the hotel restaurants but read reviews and decided to try big mistake i tend not to rely on the local crowd reviews since some are just too lazy to drive for good food and some just dont know what s good food

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: this is an old school ny italian restaurant the ambiance was great and there was even a pianist alex our server was efficient and serviceoriented he did not miss a beat the owners greet each table and seemed genuinely interested in our group there is a private room and bar too i would recommend this restaurant

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: all we wanted was some decent food but we were pleasantly surprised by the great food and service they had a scallops asparagus and risotto entrée that was to die for and a pea soup that was equally as yummy they were able to seat us without a reservation we will definitely return if we are in the area again

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the breakfast was average but certainly convenient to be able to eat right there at night we stopped to have a drinkthe bar is not exceptionally stocked well but okay for wine beer some mixed drinks

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: my husband had the tuna and i had the salmonit was phenomenal the whole family had delightful dishes

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: been visiting lorenzos for brunch 11 years the price has naturally increased during that time some foods have been reduced or completely eliminated but the dishes still offer a wellprepared broad selection one mimosa included per person and the staff is friendly accommodating good location inside the hilton garden inn off of south avenue and the comfortable ambience is enhanced by appropriate music alternating between a guitarist a piano player recommended so enjoy

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we arrived quite late after traveling all day i raced into the restaurant at 945pm asked if we could order ozzie superb waiter went out of his way to accommodate us we ordered pasta bolanaise a large salad and artichoke hearts the artichoke hearts were presented like a lovely flower the food was delicious and service excellent the next day ozzie again went out of his way when we snacked at the bar

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: friendly bar and restaurant in the staten island hilton food is excellent and well prepared staff is very friendly and attentive plenty of parking

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: lorenzos restaurant located in the hilton garden inn is a diamond wrapped in silk clothing the hotel is amazing enough and this just makes the experience that much better an excellent wine selection and delicious food try the calamari weekly live entertainment gives this high dining experience just one more thing to enhance your night make sure you make a reservation

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i had the superb caesar salad and a pasta dish that was out of this world goodaccompanied by a fine glass of red winejust a lovely lovely place and evening

reviewText: loved the small size of 8 students it was detailed and hands on which will help when i try to make some macarons on my own at home

reviewText: i booked a private macaron class for my family and it was a really fun experience john was an excellent teacher and our macorons turned out beautiful and delicious

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: small space but intimate teacher walks you through step by step lots of fun and you make a whole box to take home

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: after having sampled their offerings and taken four classes with jean and dimitri i can confidently say this bakery is not to be missed ill be sending my friends and family there too i recommend the macarons millefeuille eclairs and croissants there is also an amazing lemon loaf and classic opera cake too plus so much more the classes are well taught and you get to eat and take home plenty of delicious results yum
reviewTitle: One of the best classic French bakeries in the city

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: this is a small friendly place with great coffee pastries and morefor breakfast or lunch or a lateafternoon visit

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: took a class on french macaroon creation the instructor was wonderful great sense of humor and so talented the area was very clean and comfortable we ate samples during the class and took all we made home my family loved them will be taking their other classes great experience for the price

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: delicious french pastriesa really good assortment also great sandwiches that are premade but tantalizingly fresh i would certainly recommend this place if you are in the neighborhood and need a bite and a seat though its small it doesnt seem crowded

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: when next to george square park in nyc you need to stop by for a quick french desert we were two families with kids and wanted something sweet we visited mille feuille store and we didnt regret it we had mille feuille eclair and brioches they all tasted amazing the coffee had a really good taste and makes you wonder what we drink from the coffee chains the only items that were not up to par baguette and bread sticks the place is a must for french sweets when in the area
reviewTitle: Great coffee and amazing Mille Feuille

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: had an awesome time during the macaroon class the instructor was wonderful got to take tons of macaroons home overal a great experience

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: went w my boyfriend to the macaron making class w chef john and it was incredible it was so much fun informative and chef is a great teacher cant believe i made macarons thank you

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: great coffee wonderful for a quick snack wonderful pastries everything is tasty so eat away to your hearts content great neighborhood
reviewTitle: Great coffee… Wonderful for a quick snack… Wonderful pastries… Everything is tasty so

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: though entrance down stairs is unassuming pizza is very good service is both helpful and friendly worth a visit in world with so many good thincrust pizza

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i love the quiet the very french pastries the wonderful morning coffeecroissant bargain a genuine necessary stop

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: imho best croissants and related in the village highly recommended not a great fan of other than standard parisian pastries so have not tried their other stuff but the croissants and pain au chocolat are great so i assume other stuff is great too has a few tables but is essentially take out of course one can easily take to washington square two blocks away
reviewTitle: GREAT croissants and pain au chocolat

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: a friend and i took the macaron class with ava as our instructor ive taken countless cooking and pastry classes and in my opinion ava was the best instructor ive ever had his instruction was clear and concise every step was timed perfectly and the end result far exceeded my expectations we cant wait to sign up for our next class thank you ava you were wonderful

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i took my two daughters to this class and we had a wonderful time the chef couldnt be more helpful and patient cant wait to try making them at home since i bought the kit definitely would recommend this class

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: had a great time learning the tricks of the trade baking french macaroons with the pastry chef the chef was very insightful and the macaroons were delicious

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: excellent macaron class small group attentive and patient instructor and the macarons we made are amazing will definitely recommend to others

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: this is a little gem totally worth a visit had a tasteful baguette and a brioche with nutella both perfect for my taste and their coffee is good enjoyed a great breakfast here will return next time around no doubt thank you
reviewTitle: Love this place. Go here for breakfast

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: food was absolutely delicious but i think 20 plus tax for fish and chips is a little over priced i only came to this restaurant because i wanted to try the mac and cheese spring rolls and it exceeded my expectation also the steak tacos were really good i will come back but probably only if they participate in restaurant week

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we made a reservation and had to wait long time before we got the table the music was much to loud and once we had our table we had to wait for over one hour so i must tell that the service is not the same anymore pity

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: not even kidding when i say the mac and cheese with truffle its so good that im still dreaming about it not sure about the rest of the food so no comments this place is open 247 i think so good to hop over after a drink or 2 in one of the speakeasies nearby

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: friendly staff very clean dining room delicious appetizers and entrees tomato soup burgers fries nice chicken paillard quinoa bowl kale so many desserts too

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: um lugar super charmoso com pessoas descoladas atendimento muito bom e comida deliciosa o mac cheese é muitooooo bom

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: simple restaurant without fancy decoration or expensive furniture however the focus is on the menu and the meals we came for a lunch and tried a burger and a salad with squid both were absolutely excellent rich salad with excellent dressing and a fine burger with excellent meet and fries we were positively surprised by the very good quality of food and a rather lower price range highly recommended place

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we came here with nine people for a birthday lunch for my daughter our friends who live in the area reserved s big table the service was great the food super fun and the atmosphere spot on we came at noon and had lunch and brunch options acai bowls great egg dishes croissant french toast were some of the dishes we had the mac and cheese three ways and the amazing desserts were a treat my kids loved the fried oreos so fun would recommend for all ages

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we had a very good family dinner with 8 of us seated in the private room upstairs at the cafeteria the private room is well decorated and the service and ambiance were lively friendly and fun everyone seemed to enjoy what they ordered among the appetizers the deviled eggs and salads stood out and for the entrees the fried chicken and waffles the asian salmon and the turkey burger were excellent

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: went for breakfast and had a very good experience food was plentiful and delicious reasonably priced and the service was great

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the biscuits they bring around were warm and delicious and the chicken and waffles were superb huge portions and delicious the garlic mash was okay probably not worth how much it cost but everything else was excellent the rest of my party ordered similar dishes or burgers and everybody loved their mains the interior was a bit crowded and probably too loud making conversation a bit tricky but well worth a visit

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: 내부 인테리어가 정말 인상적인 곳입니다 정말 깔끔하고 모던하니 세련된 곳입니다 메뉴도 다양해서 먹는 즐거움도 있는 곳입니다 저희는 여기서 치킨 와플과 버거 라비올리를 먹었고 디저트로 아이스크림 와플을 먹었습니다 양도 적당하고 맛은 좋았습니다 비쥬얼도 좋았습니다 그리고 직원분들이 친절하셔가지고 너무 좋았습니다 추천메뉴는 치킨와플 아이스크림 와플 입니다

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i was visiting nyc with my friends who both grew up in the south so we decided to order chicken and waffles at cafeteria portions were huge and food was delish we split two orders between the three of us a great restaurant for lunch if you are nearby

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: big city takes on comfort food this place is open 247 the atmosphere is great we had a very good dinner chicken and waffles we started with calamari and mac and cheese overall had a good experience

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: this gem of a belgian restaurant is close to times square and has a really exciting feel to it as soon as you open the door the staff were excellent and the food choice very varied the food was hot and very well prepared and portion size was good

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: zeker een aanrader om hier als belg te komen eten of enkel een belgisch biertje te drinken aan de toog

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: 사람이 많이 붐비는 시간대였지만 많이 복잡하지 않았습니다브런치 메뉴를 제법 잘 갖추고 있는곳이구요 맛도 나쁘지 않았습니다

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: french good gets the raves but belgian food rivals it for subtle flavors besides belgian beers are among the most delicious in the world this little place tucked in times square is a nice chance of pace lighting is low so take your cell phone for menu reading but dont let that keep you from the calamari salmon and other delights

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: great meal of meatloaf fries and beer also try the mussels almost feels like youre in belgium but maybe a bit friendlier than i remember prices are very reasonable
reviewTitle: Great place for a meal before or after the Theater

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: cozy pleasant bistro with belgianfrench food reasonable prices many varieties of mussels which are unlimited on weekends large portion of well prepared salmon nice selection of hamburgers beers and wines great bread service was attentive we needed to make a 7 oclock curtain and they accommodated us beautifully the bar in front is noisy but the tables in the back are fairlly quiet

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: nos realizaron una retención del importe en nuestra cuenta al pagar para despues cargar nuevamente el importe que ellos mismos consideraron alegando que su terminal funciona de esta forma marcaron los datos de la targeta en su terminal manualmente lamentable

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: too early for drinking but i always notice when a restaurant serves chimay beer next time ill come a bit later service was hit and miss as was the food nothing special
reviewTitle: The food and service was both OK

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: i found this restaurant by searching for a place to watch the epl game while in nyc since the game my husband wanted to watch was in the morning we went to enjoy breakfast and the game this breakfast was phenomenal we sat at the bar and the bartender was super friendly i had the waffles and my husband had the banana pancakes i highly recommend both of these dishes simply amazing

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: the pub atmosphere was cozy and not too noisy for conversation the waitress asked if we were on our way to a show and assured us we would have our order in plenty of time to make it to the theater my chicken in puff pastry was scrumptious the salmon got a thumbs up too i will definitely keep bmx cafe on my list of restaurants to return to

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: not only saved us from starving on the way to the theatre because we had planned badly but was a great find our food arrived with astonishing quickness giving us space to breathe before moving on to the theatre everything was delicious and seemed to have been prepared with care lots of belgian and other beers to choose from i hope to go back when i have more time to relax

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: ive been here twice in two months the cafes belgium with comfort foods from the continent think mussels pot pies french toast with fresh fruit burgers and fries a la brussels our first visit we had the fixed price lunch our last visit a fixed price brunch before a play broadway is right around the corner servers are very friendly youll hear french as often as english and see european soccer the minute they open

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: sympathique petit restaurant confiné à lambiance assez bruyante mais chaleureuse les plats sont typiques belges et assez réussis le personnel est sympa et francophone

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: the times square area does not have many quality restaurants the quality of bxl is excellent and unusual for the area a good moderately priced menu our waitress was friendly cheerful efficient we had brunch eggs benedict and cheesetruffle croquettes
reviewTitle: Excellent moderately priced cafe near Times Square

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: avons mangé moules frites et boeuf frites les frites étaient excellentes les moules un peu moins manquaient de cuisson pour ma part bière 10 tarif élévés deux plats 3 bières 90 vous rajouter la taxe et le tips le tarif reste chèr pour ce que cétait le restau fait bar ambiance donc bruyant pour discuter en mangeant dommage le concept belge à ny est tout de même sympa nous avons trouvé ce restau en séloignant de time square où tout les restau etaient complets il fallait faire la queue pendant 2h dehors
reviewTitle: service rapide, bon, mais bruyant et chèr

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: wonderful environment easy to follow instructions great ambiance the owner taught the class and he was great now i feel confident to make macarons at home

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: loved this class left with about 20 croissants and some extra pastry to make some more when i got home highly recommend chef was great

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the french macaron is the most difficult pastry to make so many pitfalls the class was amazing the chef fantastic and the macaroons were as they should be every step broken down and every pitfall conquered every pastry chef should be taking their macaron class here

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: フランス人人のパティシエが作るマカロンケーキクロワッサンなどが食べれますアーモンドクロワッサンが美味しかったです
reviewTitle: アーモンドクロワッサン

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: wonderfully fun and once you make the macaroons youll understand how much work goes into making such lovely treats the cooking class was so much fun and our wonderful french chef is a true artist

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: im almost afraid to tell you for fear they will sell out too soon ask them to warm it and you will be transported to paris
reviewTitle: The best chocolate croissant in the city

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i booked this class for my daughter who is interested in baking both her and my wife had a great experience and they each took home their macaroons which were delicious my daughter wants to go back for the eclair class thank you

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: le mille feuille a patisserierestaurant located in lower manhattan serves delectable french pastries and coffee in addition it offers regular classes in how to prepare and bake croissants macaroons and eclairs the short classes reasonably priced for the value introduce students to the intricacies of preparing these delectable pastries i chose the class to learn how to prepare croissants aside from the treat of tasting the results of your labors you also leave with the necessaries to prepare a fresh batch at home highly recommended
reviewTitle: Lessons on how to prepare and bake Croissants

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: fantastic session felt a little cramped and there should have been a mixer per group however the results were incredible

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we walked in by chance it tasted so good that we went back the next day and brought more baked goods home to norway
reviewTitle: Delicious baked goods and pleasant operation

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: située très près de notre hôtel cette minuscule boulangerie propose de la viennoiserie de qualité des boissons chaudes demandez un expresso si vous aimez le café le regular est comment dire infect létablissement dispose de quelques places pour prendre son petit déjeuner sur place quelques employés parlent français une bonne adresse sur broadway et 77th street west
reviewTitle: Une bonne boulangerie à la française

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: this little french bakery is a must when youre visiting the city my daughter and i took a macaroon making classphenomenal best macaroons ive ever had and their lunch was amazing sandwiches with the best breads also the french chocolate donut was the best donut ive ever eaten

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we took the macaron class early morning and had the most amazing time the chef was great and knowledgable he answered all questions and was very patient with the class we were able to follow the steps and create our own batch of macarons which we got to eat and also take home id take this class again in a heartbeat and cant wait to try another one

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: tremendous fun wonderful leaning experience a delight to get into the the details of perfection from a pastry chef will take another course in the future for sure

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the class was amazing easy to follow instructions and a lot of fun nice mix of individual and group work took so many cookies home i would definitely go again

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my daughter who lives in brooklyn signed us up for this class i expected to get to make and eat a croissant or two but we each left with over a dozen delicious croissants and dough to make over a dozen more the class is very well set up and a good time was had by all just make sure that you make your reservation early as the classes sell out also make sure that you have plenty of people with whom to share the yummy croissants

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: took the croissant class great class great teacher amazing croissant i could not have asked for a better experience

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
