reviewText: theres not many places on staten island where live piano music accompanies an exquisite meal you owe it to yourself to come to lorenzos to celebrate that special occasion

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: ate here to save time we checked in and went to eat because we wanted to go into nyc the meal was good the service was excellent and the assistant restaurant manager briana was exceptional she took the time to help us make a plan for our excursion into the city

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: about 15 people for a birthday celebration at sunday brunch the buffet was attractive and varied most items were well made and tasty but several trays were out of sterno and food was cold not recommended for scrambled eggs and bacon desserts were best part of the meal very good assortment and delicious a little pricey but a nice venue

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we had four adults between us so we tasted everything available we were consistently disappointed in everything we ate the scrambled eggs were hard the waffles bland and the potatoes had a weird taste i could go on and on to top it off the 80s love songs playing on a loop were way too loud for breakfast would not recommend
reviewTitle: Not a great choice for breakfast

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: loved loved love this restaurant the atmosphere is great have a piano playa during dinner service is excellent as is the food i might just back to staten island one nite to eat here
reviewTitle: Located in the Hhilton, step inside and its like a different world.

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: thank you again tripadvisor community i typically avoid hotel lobby restaurants but your reviews and 17 degrees with gusty wind kept me indoors at lorenzos excellent muscles app with tomato garlic sauce fun atmosphere and great service locals make the drive hotel guests stay in at least one night
reviewTitle: Great surprise in Hilton Garden Inn

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the three course meal was delicious mr mrs nicotra are very gracious hosts the christmas italian show was very enjoyable the band was a family affair and very talented a wine connoisseur was there to pair up the wine for each course i would recommend this delightful event to anyone who enjoys italian music

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we celebrated my husbands birthday in the wine room and had an excellent time the place is classy and beautiful the staff was extremely friendly and helpful in preparations menu selection and service during the party every bit of food was delicious from passed around hors dourve appetizers main dishes and of course chocolate dipped fruits for desert we and our guests had a wonderful time and will recommend the place in a heartbeat

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: my wife teenage son and i went here while staying at the hilton we were pleasantly surprised great filet mignon my picky son loved it i had delicious risotto and scallops prices are reasonable service was excellent

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i was with a group of relatives who were in town for a funeral two additional members joined the group after we had ordered so they even had to move our group of ten to a larger table the staff was very accommodating with only a few slight problems i really enjoyed my pasta dish i think most enjoyed theirs as well

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: what an overall great experience at lorenzos the entire staff from beginning to the end could not be more accomodating from initial consultation to preparation and actual event each staff member was available and ready to assist the atmosphere and the food was extremely good i wish i had plans for another event

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: what can i say the food drinks atmosphere are very elegant the staff is helpful and very attentive to our families needs my families catering event went beautifully and smootly i loved it and so did my family i would definitely have another event at lorenzos and to check out one of there show on my next visit

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: loved the italian feast dinner served at the function i attended food was unique and delicious have eaten there before and always delicikus

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: lorenzos is a great place for lunch and a wonderful spot for a romantic dinner and show the menu is eclectic and reliable the chef offers daily specials from traditional dishes like chicken parm to much more interesting dishes including seafood

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: varied menu attentive staff food tasty but overdone despite uncrowded dining room one meal returned replacement offered item taken off bill maitre d handled very well
reviewTitle: Hilton Garden Inn. Wonderful service...attractive surroundings.

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: even though we live on staten island we like to stay after the hilton garden inn and go to lorenzos for dinner and entertainment the nicoltra family are great people worth the trip

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: oh i shouldve known better than to eat at a hotel restaurant we were exhausted and thought wed give it a go the food was ordinary the service was slow and it was not cheap

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the restaurant is very accommodating i have eaten here often for social gatherings and meetings i have seen birthday parties going on and the place is big enough that those groups do not interfere with couples dining i enjoyed the pianist when i ate there one sunday afternoon he was the highlight of my meal

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: came with a big group of friends the service was impeccable the food was ok very rich american fare i had the steak the sides were great

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: urgh grim the only good thing here is kind of the atmosphere and the fact you can sit outside i had the chicken which was dry and they forgot my side of sweet potato the staff are simply there to pose and look pretty they really dont do much else except give you your food and take your money
reviewTitle: Poor service, poor food and not cheap

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: stopped in for lunch with husband and was pleasantly surprised by the menu and the great service plan on returning on our next visit to nyc

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: cute place i took few fashion students to new york for a week and this place was recommended by someone who lives there food was good but the service could be faster all and all i recommend it

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this place is one of our usual stops in nyc this time we went after arriving from europe and checking it at our hotel for a late lunchearly dinner it was not as busy as i remembered but probably this was due to the time of day service was not super but quality of the food was still good
reviewTitle: One of usual stops in Chelsea

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: nice way to start our visit to nyc had a great lunch meal with quick friendly service i had the mac attack trio of mac cheese dishes which were quite good very rich though everyone enjoyed their meals and the prices generally reasonable would definitely recommend

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ive been coming to cafeteria for nearly 10 years and one thing i can say is they are consistently amazing definitely try the mac n cheese and the mac n cheese spring rolls smoked gouda dipping sauce ftw also great place to bring out of towners

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ordered the cobb salad which was quite good was seated and served very promptly and the service was efficient but not quite warm but that was ok was thanked by the desk staff on my way out the atmosphere was lively and interesting and the good was well done
reviewTitle: Solo dinner - in a corner tucked away behind the entrance - but happy with the experience

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we liepen langs dit restaurant rond lunch tijd en zagen dat er nog plek op het terras was het interieur ziet er aardig uit en op het terras kun je heerlijk mensen kijken de menukaart is gevarieerd en bevat leuke gerechten de service was prettig en de kwaliteit van het eten goed

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: stopped by after a long college hunt for my daughter came in for a quick lunch since we were starving and i dont know if it was because i was too hungry but the food was delicious the place is also very modern and staff is polite must stop by again

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: every time im in ny i eat at cafeteria but after my burned burger the bottom looked and tasted like coal and missed toppings i wont be visiting again ny has better places to eat

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i met friends here for dinner and was pleasantly surprised trendy and hip atmosphere minimalistic design my salad was divine the calamari was the perfect texture and the dressing was superb awesome martinis great and friendly service i recommend making a reservation as there were quite a number of people waiting for a table enjoy

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: after a long delay we touched down in the city around 130am we decided to grab a bite at cafeteria since the last experience was delightful well dont know if it was because it was early am or just an off day but the food was mediocre at best atmosphere was awesome though great music and service

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i went to cafeteria for lunch after my visit to rubin museum it was very busy however the service was fast and cordial the turkey burger was incredible it is a very good restaurant and prices are reasonable

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: friendly and very efficient service authentic belgium feel beer and food we enjoyed the 29 mussels with beer sunday and monday only really good and would recommend

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we have been hoping to dine at bxl for some time and finally made it last weekend it might be close to the madhouse of times square and its tourist restaurants but it is world away the atmosphere is lively at lunch but not objectionable service is the best and the food and drink selections topshelf love the belgian brews available

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: i was craving some belgian beer and frites and found this place the beer selection is really good but the fries are really ordinary but then perhaps it is too much to expect belgian style fries outside belgium the steak was also rather ordinary i would recommend going there for a drink and ambience but not so much for the food

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: this place has very good belgian food in a typical old school nyc restaurant its crowded its loud but the food is what you are there for

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: my friends and i were going to a concert at town hall and had dinner at bxl cafe its right next door so the location was supreme and so was the food i had the bouchée de la reine chicken bacon and mushrooms in puff pastry swimming in a creamy sauce with french fries fantastic our server was david he was a real charmer he made our meal a lot more fun

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: i am very fond of moules frites and bxl has good ones with a choice of several sauces ayce with stella on sundays and mondays the burger carbonnade and meatballs are average lots of beer choices the noise at lunch and dinner make it an impossible choice once was enough we went at 400 twice when it was less noisy but still impossible to converse its a shame

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: excellent service and great staff we both had the croque monsieur and it was delicious we got there about 1145 am and by noon there was not a seat left with people waiting a little pricey but its nyc would go back

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: while looking for an italian restaurant we walked past bxl and checked out the menu as they did some pasta we thought wed eat there we were very pleasantly surprised the service was very good and the food was very tasty not to mention the tasty beer la chouffre belgian beer so good as its quite a small bar everyone is packed in quite tightly while still being comfortable this just added to the atmosphere plus it was decorated for halloween when we ate there highly recommend this place and would not hesitate to eat there again

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: overall it was ok our expectations were a little higher based on the menu but it was pretty much just a little step above regular bar food its a place i would go for a beer because they have a great selection maybe with some fries and an app but not really for a full dinner
reviewTitle: Great beer selection, food is ok

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: absolute aanrader stukje belgië in ny belgisch eten belgisch bier meer moet je niet hebben super bediening en de muziek in de toiletten laten je echt thuis voelen

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: id been disappointed by mediocre dining nearby the sandwich board promising mussels and pomme frites pulled us in what a meal what an experience the ambience was terrific crowds at 5 proved its popularity we ate an authentic european meal with great tastes excellent service reasonable prices and the most surprising thing was that it was not packed with tourists but locals id eat here again in a heartbeat rightly called a hidden gem imho
reviewTitle: Not all great reviewed eateries are alike.  this one is great!

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: nice and great place after work and have some drinks and mussels or burger tables are clean fast service and good food place is a regular bar and not quiet that might be little problem to hear and talk mussels are good but not like léon de bruxelles in paris you can ask unlimited mussels program it is 2700 and unlimited mussels and fire beer is free with french fries

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: carte typiquement belge avec plats plutot bien confectionnés et belle carte de bières un peu bruyant mais ambiance sympathique
reviewTitle: Un air de Belgique à New York

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: found this place by luck and came back twice staff is nice feels feels like a small bar around the corner it seems clear customers are regulars but anybody can fit for those interested the manager speaks french

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: this is a great little bar that is also a terrific restaurant it is located right next to town hall theater and just down the block from times square central they have very nice selection of beers and the staff is very friendly their prices are also very good terrific value we have been here numerous times and never had a bad experience

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: good food good drinks for an affordable price great service europeans meeting point for a proper beer and proper meal

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: zeker het cafe eens bezoeken als je in newyork bent alle belgische bieren en gerechten zijn verkrijgbaar stukje thuis in new york

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: on 43rd opposite stephen sondheim theatre where we saw fabulous beautiful this bistro was perfect for a before show dinner can recommend filo chicken belgium style french cuisine burgers pasta cocktails in bustling setting
reviewTitle: Good value French food before show

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: you dont go to ny to drink belgian beeryes i doi love this place now perhaps i should favour an all american bar and yet i always gravitate to bxl when im in towngreat service ambience and beer
reviewTitle: You don’t go to NY to drink Belgian beer...yes I do...

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: op aanraden hier komen eten hartelijke verwelkoming door eigenaar ober meteen werden onze glazen gevuld steeds bijgevuld met water from the tap ik bestelde hespenrolletjes met puree mijn vriend 12 kip met appelmoes en frietjes heel lekker veel als dessert namen we de brusselse wafel heel lekker vers werd geserveerd met verse slagroom en aardbeien heel grote bierkaart zeker een aanrader

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: hier als bij toeval op gebotst en blijven plakken vriendelijke belgen achter de toog en eindelijk echt koud lekker bier lekker hangen aan de toog en genieten als bierliefhebber of belg zeker to do in mid town

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: opgezocht op tripadvisor en onmiddellijk gaan eten het was er zeer lekker ik heb de carbonnade flamande genomen en die was zeer lekker en heel veel mijn partner heeft chicken saté en die was ook zeer lekker een aantal tafels achter in de zaak als je binnenkomst weet je niet direct of je mag doorlopen maar eenmaal daar helpen ze je wel verder er is wel wat rumoer daar moet je wel tegen kunnen vriendelijke bediening en behulpzaam je krijgt onmiddellijk water from the tap er komt redelijk wat volk het kan er dus druk zijn

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: i made a reservation for 5 so we could have a good table to watch the game and enjoy some lunch we arrived to be seat at a table right in front of the screen and could watch every move during the game unfortunately belgium lost but we had a fantastic time however during this world cup july 2018 we were not allowed to make a reservation when belgium was playing so we had to find another place not sure i agree with that policy
reviewTitle: A great place to watch Euro 2016

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: a happening cafe right off the main track in times square met for drinks and dinner for a long overdue catch up with a friend we had a couple of drinks at the bar and then got a table we both had monday night special if all you can eat mussels so delicious waiter was attentive and very good will definitely be going back

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: restaurant francophone avec un bon acceuil cependant la proximité de times square ne justifie pas les prix élevés pour des plats convenables mais sans plus

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: lekkere huisgemaakte bouchée a la reine kan echt wel begrijpen dat amerikanen dit appreciëren op de kaart verder terug te vinden de typische gerechten waaronder mosselen over de belgische bieren moeten we natuurlijk niets vertellen leuke ontdekking na 2 weken american lifestyle

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: stopped in for a quick dinner before a show on a hot evening service was extremely welcoming great beer selection especially if you like abbeystyle ales but what set this place apart are the mussels ive enjoyed mussels throughout the northeast but nowhere have i had a batch as good as these i cant wait to get back sunday and monday nights they have all you can eat and they allow you to mix and match their various preparations oh dont like moules frites you say the stewed sirloin tips was a hearty meal even on a steamy summer evening

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: om een vriend te begroeten die reeds 5 jaar als newyorker door het leven gaat is er geen betere plaats te bedenken echte pinten belgisch bier worden hier geschonken typische brusselse bruine kroeg die over de middag en na 5pm stampens vol zit vriendelijke bediening in het vlaams wel dure pintjes verstaanbaar want de kosten om deze te importeren zullen niet mals zijn een aanrader

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: everywhere you go in ny city or in the rest of the us you get greeted warmly and the staff pay attention to you here for a cafe that bears the name brussels the guy behind the counter is french and he is surrounded by french people and they all have that superior attitude we all loathe food ok but nothing to write home about

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: een van de weinige plaatsen waar je een goed biertje kan drinken ook het eten is lekker zeer vlotte bediening als je niet snel iets extra bestelt dan krijg je onmiddellijk de rekening zodat je kan plaatsmaken voor nieuwe gasten het was er super warm en enorm luidruchtig wat wij een groot nadeel vonden je moet bijna roepen om elkaar te begrijpen
reviewTitle: Eindelijk een lekker biertje, maar heel luidruchtige bruine kroeg.

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: неплохое кафе типа паба в центре ньюйорка рядом шестой авеню ну что сказать пиво хорошее сервис неплохой а вот еда так себе кухня заявлена бельгийская с соответствующими блюдами мидии были большие но переваренные поесть можно но скорее всего сюда на ужин больше прийдем вряд ли а так ничего если только по пиву неплохо

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: inderdaad niet meer dan een veredeld café maar wel een heerlijke belgische kaart lekkere mosselen à volonte gegeten niets op aan te merken een zeer geschikte plek voor een deftige maaltijd aan een eerlijke prijs

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: the one restaurant i visited in new york where the staff was engaged in having fun and totally ignoring the customers menu was very limited and not as advertised on their web site food was not bad service left a lot to be desired

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: place is inside the hilton garden inn great food and the owners nicotras very hands on and make sure everyone is happy its a top shelf restaurant and after a late meal on friday evenings across the hall there is a dj playing the 7080s dance music at no cover charge more mature adults over 30 and up

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: great bartenders food entertainment and good atmospheredrinks are well made and delicious bartenders are experienced and friendlycan meet someone special there

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: ate dinner with a business colleague here one night and it was just okay the service was slow especially in bringing out our dinner i think there was a large party that backed up the kitchen there was an uncomfortable time period between our appetizer and entree i had turkey chili which seemed like it was out of a can my glutenfree pasta was wellprepared and tasty but nothing to write home about my friend had lamb chops which he said were good but he didnt finish them overall rather go somewhere in the neighborhoods of staten island

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: located at the hilton garden inn lorenzos has a nice atmosphere and very good food even the coffee is great the staff is friendly and helpful

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: food was very good enjoyed our lunch wait staff attentive without being overbearing will go back give it a try i dont think youll be disappointed

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: nice that an hgi has an attached restaurant but it did not work this review is of bar service they had aiming room as well good discounts on appetizers and drinks from 47 food was under seasoned and poorly prepared top that with interminable waits and it was a failure

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: ive been to this restaurant many times since it has opened and have recently realized the menu has not changed too much of the same does not give me a reason to come back even the specials are the same i would also like the wait staff to be a little more sincere when they ask how is everything also nothing is free 3 bucks for a glass of club soda is a little bit off the charts especially the second refill after spending 300 for a family of four

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we were warmly greeted to sunday morning brunch the food was good omelet station the best but it was a chore to get coffee refills overall good will return

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: this is the 2nd party of 100 plus people we had at the garden inn and it was as perfect as the 1st party we had complete sit down dinner party with a cocktail hour and open bar and it could not have been any better the food and service at this hotel is always tops and you cant find a better place for a party we usually stay overnight and enjoy a great breakfast in the morning we cant wait for a reason to olan another party at the hilton garden inn in staten island ny
reviewTitle: Hilton Garden Inn, Staten Island NY

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i have been here several times for lunch and have not been disappointed yet last time i was there it was not crowded and our group could actually hear each other during conversation

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we are staying at the hilton garden inn for a few days we werent aware of lorenzos we tried it our first night and it was excellent the food and service were the best we visited two more times our server alex is a true professional and very accommodating we were not rushed at all as a matter of fact we were encouraged to sit relax and take our timethe chef prepared meals for us that were beyond our expectationsthank you all for a fantastic dining experience lorenzos is a great find in staten island we will definitely return

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: prompt polite and fast food was great staff was very nice small bar crowd but i did not drink food was so good i went back the next day enjoyed every bite happy customer only downside is it is a bit pricey but it is in a hilton hotels so it is to be expected it appears as though the have some pretty good live entertainment of their lineup so check before you come no shows during my stay
reviewTitle: Great food two nights take out

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i eat here all the time and it is a professionally restaurant the service and food are both excellent you cannot go wrong choosing this place

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: ive been to lorenzos a few time there is not much else in that part of staten island the food is very good but the portions are small and overpriced the lunch salads are half the size of what you would get anywhere else although the limoncello salad is to die for

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: great food atmosphere and staff cafeteria is a restaurant i visit on every trip to nyc never disappointed breakfast lunch or dinner always satisfied with the meal love their caeser salad wgrilled chicken

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: good food open 24 hours amazing dishes and lovely sweets recommend for anytime of the day they have healthy and non healthy options

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the food was good especially the cobb salad and the maccheese with smoky bacon were both great the atmosphere was very nice the only problem was the service while all the waiters were very nice and friendly the service was very slow and there were several mixups with our food still i would definitely recommend cafeteria but would hope that they improve their service

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: left my midtown east comfort zone and ventured to the west side after a yoga class on 8th and 16th the wife and i took a walk and found this place great out door seating and the place was packed there was a 58 minute wait but well worth it we got out side seating and started with a nice bloody mary and avocado appetizer both were perfect main dishes cane out after a second bloody mary eggs benedict and scramble egged with w spanish ham and cheese fantastic the staff was very accommodating

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this was a nice lil fancy diner my friends and i went to theyve been before but it was my first time the mac and cheese trip was delicious and so was the fried chicken and waffles not sure if it was the same the waffles or a combination of both but they were some of the best i ever had the aloe vera cocktail was also very delicious the staff was great friendly was a little pricey but not exorbitant i guess thats nyc for you i would recommend this place to anyone

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we waited for an hour and a half to get our food after being seated the manager said to my husband ill take care of you meaning hed compensate our group somehow he never did my burger was so dry as to be inedible it was tasteless and way overdone we waited so long i didnt want to wait any longer by sending it back horrible service we asked for ketchup and never got it this place looks good from the outside but isnt pass it by

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: while in nyc my wife and i had lunch at cafeteria twice the food and service were exceptional our waiter christian provided great service to us we really enjoyed our visit and plan on returning

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: had the green eggs and hamthose in our party had the waffles and chicken salmonblt and crispy calamari salad all were worthwhile save that i thought the calamari was a little heavy on the breadingstaff was attentive and pleasantdid have an overcharge on the bill which took two interactions to resolve itwould go back if in the area

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: beautiful and cozy place to eat in ny good food cool people and nice location i highly recommend it

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: maybe this is trendy because it was on sex and the city years ago the waiters seem not to have waiting tables as a priority they are rude and seemed angry that i asked for my meal to be sent back because my eggs were served cold
reviewTitle: Terrible service, hot food served cold

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: stopped on a whim as we were across the street walking its was really really good food cooked well and nice presentation will for sure come back

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we used to live in the area a decade ago and went back for a visit still good after all these years service was good and attentive and a nice lively crowd good choice airy with outdoor space
reviewTitle: Still good after all these years

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: 在一個星期五深宵二時到訪這間餐廳人頭湧湧還要等位餐廳設計時尚十分熱鬧侍應們都十分年輕而有能量食物十分美味必須要嚐嚐他們的招牌菜mac cheese

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i found the atmosphere too and noisy to my liking staff was generally ok but not too friendly or helpful the food was ok not great and average priced for nyc

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: our group had the mac n cheese sampler and the mac n cheese egg rolls and both were delicious the drinks were great too fun atmosphere the bathrooms are super cool too

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: delicious food we ordered the mac attack that gives sample portions of bacon goudafontaine and truffle oil mac n cheese so good my chimichurri steak parmesantruffle oil fries and over medium eggs were delectable my friends loved their chicken and waffles they said that was the best waffle theyve ever had the cocktails were very refreshing we enjoyed our brunch so much that we came back again for a late dinner the customer service was great jessica and gaddy were awesome both were attentive the wait time wasnt bad on a saturday at 1pm

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: first time i walk in this restaurant i immediately noticed the nice causal decor i got great service and the food came out in really great timing the salmon is great here very succulent and excellent with veggies i love this place

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: pasta con queso excelente los blodymary ricos tambien mini burguesas los nachos en fin lo que ordenamos estaba super rico para despues dormir ya qye veniamos de tomarnos ny

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we ordered the pate it came with regular bread slices not toasted which didnt compliment the pate we ordered bitterballen they did not taste authentic and additionally they were pretty tasteless we also ordered frikandel maybe not always on the menu and only for he world cup it was very small but it was more authentic than the bitterballen the poutine wasnt great either the chicken sateh was pretty good lastly the beer and the beer choices were phenomenal if you go for the beer a 5 star the food a 2 star thus the 3 star rating
reviewTitle: Okay but not as authentic as hoped for

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: great belgian themed restaurant on 43rd st not somewhere to go for a quiet dinner since it seems pretty popular with local afterwork types dropping in to relax after a nodoubt hard days deal making that said the food was great absolutely authentic with an antwerp sized pot of moules and frites on the side great selection of belgian beers too i was momentarily right back there in belgieland
reviewTitle: Great Belgian themed restaurant in Midtown Manhattan - very authentic

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: sometimes you dont want fancy you just want good bxl delivers with a delicious french onion soup with a depth of flavor in the broth mussels are their speciality and can be ordered a variety of ways my dining companion said they were the best she has ever had in new york the beer selection is very good making the bar a lively place to be we had a table in the rather smallish dining area where it is perfectly ok to have a lively conversation top it off with friendly efficient service and you have a winner
reviewTitle: Great French Onion Soup and Mussels

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: you could walk right by this place and not notice it all but what a great spot inside a little funky but its handy to times square and offers a good bar scene a lively dinner crowd and nice food served with a smile the walls are decorated with portraits of all the king leopolds of belgium to get you in the mood for classics such as moules frites carbonnade flammandes and excellent belgian beers

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: this place makes you feel like youre really in belgium plenty of beer choices most of which are imported from belgium did not eat but the food looked great

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: бар сразу зацепил с первого взгляда такое хорошее место чувствуешь себя как дома сладко и гладко

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: great selection of beer and moules frites generous portions of mussels served in a small roaster with a delicious wine sauce reasonably priced right across from the stephen sondheim theater where our show beautiful was playing highly recommend
reviewTitle: Go for the Mussels and Beer!

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: met with friends on first morning back in nyc beers are excellent here and it has to be said that their bloody mary would do serous damage if you had more than 1 absolutely wonderful had eggs benedict for brunch which was very good actually returned later in the week for a beer with a client great place which is close to the office so will revisit

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: good food and service delicious desserts a great selection of beers wifi available great spot overall

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: bxl cafe times square is one of 2 bxl belgians in manhattan it is small busy and very loud the food menu is limited but the food was good mussels are a specialty they offer a variety of selections they have a nice beer selection on tap in bottles the service is friendly but at peak times can be a little slow they seem to be a little disorganized when they are busy like bringing the main course while we are still working on our appetizers

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: excellente cuisine service au top et les bières délicieuses et lambiancesonore mais elle fait partie de lendroit a recommander

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: de hamburger was verbrand voor de helft de frieten waren niet te eten enkel de stella was lekker neem oorstoppen mee want iedereen zit hier te roepen teleurstellend

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we had the waffles with fresh berries coffee and fresh squeezed orange juice staff was very friendly and helpful

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: delicious food loved the moulesfrites good service great beers a little loud soccer on the tvs and after work trip to the bar for many but a great beforetheater meal we were 2 and ordered a salad and some mussels and a beer each make sure to get a table that seats 4 no room on the table to hold all the plates
reviewTitle: perfect mussels and great Belgian beers

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: my bride and i visited prior to a saturday matinee for lunch her bourbon lemonade was a good choice eleodee our server originally from lyon was very helpful to me in selecting my two beers the clientele was speaking french and the european football on the several tvs gave the cafe an ambience of belgium our sandwiches were great they use open table for reservations

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: je conseille fortement pour se sentir chez vous lors de votre séjour très bonne cuisine et bon accueil

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: a great valentines day menu i was happy that my wife booked us there for dinerif i can i will go back again when the restaurant has their special menu daysa real different experience for valentines daywell done

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: went for valentines day dinner table was ready at my reservation time and seated right away food was very good lots of good wines to choose from there was live piano music which was very nice

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: this restaurant serves a wonderful brunch but i would not consider returning for lunch or dinner i have attended parties and dinner events many times and found the meals to be marginally good however brunch is quite a treat and requires reservations on sundays it is situated in a lovely hilton hotel the bar is very nice and attracts an older crowd there are many private events and weddings at the hotel and so crowds vary in any case it is often a festive friendly environment

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: great place to eat and enjoy been there over a dozen times and i have never been disappointed food is excellent service is excellent the servers are polite and friendly

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: ive been staying at the hilton garden inn where loenzos resides we typically eat breakfast every morning and dinner a couple of nights per week the food is not too pricey and isusually wellprepared for dinner i have had their seared tuna veal scallopini and crab cakes it has all been very well prepared and service is generally good

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we got to eat a delicious meal of salmon pasta and eggplant rollatini while watching a terrific show waiters were excellent and very friendly i loved watching the snow fall through the large picture window delicious dessert and specialty coffees too im coming back in june for jay the americans it was worth the hour trip there and three hours back on sat in the blizzard it wasa great cause we could stay in the hilton that night and not have to drive back home in the dark rev meryl james

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we were six diners on a saturday night good food we had calamari appetizers and steak and pasta entrees the ambiance and service were top notch a lovely room with piano music set the tone for a terrific evening this one is a real winner

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: a must go for a special occasion but expect a bigger bill here food and service are both excellent

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the food was served hot and the portions were good price is very reasonable we went on a monday night and there was no entertainment the staff was very friendly and service was fast

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the food was superb service was excellent prices surprisingkly reasonable be sure to check out the specials

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: ate here after a late night wedding party awoke to eggs bacon and waffles oh boy just what i needed freshly made omlettes anyway u want fresh fruit

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: weve been fortunate to attend several shows at lorenzos restaurant at the hilton garden inn on staten island the talent was excellent couldnt find better in the city the meal was enjoyable and the service was excellent
reviewTitle: A Manhattan Evening on Staten Island

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: had breakfast for two mornings that we stayed in the hotel the food is basic and ok since no other options nearbythis will do

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: wait staff was fantastic very attentive piano player during dinner nice touch delmonico ribeye was one of the best steaks i have ever gotten at a restaurant as a professional grillmaster i was quite surprised
reviewTitle: One of the best steaks ever!

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: bar area was ok nothing special always had at least one little tiny flying bug annoying usboth at the bar area and at our dinner table dinner was ok the onion soup not good at all very bland and tasteless service was very good but the food not so good chicken was tough tasted like it had been frozen we had breakfast there too was average scrambled eggs and bacon ok everything a little dry maybe go out to eat if you are staying at the hotel

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i was quite pleased the cavatelli with broccoli rabe and sausage was tasty and wellprepared jasmine was welcoming gracious and knowledgeable the room was bright clean and pleasant theres a lot to like here i will definitely eat here again

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: テラス席と中に広い客席があります どちらも陽当たりが良くのんびりした午後におすすめです スイーツやコーヒーはマンハッタンにしてはリーズナブルでした美味しいですがボリュームが凄いのでシェアしてちょうど良い量です そして店員が皆さんとても親切で気が利きます バーニーズやウィリアムズソノマチェルシーマーケットにも近いのもポイントです
reviewTitle: 陽当たりの良いカフェBanana salted caramel waffles

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ate here a while back good service nice french toast staff were more or less polite and friendly loved the coffee and orange juice the latter being freshly squeezed the only complaint i had was the long wait on a sunday morningalmost had to wait an hour to get a table

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: far too loud for a diner if you want to discuss with your date rushed service undefinable taste everything seems to be deep fried the main dish is already served when we did not yet finish our starter signature dish is chicken on waffle which made no sense unless you want your main and dessert at the same time a most disappointing visit especially when i read the recommendations

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: en ganska skön restaurang med goda burgare min favorit trevlig stämning och bra service extra skönt lite senare när solen når ner till uteserveringen

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: in nyc you just want to grab something to eat even late at night this is a great spot to grab tacos sweet potato fries and mini mac cheese i love the basement seating as well
reviewTitle: Love this place for late night eats

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i havent been here in a while since the revamp but when i returned it was lovely prices increased but food was still good it is worth checking out if you are an out of towner or a local
reviewTitle: Late night with friends was a really good time!

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: food is very tasty coffee is pretty darn good service is also pretty good menu is limited but covers most of the categories um theres only one bathroom in an open format stalls are private but when youre washing your hands before you leave a female might be entering it messes with your mind for a second did i enter the ladies room by mistake
reviewTitle: Very good food - let me warn you about something

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: turning a hohum cafeteria in a place to go has been achieved with cafeteria though with the transformation comes an increase in price its worth it the mac and cheese is fabulous the pulled pork terrific fries nothing special but quite tasty everything freshgiven the neighborhood the clientele changing demographics and just general prices needed to keep up with this areas decades long refacing prices are fair at best ask for jacob hes the best and will treat you well to your hearts content

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the drinks are delicious and so is the food i went for breakfast and had a buttermilk biscuit breakfast sandwich and it was wonderful the food is pretty pricey but i will say i really enjoy the food i will be coming back here

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: a unique concept in a city that never sleeps all day breakfast great menu throughout the day great ambience and atmosphere another great experience of new york which is not at the heart of manhattan but a gem in the city

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: wonderful brunch we had to send back the french toast because it was cold but they remade it and brought it right back out everything was outstanding we had the cuban sandwich the turkey burger truffle fries and french toast cant wait to come back in the summer a must hit for food in chelsea

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: been going to cafeteria for a while now the food is always good just be prepared for the wait its such a popular restaurant and theyre always packed well worth the wait though the crispy fish tacos appetizer is delish the smoked gouda and bacon mac and cheese is always a must

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: very good energy good and relaxing service the place is a bit noisy there menu offer a very diverse choice at a very reasonable price the food is good i just wish they would use less mesclun there mussels selections is great so is there beer will definitely go back

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: second time here and did not disappoint great staff food excellent and nice beer selection family especially enjoyed the fries
reviewTitle: Excellent croque Madame, fries and beer selection

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: un très chouette endroit un peu bruyant mais on y mange vraiment super bien et pour un prix raisonnable seul bémol cest assez bruyant sinon le personnel est agréable et le gérant super super sympa nous y retournerons

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: i went for mussels fries and belgium beer and that is exactly what we got good selection of belgium beers including my favorite chemay bleu also really enjoyed the mussels but could have done with more fries

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: the staff is friendly and the service is quiet fast the quality of foods was good large selection of belgian beers restaurant is quiet noisy

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: going to a nearby show so without any notions of what it was we opened the door to a packed place with a euro feel she had veggie burger i had great medium rare cheese burger with great fries both were excellent service was quick professional highly recommend and btw the bathroom was spotless

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: on a family members suggestion we ate dinner here while in town being tourists we had another family in town join us and we all thought it was fantastic the service was patient attentive and very friendly we all loved the food and beer choices wed definitely return if we lived in the area great spot
reviewTitle: Wonderful service, fabulous food, and great beer choices

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: had lunch there with my son during a quick nyc visit highly recommended great quality food in large servings very friendly service fantastic location leopold ii on the walls adds a touch to the decor that you dont see often
reviewTitle: Great value, good service, fantastic location

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: what a fabulous selection of belgium beers we loved the rodenbach grand cru on draft a rare find and stunningly delicious lots of lovely ales to choose from a friendly bar unfortunately had no time to eat there this time will definitely return

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: 여러종류의 맥주를 보유하고 있습니다 음식도 맛있습니다 저녁에 활기가 있는 분위기 괜찮은 음식점입니다

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: great choice for a pre or post theatre meal known for a huge selection of beers and mussels belgian inspired so mussels frites fries are the main meals but also burgers etc very noisy in the early evening hours perfectly situated in the heart of the broadway theatre district

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: interior feels like what belgians call a brown café brasserie style typical belgian food served like beef stew or mussels large choice of belgian beers i always go back when i am around in nyc which definitely means i appreciate the food and the staff
reviewTitle: Belgians, if you feel homesick in NY, here is where you want to go!

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: veel van gelezen maar toch ontgoocheld bij het binnenkomen geen vriendelijke ontvangst kaart ziet er ok uit en ook de selectie van bieren was ok mijn vrouw en ik hadden een ceasar salad gevraagd met kip maar van die kip was er weinig te vinden nog maar gedaan met eten en hup de desertkaart voor je neus geduwd ik had de indruk dat alles gehaast moest gaan de tip hebben we zeker niet gegeven want we hebben zelfs geen woord gehoord van deze persoon

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: as the title this is a good bar for belgium beers we drank in here on a few occasions we also ate here and were served by a pretty girl with attitude not a good one may i say

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: après avoir bu un bon verre en balade nous sommes revenus pour le déjeuner et nous avons mangé léger pour éviter la fatigue daprèsmidi repas sympa restaurant plein il vaut mieux venir tôt pour avoir une place bière belge au choix
reviewTitle: café comme on l'aime chez nous

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: upscale diner feel to it lots of choices on the menu chicken pot pie was great and for january non drinkers there are good mocktails pleasant atmosphere before they turn up the music later at night good service would also recommend the ginger tuna or cobb salad

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: here for round two of my daughters birthday the staff was amazing attentive and spot on we asked for recommendations and we loved our meal chicken and waffles are perfect and the meatloaf could have served four peoplebut the mac and cheesekiller loved the atmosphere and the waitstaff michael and jacob went out of their way to make sure all of our needs were met they are the best truly the only thing i would suggest is adding kettle orange to your bar

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: again new yorkers are so helpful and willing to share special spots so here another one this place is hip trendy and so lively drinks are the best in town and the food is also delightful

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the menu isnt extensive but it does have enough great things to order like hello give me those mac and cheese spring rolls the burger is fantastic and the parmesan truffle fries are banging

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i went to the outsider art show which i always enjoy right around the corner was cafeteria having not been there before and i thought i would give it a try i had a very enjoyable late breakfast of their special french toast and a delicious coffee very pleasant and attentive service not inexpensive but very fairly priced

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: had pancakes and fruit bowl both of which were excellent outdoor seating is quiet noisy but sitting inside is fine

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: 5 of us had brunch food was very good good menu reasonably priced for nyc the room was small but wellappointed tables were somewhat crowdedgood menu the bathroom was remarkable service was average

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this place is chic and trendy open 24 hours so great if youre jet lagged the food is delicious and so are the drinks fabulous service

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ate here in a blizzard one saturday morning was well worth the 20 minute wait delicious salmon benedict served up in a trendy buzzing atmosphere charming staff and quickly served would go back anytime

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: went for brunch with friends and absolutely loved the food and coffee our server was excellent and accommodating food was so fresh and tasty definitely worth a visit smile hostess
reviewTitle: Excellent food and service, hostess could crack a smile 😀

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: perfeito e completamente fora da rota turística ambiente amplo e sem fila de espera preço justo comida deliciosa e atendimento impecável

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: home style food very warm and nice good price and good food perfect after looking around the neighborhood

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we called into the cafeteria as its pretty reliable i suppose i just wanted a practical meal which i got a tasty salad but the chicken didnt add much to it my partners mac and cheese was nice but just that the tastiest thing was the warm biscuits i dont think there is anything wrong just nothing wow the service is friendly its oki just seem to find it fine

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: très bien les mets proposés à la carte sont originaux et une fois lassiette en face de vous la saveur est là seulement comme il a été souligné dans de nombreux commentaires le lieu est vraiment très bruyant malgré laffluence le personnel reste dévoué

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i got an omelette and he got the chicken and waffles both were average nothing crazy special the waffle was described as cheddar and tabasco but we couldnt really taste any of that i wouldnt seek this place out on a special trip to nyc for for a meal i think you could do better but in a pinch it was a decent meal if you like horseradishy bloody marys then try theirs i couldnt finish it i guess i dont

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: the food was fresh and delicious the ambiance was really nice and chic the waiters were extremely friendly and attentive in their cute tight jeans we all enjoyed our food the only con was watching one of the waiters walk around and scrape the food out of the grooves in the tables i would have preferred not to have to watch that maybe do that after hours we were the first ones in the restaurant that day so obviously it was old and should have been cleaned before opening but overall highly recommend and would return

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: my family visited this chic restaurant this week we tried a lil of everything the mac attack was very flavorful and it came out hot fast the fish chips were tasty yet not greasy the fries were cooked to much though a little hard we also tried the ginger salmon and my mom finished her entire plate my daughter also had the branzino fish and the presentation was nice i also had the salted carmel milkshake it was great a must do in new york

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: three friends went for brunch first the positive my omelette with avocado and goat cheese plus roast potatoes was excellent as was the toast and coffee but 1 the tables very attractive have grooves in them the grooves are caked with ancient food which is unsanitary and unappetizing 2 the fellow who came around with the coffee was totally aloof 3 it took 40 minutes for our food to come when my friend complained it turned out that there had been a mix up in the order it was not a relaxing brunch despite the lovely food
reviewTitle: Fabulous omelette BUT I'll never go back!

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we had fried calamari that is blanch no tastenot seasoned for apetizer delmonico ribeye that is good but too much onions and the steak fries do not taste good with parmigiano cheese on them we also ordered the pappardelle wide pasta with shrimp and it was okay i had a white wine that tasted old the piano player that saturday night was awesome though overall lorenzos is a 3 star out of 5 star
reviewTitle: Service is excellent but the food is 3 out of 5 star rating

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we bought tickets to see joe piscopo you needed to buy dinner to see the show we were pleasantly surprised that the food was very tasty a little disappointed that it was a limited menu but good none the less drinks were good and not watered down pleasant atmosphere good service

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we met a group of friends for breakfast on a sunday their brunch begins at 1130 breakfast before that the food was fairly good the omelet station was the most efficient ive ever seen several cooks many pans quick order taking and turn around with a nice custom omelette its all buffet so the wait staff doesnt need to do much but we had to struggle to get coffee refilled if they just brought a carafe for the table i would have rated them very good we repeatedly had to just about beg to get refills

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: very nice atmosphere great for sunday brunch and for a night out with that significant other very nice menu located in the hilton garden the bar right outside of the restaurant very nice for cocktails

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: food familiar and prepared perfect breakfast buffet has more than adequate choices and the omelette chef is great
reviewTitle: Awesome food and wait staff...Jimmy is great! Great sense of humor.  They all are very friendly.

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: drinks were a little over priced but thats what you get at a hotel the space was pretty tight the ambiance was pretty cool slightly trendy

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we stayed at the hilton garden and felt very lucky to have such a good restaurant right on the premises we enjoyed lunch and the breakfast buffet food was tasty and the service was excellent staff were very attentive and pleasant to my children which can make a big difference for family dining

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: food not all that good and the service could be a lot betterbesides being over rated they are also over priced for food and drinks and i believe in going to a place at least three times or more before i give up on them because you can catch any restaurant on a bad night

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: delicious food great atmosphere great service ive never been there during a show but that is definitely on my bucket list

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: had dinner and a show at lorenzos in october food was very good and the entertainment was excellent i saw the a drifters in concert there was an excellent view of the stage wherever you sit

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: unlike many hotel bars lorenzos has a great welcoming vibe the place was full of road warriors and we all had a nice time exchanging stories food was good and not overly priced the place was full and the bartender was very busy but she did not miss a beat looking forward to a return visit

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: sunday dinner buffet was excellent great antipasto meatballs chicken piccata loved dessert bar with chocolate fountain

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: one of the best italian restaurants in new york and im a native new yorker ozzie was my waiter and he was friendly and extremely knowledgable this was my 4th visit and as usual it was outstanding the piano player was extraordinary and played all my requests i didnt want to leave and stayed for two hours th calamari was the best ive ever had and the shrimp was delicious if youre in new york you must make a point of visiting this hotspot prices were reasonable especially for the great food they served kudos to everyone bill bennett

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we went to lorenzo restaurant for a holiday get together the sunday dinner was wonderful we also had a birthday celebration at a sunday brunch both were excellent we will be going back again pat devine

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: this is a very nice restaurant with good food from sandwiches to steaks located in the hilton garden inn we had both lunch and dinner there and were very pleased with everything we ordered

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: not only have i been to lorenzos for a wonderful brunch dinner but i also had my small intimate wedding dinner in the beautifully decorated private wine room there the food is delicious the staff is always so attentive professional the nicotras will do whatever it takes to make your experience unforgettable

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: my boyfriend and i didnt enjoy the food at all and everybody is so old its definitely not a favorite of mine i definitely will not be returning unless i absolutely must
reviewTitle: It's kind of an old age home.

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: unfortunately whilst i like the hilton hotel which lorenzos is part of i think the restaurant is appalling for evening meals this is the 3rd and last time i try the restaurant the service was poor with arrogant and rude staff the meals when served were cold we have made the owner aware of our concerns but we wont be using lorenzos again there are plenty of other good eateries local to the hotel to ensure fairness the breakfast is superb the breakfast is cooked fresh and the staff go out of their way to help complete contrast

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: for a restaurant situated in a hotel i was surprised at the quality of service food and atmosphere we had excellent service our waiter was over friendly the food was excellent and far greater than i expected i would recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting the staten island restaurant i would recommend a collar shirt and nice jeans at the very least

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my girlfriend and i took the macaron baking class and it was awesome chef jean made the class enjoyable and the pace was great the best part was being able to enjoy the macarons that you make

reviewText: very professional exceedingly wellprepared class for making croissants and the results were excellent participants left with 15 just baked croissants and extra dough to make more at home the class was a gift to my 12yearold granddaughter who loved the whole experience

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my girlfriend and i went for a baking class for french macaroons the staff was very polite kind and professional we had a wonderful time would highly recommend

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: it was excellent we enjoyed ourselves the macaroons turned out very good clean place and the chef was friendly

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: great class learned how to make the croissant dough how to laminate and shape the dough how to proof and bake for a perfect result

reviewText: i attended the croissant and the mille feuille class here both were very informative and the individual hands on approach ensured each student was involved taking home my baked goods was so satisfying

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my husband and i were given the macaron making class as a christmas gift it was such a unique and thoughtful gift and the whole experience was really great the pastry chef john was so nice and friendly that he made it even more enjoyable the macarons we made were delicious as was the almond croissant we ate before the class

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i went with my boyfriend and we had the best time you get to learn how to make the macarons from start to finish it was so engaging and so much fun plus you get to take home 24 macarons that you make yourself highly highly recommend

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: amazing we had so much fun the instructor was very nice attentive and funny it was worth every penny and then some

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: this is a small well lit cafe where i always go to buy my bread and croissants when friends from france visit they are never disappointed its also a great little place to have a coffee and watch the street life

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: loved the classes looking forward to more food is delish too people helpful friendly informative
reviewTitle: Fabulous! I have taken the macaron as croissant class so far and am seriously looking  forward to more!

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my husband and i took a croissant making class on saturday with chef dimitri that we highly recommend the class was immersive each student had their own station so we could each work through every step which is usually my problem with many of these cooking classes chef dimitri was clear and helpful and the best part was we came home with at least 15 croissants plus the dough to make another 1015
reviewTitle: Great classes offered at this quaint bakery!

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: it was a present for christmas for my son he had a wonderful experience and so did his friend they both learned how to make croissants and brought them home to enjoy with their families

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the class was excellent and informative the teacher was enaging and helpful so happy i got to bring home such delicious croissants

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i have been visiting millefeuille for over 2 years and it is always a pleasure the food is excellent and the service friendly i also took their croissants making and eclairs choux workshops and i had fun while learning about french pastry making i am a customer for life 3

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i just took their macaron class and i could not have been happier with the experience or with the yummy treats that we created chef jean was amazingvery informative hands on and patient i gained a terrific understanding of and new respect for one of my favorite desserts i highly recommend the class

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my daughter and i took a macaron making class at this quaint little french bakery chef jean was the perfect teacher helping with every step and the final product delicious

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: great baking class and hand on experience i still cant believe i made eclairs they were delicious and i cant wait to make them again at home

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my son 10 and i attended the macaron class with a friend and his mom my son loves macarons the instructor was thorough friendly and he really teaches you about macarons and the process we had a great time and were able to take home 2 dozen cookies each

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
