reviewText: we have searched all over time square for good food on a budget this place is amazing a gem in the sea of rocks potato cake amazing pancakes delicious

this is a great place to hang out first of all they have a lot of beers on tap and theyre very good theres also a full bar and a big food menu but best of all in addition to their indoor seating theres a courtyard with outdoor seating as well as its own bar its a great place to pass a summer evening
ruime keuze aan verschillende eigen lekkere biertjes van de tap kan van 1 glas tot hele pitcher drinken zelf halen bij de bar en eten zelf bestellen bij de keuken gezellige drukke tent
their crafted beers were very interesting unique seasonal taste that was very refreshing if you like well crafted beer stop in we did not eat so i have no review of the food

ambiente super agradável serviço simpático e eficiente comida espetacular wow eles têm um prato de petiscos de couve de bruxelas e cerveja incrível não tem como melhorar não é à toa que fica cheio wowww
some good brews here lots of help from the bartender to select a good match not too crowded in the daytime great area to explore

one of gowanus best huge selection of beers nice space delicious meatballs odd layout bar is in the back but food is good bring it to own table huge selection of beers not too expensive feels like i should be in portland or fun spot probably not to good for big groups right off fourth ave
sehr legere atmosphäre das bier ist für einen österreicher etwas gewöhnungsbedürftig aber ok die burger sehr gut aber klein

from simple to complex ipa to stout there will be a beer for everyone here i had a great time reading all the flavors in all the beers my friends and i managed to grab a table and we ordered some food the hot chicken sandwich was probably the best chicken sandwich i have ever had the fries were great too my friends got a burger very good and a yogurt bowl looked good but i was already shoving chicken in my face and didnt manage to try it

the beer is very good i particularly liked the threes wandering bine with 19 different beer types there is something for everyone the best thing is that it was not packed and you could move around the music was also very good a very nice place to sit and drink beer with friends
we sat at the bar lucky to get seat to sample some of the local beers they were great this is a very busy place on a very unassuming location the bartenders were very friendly and knowledgeable

we stopped in here on a saturday afternoon to check out their beers and we were not disappointed the space is really inviting and the back patio is fantastic it was really busy so we waited a while for beers at the bar but their beer selection was great we didnt get food but some friends we were with did and they raved about the hot chicken sandwich
nice place for a weekend beer hunt with friends always packed with a lovely outdoor space very limited beer selection

this is a big place with a couple of levels and an outside garden space the beer room looked nice but we opted for the outside order pay and take your drinks from the bar space outside quite a few tables you have to find your own space a lot of people were just standing and drinking

very friendly staff considering the bar was jammed both times my coworkers and i walked from our hotel around the corner to unwind from marathon work days overall the beer was cold and the food was typical bar food once we were able to order look forward to coming back to this place the next trip to brooklyn
reviewTitle: Nice Bar But Way under staffed during the week!

reviewText: my friend and i stopped here out of brewery tour of brooklyn it was pretty busy but we managed to find a bench outside to sit on while we enjoyed our brews the patio area was pretty nice on a summers day

not a typical place to have brunch at but it was the perfect choice as it was not crowded and offered some limited but very delicious choices the beer was very good and you can get it in a variety of sizes the man behind the bar is very helpful and could help you if you cannot decide on top of all of that they have a very cute garden in the back where you can spend a lovely time in the sun
this place is great the beer and hard cider are excellent the staff is top shelf very hard working and very friendly

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i ask for the concierge to suggest a place that have deep fried oreo and they recommended this place its really casual and not pretentious but the food is just basic and not particularly good their deep fried oreo is definitely not as good as the one at catch and not even their signature mac and cheese are particularly good

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this is a great location and open 24 hours for late night clabbers in the area the mac and cheese is supposed to be to die for but i didnt think it was as good as what i make at home it was honestly quite bland however the chicken pot pie was amazing and i would absolutely recommend it it tastes just like homemade comfort food the service was just ok my server was cocky as if he didnt need my tip and didnt care but the food was good for sure

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we stumbled on this place while staying in manhattan its name didnt describe the great cuisine within it is all in black white with young waiters upscale atmosphere but reasonable we had the calamari which was tender and flavorful with hot peppers the pear salad was full of fruit for a change with all sorts of extras thrown in the burgers were flavorful perfectly cooked to order and we finished off with the mile high carrot cake wow a multi level layer cake with cream cheese and butter cream frosting stood 8 off the table deeeeeelicious
reviewTitle: Had Fun Hear while antiquing in Mahattan

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i always eat at least one meal at cafeteria when i am in nyc they do a good job with ramped up comfort food i am not normally a big fan of meatloaf but theirs is great i have always had good experiences with the service there and the prices are a decent value this may seem odd but if you eat there check out the funky restrooms

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: thankful for this delightful restaurant in chelsea which is open late enough for me and my 3 daughters who are hungry travellers arriving from the west coast it offers a diverse menu to suit our palates and appetites we ate there twice once for dinner and had the macaroni and cheese and once for dessert where the banana split on waffles was wowed and shared and the chocolate cake was delic service was excellent and we did not feel rushed prices low altogether a great choice

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: with so many high priced fourdollar sign meals its just nice to have a meal that isnt a 50 or more but is still delicious i had the turkey burger and it was delicious we loved the atmosphere and we loved that we didnt have to be all dressed up after a day of sightseeing im so glad a friend recommended this to me before our trip

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: absolutely the best restaurant ever in the city everytime im in nyc i have to come here to have dinner food is delicious waiters are friendly and professional and the atmosphere is unique try their maccheese chicken with waffle and white grape martini i love it well done guys
reviewTitle: The best Restaurant in the city

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: i went there for brunch and was really impressed with the service and quality of the food the dishes my friend and i took were fantastic

reviewText: we walked into the brew place next store looked at the beer list and left walked into bxl and loved it now we like belgian beers so that helped but eugene was great super friendly and glad to share a taste of the beer wife had a cheese burger i had pasta carbonara awesome i cant wait to return

reviewText: a very acceptable spot for predinner fare across the street from the sondheim theater and the show beautiful pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food excellent soups great salads interesting and tasty entrees vibrant bar scene the only knock is on the noise level which is very highif you can get beyond that this is a very pleasant and satisfying spot to get a good meal before the show

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: a little bit of authentic brussels in the heart of new york this brown cafe style bar and restaurant serves authentic and unsophisticated but tasty traditional belgian food including mussels frites and waffles but also carbonades beef stew or bitterballen hard to explain but tasty a wide selection of belgian beers the atmosphere is like a place in brussels the bartender speaks french and english the radio plays french songs and soccer is on the tv great for a break or to hang out with friends

reviewText: we stopped in here prior to our broadway show and ordered a beer imagine our surprise when an 8 oz goblet of beer turned out to be 12 without tip although we assumed that it was popular due to the amount of people in there it was too rih for our blood

reviewText: we were visiting midtown with friends and stopped by here for dinner before a play the food is outstanding along with the service of course get the mussels with any of the sauces but the mariniere is the most classic and the best combined with the fries its the signature belgian meal and the best thing on the menu the wine list is a bit limited but good quality but its the belgian beers you come for there are no bad choices

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: mille feuille could not be more charming and the class was a delight our teacher took us through each step of the process inviting us to actually make and layer the dough ourselves as well as shape our own croissants and we happily skipped home with 12 of our own homemade croissants each and dough to make another batch they were delicious and id like to think i could accomplish them or some semblance on my own in the future would recommend for family friends or solo

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i took the macaron class there had a blast met some really nice people the teacher was great very informative and the macarons were very delicious it was a nice clean place the pastries looked very tasty

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we absolutely enjoyed the class well try to do this at home its very useful for people who like to have a fresh warm croissant at the morning

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my daughter and two friends took this class and loved it they came out with a bag of almost 20 freshly baked croissants and dough to make more

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: what a pleasure to stay at a hotel with a real and very good restaurant for everyone not just guests nice bar area warm restaurant and very good food at reasonable prices i recommend the gnocchi buttera

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: lorenzos is delicious ive been to eat several times went for a work event just recently and have been several times before the restaurantbar is a great place to entertain clients bobby one of the bartenders might be older than many of his coworkers but he is probably better than most all other bartenders ive ever encountered and hands down that was the best chocolate martini ive ever had

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: just because its in the hilton doesnt mean a thing food was not that good expensive service was slow disappointing considering it is supposed to be highly rated would not return

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: went to lorenzos with a bunch of my girlfriends before heading out to above we had martinis and appetizers at the bar the older bartender made us great martinis we all had alot of fun will def go back there again for more yummy drinks chrissy

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: located at the hilton wonderful staff make me feel like i was a regular there my water was always full i did not feel rished and the food was out of this world not your usual dry chicken breast sandwich i ordered steak which was made to perfection while the prices are a little high it is new york and you get what you pay for i highly recommend this place especially if you are staying at the hilton

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: great place with a feel of being in the city without going smart decor as well as a bounty of tapas to choos from before diving into the main coursesthe fresh guacamole and baby lamb chops are excellent friendly wait staff good as welljust b prepared to wait but its worth it

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we had the pleasure of seeing the louis prima jr show at this fine restaurant cabaret our table was excellent the room is lovely and the menu and food was outstanding the prima jr show was fabulous and the saxophone playerbeyond words dont miss and evening at lorenzos we also enjoyed the overnight package as the hotel is great and they treat you so special we cant wait to return you are missing a great weekend if you dont spend time here

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: i ate here several years ago and thought it was one of the better places i had eaten in nyc however they are going thru renovations so unless you are staying at the hotel or at the hampton and just need a place to eat and dont want to drive then go elsewhere until they get finished i hope they return to what they were before renovations and i expect they will but for now i will stay away

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: good portions good service wine food ambiance is nice tables not on top of one another and its quiet just the perfect blend after traveling on a plane with the chaos of airport activity

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we had our family reunion dinner and breakfast at lorenzos and were extremely satisfiedthe staff were very accomodating food quality and menu variety were excellent

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: this is an americanitalian cuisine food and service was excellent this is the perfect place for a special getaway or party

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: we were at lorenzo before but this was our first time for sunday italian dinner which was very good great food and front desk was very friendly only server needs to find time to smile and the place was empty so wasnt busy at all he not even said bye when we left and he was right next to us but we will go back

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: dont know why this restaurant was empty food and service were great its walking distance from the hampton and housed in the hilton gardens try the specials they were great

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: located in the hilton garden inn on lois lane dont blame me i didnt name it we were there for breakfast on sunday the fixed price buffet includes juice coffeetea fruit cooked to order eggs and omlettes french toast waffles pancakes breads and more for a hotel restaurant to offer all this for 1295 is almost unheard of but you heard it here try it

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the staff was courteous friendly and the service was wonderful the food was excellent and not too pricey though on the top end would definitely eat here again

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: kudos to vito murat and the entire staff at lorenzos that served our party they were very attentive to a group of 8year old baseball players and their families who had traveled to the area for a baseball tournament we put this group dinner for 40 together in a weeks time and the delicious food and great service enabled all of us to unwind after a day of baseball games thanks again for a very nice evening

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: had a wonderful experience for lunch with my gf food was amazing and the size was astounding for a lunch menu definitely recommended i have been here for sunday brunch and dinner never any complaints

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we stopped here for brunch and were not disappointed staff were happy and friendly the food we ordered we shared which was delicious just ask for extra plates bowls sharing is ideal if you are not big eaters clean and tidy with outside seating to people watch

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: good breakfast menu go healthy with fruit and yoghurt or go for the pancakes and waffles large portions nice spacious place open 247

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: came here for a business meeting quite noisy but def better than pain quotidian across the road in every way breakfast menu good and food 4 star coffees not so great and service frustrating 35 stars would give it another shot

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: we ate there at our first night in new york and it was really good we ordered salmon and california salad and both of them were great also there is a lot of beers cocktails and the atmosphere is nice

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: went for lunch and couldnt have enjoyed it more had the best pancakes of my life lemon mascarpone with blueberries people on both sides of us kept asking what i was eating because it looked and tasted so amazing thick yummy bacon and strong fresh coffee completed the experience the staff was super fun quirky and attentive without being overbearing was recommended by two different friends that are nyc pros and it was all they said and more

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: absolutely the best restaurant ever in the city everytime im in nyc i have to come here to have dinner food is delicious waiters are friendly and professional and the atmosphere is unique try their maccheese chicken with waffle and white grape martini i love it well done guys
reviewTitle: The best Restaurant in the city

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: this place offers great 24 hour eats and delicious cocktails ordering a salad and the trio of mac and cheeses we were not disappointed both were delicious each mac and cheese exuding a unique flavour all perfectly cooked with a crispy top the avocado salad was gorgeous with a perfect dressing a nice light accompaniment to the heavy mac and cheeses theres a wide selection of cocktails all delicious the staff are friendly and the atmosphere is great definitely want to go again when i have the time

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: my son and i had a delicious dinner served by a friendly and efficient waitress i had the delicious salad and soup and my son had a macaroni and cheese specialty dish along with divine french fries all food was fresh and tasty

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: food was good but service was awful i think our server donnovan purposely did a bad job because the tip was automatically included on a party of 2 we had to ask the hostess for a server it took him over 15 minutes to greet us i understand it was unexpectedly busy but he passed our table several times he could of at least quickly greeted us and told us he wouldve been with us momentarily the doorman and hostess were great

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ive been going to this place for a few years now have take basically everyone i know here and have gone for birthday dinners the last two years its easily my favorite restaurant in manhattan and the best mac and cheese ever i would definitely suggest the mac attack and the fried oreos are soooo good atmosphere is great a bit loud and younger crowd and its open 24 hours which is awesome

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: μετα από μια βόλτα στη νέα υόρκη ο δρόμος μας εφερε στην 7η λεωφόρο πολυ ωραίο περιβάλλον ωραια προσεγμένα πιάτα ωραίες σαλάτες κ κυρίως ωραιο το κοκτειλ της φραουλας με διόσμο κ σόδα
reviewTitle: Ωραίο περιβάλλον κ πολύ καλή εξυπηρέτηση.

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: ive come here dozens of times in the past few years you can never ever go wrong by eating here i usually come here after the club is over around 45 am it is usually full any day of the week their mac attack is what theyre known for as well as their chicken and waffles everything there is good the service is always up to par as well

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: great spot for late night dining since theyre open 24 hours a day the food was pretty decent i had the chicken and waffles which seemed bland initially but then i dipped it into the sauce and wow that made all of the difference it was delicious try them out

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: my teenage daughter recommended we do dinner there as we had family visiting despite it being a sunday evening there was no wait and we were seated immediately what an absolute treat from sabrina our server who gave us great suggestions on what to choose the entire evening was a hit food was so darn good we plan to go again this week end great food great ambiancegreat service what more do you need

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: went for lunch with a friend the place is really nice easy and simple the terrace is very nice inside and outside decoration in white food is amazing i had a delicious salmon great portion of veggies are which i really appreciate perfectly cooked the sautéed spinach amazing and what can i say about deserts uffff we had the peanut butter tower and roasted banana better impossible perfect flavor and beautiful texture you really need to try it great service and good prices community back soon

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: a friend recommend the cafeteria and she was dead on the food was great i had the grilled salmon blt i shared the sampler mac cheese with my guest wow this has just become my second go to in nyc the service was be aware the the atmosphere is very active and a little loud

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: сказать что здесь шумно это ничего не сказать ты такое впечатление что находишься на стадионе чтобы услышать друг друга приходиться кричать срывая голос заказать чтото тоже не представляется возможным поесть в такой атмосфере просто невозможно блюда были посредственными наш официант изза шума не правильно понял заказ и принес одно и тоже блюдо два раза не советую ходить сюда либо заранее бронировать столики на улице мы проверили если открыть рот и просто начать орать во всю глотку то никто не обращает на тебя внимания так как ты вливаешься в общую атмосферу

placeAddress: 119 7th Avenue New York, New York City, NY 10010
reviewText: arrived at 5am because of being jetlagged the place was playing house music the crowd was young eating hamburgers and pasta at that hour the crowd looks like they were eating after a heavy night of partying the place is cool young and funky its us that looked out of place

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: this is a great place beer bxl is wonderful so are the mussels the endive ham augratin was great i better stop now desert is coming
reviewTitle: Not Closed Today - It's All You Can Eat Mussels Day!

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: missing belgian after a visit this summer we decided to get a fix while in nyc for the weekend reservations easily obtained and got a pre show reservation on a sat at 5pm mussels are generous albeit small but tasty fries are not thick and hearty like in belgium however they are cooked the same way and just perfectly done son loved the shrimp croquettes and husband and i thought the onglet à léchalotte was outrageous beer selection is amazing and so loved having a de halve maan straffe hendrik fro bruges

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: stopped in on the way to a meeting for a quick lunch and was so happy i did fried calamari comes with a small salad garnish which was perfect calamari is tender and lightly fried more calamari than breading salad and dressing were a nice addition would get a larger version next time will keep this in mind the next time i visit this client

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we were a party of 12 having split between broadway matinees we had agreed on spec to meet here it proved an excellent choice on arrival it seemed all tables were booked but the staff asked us to wait at the bar soon came back to offer a table for some the drinks were very good the food was excellent the staff were friendly helpful efficient prices were average atmosphere was excellent

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: at 530600 on a wednesday the bar was a scene for which the term happy hour was invented when we left about 7 it had calmed down considerably despite the crowd at the bar in the front we were seated immediately in the rear dining room which was crowded but had some empty tables despite the numbers service was impeccable as was the food and drink for two people we split an order of pate and order of moules marocaine moroccan and 4 pints of beerplenty for all and under 100 even with a big tip nice stopping place
reviewTitle: Loud, Energetic, Convenient, Great Casual Meal

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: stopped here after a broadway show what a delight felt like being back in flemish belgium great beer mussels fries frites lots of atmosphere very friendly service

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: un très bon chois de bières et de nourriture belges personnel très sympa ambiance décontractée autres bxl à new york et tout aussi bien
reviewTitle: Un bon café-resto belge à NYC

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: reasonable prices exceptional greeting at front door delicious omelette and coffee great start to the day

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: my wife and i went for lunch midweek the bar area was busy even for early afternoon on the wednesday before thanksgiving we shared the croque monsieur without the béchamel sauce essentially a grilled ham and cheese with an order of frites with our belgian beer we enjoyed the food the atmosphere and the drinks

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: ate here last night a couldnt fault it great selection of drink the filet mignon was spot on and the muscles delicious

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: pub parecchio rumoroso e angusto dove si fermano per bere o per mangiare persone di tutte le età cibo buono servizio semplice leggermente alti i prezzi in proporzione a ciò che offrono

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we had a very comfortable christmas eve dinner at bxl east with nice enough food mostly moules cooked in every way and sauce possible and a good bottle of white wine the bill came to 86 with a gratuity charge at 18 of 1548 together with tax coming to a total of 10911 the bill has written on it service is not included i may well be stupid but what is a gratuity if it is not a service charge someone please tell me
reviewTitle: Nice place, shame about the service charges

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we stopped here before a concert it was very busy but we lucked out and got a table quickly the beers were amazing and we just had calamari but it was delicious and the dipping sauce made it even better its not cheap but nothing is in nyc

placeAddress: 125 W 43rd St, New York City, NY 10036
reviewText: we had dinner with our two small children and although it was very busy the service was great and the food generous and tasty we had a very generous serve of mussels which was delivered to our table promptly and our wine and water was always refreshed if your kids dont like a lot of noise and hustle and bustle this might not be the spot to go for dinner

this restaurant and microbrewery is a great place we went twice in one week while visiting all the beers were full bodied rich and tasty the aged beef burger medium rare was to my liking and the regular cheeseburger was to my wifes liking all the food was hot and delicious it even has a nice garden area outside which was more quiet than inside we really enjoyed this unique joint
so happy to have the opportunity to visit twice in the acc tourney week great beers duh everyone knows this cool bottle shop

their beer was fine good even was pretty crowded which is to be expected i suppose most impressive thing for me was the other drafts on tap and the fact that you could basically pour smallmediumregular sizes of everything
this is a brewery with a little bit of everything great beer a food counter coffee shop and tiny but well appointed bottle shop nice people and a great guest tap selection as well highly recommended
ótimas cervejas próprias e de outros locaiscomida boa e informalvaleu a pena pelas ótimas cervejas
we called in here for a few drinks before a game at barclays the beer is good but it gets a bit difficult to get them when it gets crowded
土曜日に行ったのですが店内もガーデンも地元の若者でいっぱいでした気軽にオーダーするならキャッシュオンデリバリーのカウンターがよいのですが混雑しているのでオーダーのタイミングが重要かもでもスタッフがうまく順番にオーダーを聞いてくれましたそのへんで立ち飲みしていてもよいですしパティオのベンチに座ってのんでもok気取らないカジュアルな雰囲気です
reviewTitle: 地元の若者に大人気のブリュワリー

reviewText: actually the craft beer that i had short attention span ipa was very tasty nice the in house eatery the meat hook dish i got the meat plate was a bit to be desired just a few slabs of different types of meat and a few olives small pickles with some small onions at least i think thats what they were probably should of got the tacos it was yeah just okay nothing to put on them as of oil or even mustard seemed a bit trendy yet hey im just a midwesterner from minnesnowta dont you know
reviewTitle: Maybe just come for the Craft Beer!

reviewText: visited during the day with my husband the food is average but the setup to purchase drinks and food can get confusing for a tourist the fries was wayyyy to salty for me my burger was average ive heard the vibe is better at night

threes brewing ofrece varias cervezas tanto propias muy buenas como de otras cervecerías el lugar está muy bueno cuenta con un patio excelente para los días con buen clima la comida está separada de otro local que queda en el mismo espacio pero funcionan separados
マイクロブリュワリーによるバーですが醸造所といった趣はなくおしゃれなバーですね入店後すぐフードカウンターがあり定期的にショップがいれかわるとか私が訪れた際はブルックリンキッチンに出店するミートフックのバーガーショップでした ビールはピルスナーを注文美味しかったですがクラフトビール屋のバーにしては雰囲気が洗練されすぎているようなもっとローカル感があってもいいと思うのですがあまり感じられませんでした
reviewTitle: クラフトビールが楽しめるバー

reviewText: nice spot good bar lots of interesting beer small tasting portions changes monthly for food invitational right now mexican very good snack food tacos nachos etc backyard patio rustic pleasant
reviewTitle: Nice spot off the beaten path

reviewText: around the corner from the fairfield inn this lively brewery is a neighborhood gem terrific brews highly recommend the table brew and the food was delicious the menu changes regularly street tacos when i was there and coming from denver where street tacos are the best i was pleasantly surprised how good they were here in nyc friendly staff and the garden out back is a nice place to hang out on a warm night highly recommended
nice spacious patio out back with tables for two or picnic tables that are good for groups good place for a date friends even families a few babies and strollers were welcomed by staff

had lunch here with friends family the place has a good vibe a good selection of local beers wines although a bit overpriced the food was very good went down a treat think its very good chefs changing all the time like a pop up restaurant so the menu changes regularly sorry to only give it four stars due to the price of the drink

when traveling with my brother theres going to be a microbrewery stop this was close to the hotel so we went there the did not offer flights but they did offer free tastings of the ones you wanted to try so that was pretty awesome we ordered a cheese tray which was expensive and very small but this is new york the employees were as friendly as they had time to be

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my son and i took this class and it was very well taught and a lot of fun great location in the west village and cozy bakery

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: stunning bakery that serves the best french macaroons could go there every day and more a real gem in ny

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the instructor was great his name was dimitri and i think he teaches most classes it was very user friendly having experienced bakers to newbies in our class everyone was able to go home with amazing croissants i will definitely be make for the macaron making class

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i took this class with my mom and we had a great time we loved that it was a small group the instructor was very kind and dynamic and the macaroons were delicious it was a great forum to learn the technique and ask questions thank you

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: closed for upgrades of the display case i was looking for good listed place to take amid day dessert but no way only this was best in my way i hope to come back sooner for good dessert
reviewTitle: Closed for upgrades of the display case

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: the most difficult class of them all but the chef makes you feel like you are actually mastering the art and you get to go through every step of the process be prepared to eat croissants for a while because you leave with a dozen of them plus dough for another batch a lot of fun and even as a beginner youll make really good croissants

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: they premeasure and combine things before you arrive you simply mix with a spatula and press the mixer on if you think youll truly learn how to make macarons you dont really its fun but i thought we would get to make from beginning to end
reviewTitle: Don't truly come out of it learning how to make macarons

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i took the french macaron class here and i loved it it was informative paced well and i definitely learned the process i wish we had a chance to work with the egg white separation as thats what i really wanted to learn everything was premeasured we mixed whipped the egg whites but the class was overall great i went on my own most folks had a friend or family member but it wasnt an issue id highly recommend

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: registered to attend the french macaron preparation class and it was fabulous our instructor provided us an apron the recipe and first everyone washed their hands i was so glad he did this hygiene is very important when baking im not sure on the spelling of dmitri our instructor therefore he has to forgive me if ive misspelled his name dmitri was patient and explained the nuisance to making perfect french macarons you take home what you make had a great time would definitely go back and take another class note the bakery is very cozy

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: it was a small group of 8 we were taught how to mix the batter and we piped the macarons on our own its a good class to take would recommend it

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: went there by accidentsloved mostly what they made from the cronuts macaroon coffeeits a must to stop and see their lovely delicious products small cafe yet its cozy and the owner is great he teach some pastry class and i was able to book a class for making macaroon with my 8 years old daughter loved it will come back for more baking lessons
reviewTitle: little great french cafe in NYU...

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my niece and i planned this activity to celebrate her 20th birthday we had such a great time the place and atmosphere was fun the chefinstructor made everyone feel comfortable and was easy to follow directions the macarons that we made lookedand tasted liked they were made by a professional chef i would definitely recommend this activity it a nice way to spend the afternoon

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: great time all around making macarons dimitri was an awesome instructor and made it super easy for us

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my 15yearold daughter and i took the macaron class at mille feuille it was a lot of fun and our instructor was very knowledgable and patient i actually think we could make them at home with a little practice we left with a lot of yummy and beautiful macarons and some great memories

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: we had a great time learning to make macaroons the instructor was very patient and showed everything step by step the best part was seeing the results of our work and trying them and sharing with our friends and family

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: i took a macaron baking class recently and it was amazing pier was so patient knowledgeable and professional i highly recommend to take this class i had so much fun and brought home 24 macarons that i personally made

placeAddress: 552 Laguardia Pl between 3rd Street & Bleecker, New York City, NY 10012-1459
reviewText: my friend and i signed up for a baking class did not know what to expect and ended up with a great experience dimitri was very patient and detailed with his teaching everybody was friendly the baked products are very delicious highly recommend it to try it

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: had the sausage meatballs and there were outstanding service was great very classy and a bit pricey but it was worth it

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: six of us from out of town needed a place to eat that was walking distance to our hotels so this was the choice not knowing what wed get and having eating a lot of bad hotel attached restaurant food in our day we all left the table full and extremely happy with our meals not sure i will ever be in the area again to go back but would recommend it to those who are

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: okay just had breakfast wait staff were nice and the chef was very personable and accommodating may try dinner next time if we stay there

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: both my wife and i had paninis for lunch they were just ok nothing special very expensive especially for what we had would not bother to stop again if for some reason im off the beaten path again
reviewTitle: Nothing special except the high price

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: its ok but after all youre in ny surely you can find somewhere better to eat had dinner only one night and it was not bad not great but edible i would say 6 out of 10 prices are appropriate for the area

placeAddress: 1100 South Avenue Hilton Garden Inn New York/Staten Island, Staten Island, NY 10314
reviewText: the service was great in the dining room i had the special which was lamb over risotto with peas and mushrooms the favor and presentation were wonderful the calmari panella has an asian influence and was very good
